cxd4 10. cxd5 Nc5 11. dxe6 $1 Bxe6 (11... Nxd3 12. exf7+ Ke7 13. Ne4 Nxc1 14.
Qxc1 {or 14.Nd6 with a promising attack. The value of the novelty depends on
this    position.}) 12. Nb3 Bxb3 13. axb3 Be7 14. Bc4 $1 b5 15. Bd3 {Weakening 
of the queen's side is worth two tempi. Now white has a big advan-   tage.} Rb8
16. Bf4 Rb7 17. Rc1 Qd5 18. Qe2 O-O 19. Rfd1 Nxb3 (19... Ne6 20. Be3 Bc5 21.
Qc2 {and white gets a material advantage.}) 20. Rc3 $1 {
Winning move. Black is not able to defend himself against numerous threats.}
Rd7 21. Bc2 Na1 22. Rxd4 Qe6 23. Bxh7+ Kxh7 24. Qd3+ Kg8 25. Rxd7 1-0

