1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. Bf4 Bg7 4. e3 d6 5. Be2 O-O 6. h3 c5 7. O-O Qb6 8. Nbd2
Be6 (8... Qxb2 $2 9. Nc4 Qb5 (9... Qb4 10. c3 $1 Qb5 (10... Qxc3 11. Rc1 Qb4
12. Rb1 Qc3 13. Rb3 $18) 11. Nxd6 $16) (9... Qc3 10. Rb1 $1 {/\ Rb3}) 10. Nxd6
$16) 9. Ng5 Bd7 10. Nc4 Qc7 11. c3 h6 12. Nf3 b6 {During the game I thought
that Artur stood better but that doesn't seem to be the case} 13. Bd3 (13. a4
Bc6 14. a5 $140 Nbd7) 13... Qb7 14. Re1 Bc6 $1 15. Ncd2 Ne4 $1 16. Nxe4 Bxe4
$10 17. Qe2 Nd7 18. Ba6 (18. a4) 18... Qc7 19. Nd2 Bb7 20. Bxb7 (20. a4 Nf6)
20... Qxb7 21. e4 {I'm not so happy with this move. It doesn't spoil much
though-White's mistake comes later} cxd4 22. cxd4 Rac8 $1 {Black has equalised}
23. Nf3 Rc7 24. Qe3 Kh7 25. Qb3 Nf6 $1 26. e5 (26. d5 Rfc8 {
And White will find it difficult to control Black's activity along the c-file})
26... dxe5 27. Nxe5 Rcc8 28. a4 Nd5 $10 {
The knight on d5 solves Black's problems} 29. Bd2 e6 30. h4 h5 31. a5 Rc7 32.
a6 $6 {White is overreaching} (32. axb6) 32... Qc8 33. Qd3 Rd8 34. Bg5 Rd6 35.
Qa3 Bxe5 $1 36. dxe5 Rdc6 $17 37. Qb3 Rc2 38. Ra4 R7c4 39. Re4 Rxa4 40. Rxa4
Re2 41. Qf3 Re1+ 42. Kh2 Kg8 $1 (42... Qc7 43. Rc4 $1 Qxe5+ 44. g3) 43. Bf6 Qc7
44. g3 Qc2 $19 45. b3 Re3 46. Qg2 Rxb3 47. Rd4 Rd3 48. Re4 Rd2 49. Rf4 Kh7 50.
Rf3 Ne3 $1 0-1

