1. c4 {Ribli  Kortschnoj  Topalov has a broad repertoire with both colours. In
Madrid he predominantly played 1.e4 but right after in Las Palmas kept trying
1.c4} Nf6 2. Nc3 e5 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. g3 Bb4 5. Nd5 e4 6. Nh4 d6 7. Bg2 $1 {
A real improvement (if you can call a move like Bg2 earth-shattering!).Topalov
shows that g5 is not athreat} (7. Nxb4 Nxb4 8. a3 $1 (8. d3 exd3 9. exd3 O-O
10. Be2 Bh3 {Korchnoi-Adams Wijk aan Zee 1993. White was blown off the board
in 26 moves  after some inaccurate play but anyway has no advantage at this
point}) 8... Nc6 9. d3 exd3 10. Qxd3 {is Gurevich-Adams Munich 1993. White won
a long ending but Michael was doing quite well out of the opening (full
compensation for the exchange).}) (7. a3 {Kortschnoj} Ba5 $1 $13) 7... g5 {
Show me!} 8. Qa4 $1 Bd7 (8... gxh4 9. Nxb4 Bd7 10. Nxc6 Bxc6 11. Qb3 $14 {
/\ Qc3,b3,Bb2}) (8... Bc5 $5 9. d4 $1 (9. Nxf6+ Qxf6 10. Bxe4 Qxf2+ 11. Kd1 Bd7
$19) 9... Bxd4 10. Bxg5 Bxb2 11. Rb1 h6 $1 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Nxf6+ Qxf6 14.
Bxe4 $14) (8... Ba5 {Ribli} 9. Nxf6+ Qxf6 10. Bxe4 gxh4 11. Bxc6+ $16) 9. Nxb4
Nd4 (9... gxh4 $5 {Ribli}) 10. Qd1 gxh4 11. Nc2 $1 {
The knight on d4 has to be eliminated.} h3 $2 (11... c5 12. Nxd4 cxd4 13. d3 $1
$14) (11... Nxc2+ $1 12. Qxc2 Qe7 (12... Bc6 {Kortschnoj} 13. O-O (13. b4 {
Ribli} a6 14. Bb2 $16) 13... Qe7 $14) 13. d3 {
and white is a little better but not more}) 12. Bxe4 $1 Nxe4 13. Nxd4 Qf6 14.
Nf3 $16 Bc6 15. O-O h6 16. d4 $1 (16. d3 Ng5 (16... Nc5 17. d4 $16) 17. Nxg5
hxg5 18. e4 $16) 16... d5 (16... O-O-O 17. d5 Bd7 18. Be3 {/\ Ba7,Bd4}) 17. c5
O-O-O 18. Ne5 {this looks like a Petroff with White having a pawn on e2 !!}
Rhg8 19. a4 h5 20. Ra3 $1 {Overprotecting g3} Qe6 (20... h4 {Ribli} 21. b4 $36)
21. b4 f6 22. Nd3 $1 $18 (22. Nxc6 $5 $16 {Kortschnoj}) 22... h4 23. Nf4 Qf5
24. b5 Be8 25. Qd3 Rd7 $6 26. Qb3 Rg5 27. c6 $1 Rdg7 28. cxb7+ Kxb7 29. Qf3 Qd7
(29... hxg3 {Ribli} 30. fxg3 Nxg3 31. hxg3 Rxg3+ 32. Qxg3 Rxg3+ 33. Rxg3 $18)
30. Nd3 Bh5 (30... hxg3 31. hxg3 (31. Bxg5 $18) (31. Bxg5 $18 {Ribli}) 31...
Rxg3+ 32. fxg3 Rxg3+ 33. Qxg3 Nxg3 34. Nc5+ $18) 31. Nc5+ Nxc5 32. dxc5 Kb8 (
32... Bxf3 {Kortschnoj} 33. c6+ $18) (32... Qe7 $5 $14 {Kortschnoj}) 33. Qxf6
Rf5 34. Qd4 Bxe2 35. Re1 hxg3 36. Rxg3 Rxg3+ 37. fxg3 Qe8 38. Rxe2 (38. Rxe2
Qxe2 39. Qh8+ Kb7 40. c6+ Kb6 41. Qd4+ $1 (41. Qb8+ $4 Kc5 42. Qxa7+ Kc4) 41...
Ka5 42. Bd2+ Qxd2 43. Qxd2+ Kxa4 44. Qc2+) 1-0

