{
Black would be simply 2 P up and White's counterchances would be very nebulous.
}) 17. fxe7 Qxe7 18. Bf5 Nc5 19. Nc4 $44 {><>> Now White has active pieces and
some play against Black's K , which balances the situation.} Qf6 20. Qd2 d5 21.
