Nf5 25. Nf3 Be7 26. Ng5 Bxg5 27. fxg5 Qa4 28. Ra3 Qc2 29. Rad3 Qb1 {
0-1 Roofdhooft,M-Tukmakov,V/Antwerp op(04) 1993}) (13. f5 {Boensch} Ne5 14. Rh3
Nfg4 $15) 13... Re8 (13... d5 14. e5 Nd7 {with the idea ...f6}) 14. Qf2 a6 15.
f5 Nd7 16. Qg3 Qb6 17. Nd1 (17. Qxd6 Nde5 {Leaves White's queen awkwardly
placed. Black threatens 18...Bf8. Also possible is 17...Be5!? when 18.Qxd7??
loses to 18...Rcd8} (17... Nde5 {Boensch} 18. fxg6 hxg6 19. Be2 Red8 20. Qa3
Nd4 21. Be3 Qc6 $44) (17... Be5 18. Qxd7 (18. Qa3 Nb4 $44) 18... Rcd8 19. fxe6
Rxd7 20. exd7 Rd8 21. Nd5 $10)) 17... Nce5 18. Be3 Qa5 19. Bg5 h6 $6 (19...
exf5 20. exf5 Nxd3 {with counterplay e.g.} 21. cxd3 (21. Qxd3 Re1 22. Ne3 Rxa1
23. Rxa1 Bxb2) 21... Qe5 $1 {and now} 22. fxg6 (22. Bf4 Qxf5) (22. Qh3 Qxf5 $1)
(22. Qf3 Qxf5) 22... fxg6 23. Bf4 Qe2 24. Nf2 Bxb2 25. Rad1 (25. Rab1 Rc1 $3
$19) 25... Be5 $17) 20. Be3 Kh7 21. Qh3 exf5 (21... Nc5 {Boensch} 22. f6 Bf8
23. g4 Ncxd3 24. Bxh6 (24. cxd3 Nxd3 25. Bxh6 Bxh6 26. Qxd3 Qg5 $17) 24... Bxh6
25. g5 Ng4 $19) 22. exf5 Qb4 23. Nf2 (23. fxg6+ fxg6 24. Bxg6+ Nxg6 (24... Kxg6
$2 25. Qf5#) 25. Qxd7 Rcd8 $44 (25... Rf8 $17 {Schulz,A})) 23... Nc5 (23...
Qxb2 $2 24. fxg6+ fxg6 25. Bxg6+ Nxg6 (25... Kxg6 {Boensch} 26. Nd3 Nxd3 27.
Qf5#) 26. Qxd7 $36) 24. a3 Qa4 (24... Qxb2 25. Rab1 Qa2 (25... Qxa3 26. fxg6+
fxg6 27. Bxh6 Kg8 28. Bxg7 Kxg7 29. Ne4 {looks equal}) 26. Bxc5 Rxc5 27. fxg6+
fxg6 28. Rxb7 {with complications and equal chances}) 25. Rae1 Ncxd3 26. cxd3
h5 27. Bd2 Ng4 28. Ne4 (28. Nxg4 {Boensch} Qxg4 29. Qxg4 (29. fxg6+ Kxg6 30.
Qxg4+ hxg4 $17) 29... hxg4 30. fxg6+ Kxg6) 28... Qc2 29. Rc1 (29. Nxd6 $4 Qxd2
30. Rxe8 Nf2+ $19) 29... Qxb2 30. Qf3 Ne5 31. Qe3 Qxa3 {Black is collecting
pawns while White's last few moves seem rather aimless. Time trouble perhaps?
White certainly doesn't appear to have enough compensation for two pawns} 32.
Bc3 Kg8 (32... Ng4 {Schulz,A} 33. fxg6+ fxg6 34. Ng5+ Kg8 (34... Kh8 $2 35.
Bxg7+ Kxg7 36. Rc7+ Rxc7 37. Qxe8 Nf2+ 38. Kg1 Nh3+ 39. Nxh3 $18 (39. gxh3 $2
Qc5+ 40. Kh1 Qxg5 41. Qf8+ Kh7 42. Rf7+ Rxf7 43. Qxf7+ Kh8 $10)) 35. Qf3 Qb3
36. Bxg7 Rxc1 (36... Kxg7 $4 37. Rb1 $18) 37. Rxc1 Kxg7 $19) 33. fxg6 fxg6 34.
Qb6 Rf8 35. Qxb7 $2 {A blunder which should lose instantly. 35.Rfd1 appears to
be the best chance to survive a bit longer but White has a lost position
anyway} (35. Nxd6 {Boensch} Rxc3 $19) 35... Qa2 $4 {
And now Black returns the blunder!} (35... Rxf1+ 36. Rxf1 Rxc3 37. Nxc3 Qxc3 {
is winning easily for Black}) (35... Rxc3 $19) 36. Bxe5 $1 {Black must allow
mate or lose a rook. I suspect that both players were short of time during the
last few moves} (36. Bxe5 Bxe5 (36... Rxc1 37. Qxg7#) 37. Rxc8 $18) 1-0

