c6 8. d5 Ng4 9. Bg5 f6 ({
Black should not grab the b-pawn at cost of development:} 9... Qb6 $6 10. O-O
Qxb2 11. Bd2 {with the following 12.Rb1}) 10. Bh4 c5 11. O-O Nh6 12. Ne1 Nd7
13. Rb1 (13. Nd3 {Dolmatov} g5 14. Bg3 f5 15. exf5 Nf6 16. Qd2 g4 17. Bh4 Bxf5
$132 {Ioseliani,N-Dolmatov,S/Moscow/1993/}) 13... b6 14. a3 g5 (14... Nf7 {
Dolmatov} 15. Bg4 h5 16. Be6 g5 17. Qxh5 gxh4 18. f4 $40) (14... Qe7 $5 {
Dolmatov} 15. Nb5 Nb8 16. b4 a6 17. Nc3 Nd7 18. bxc5 bxc5 19. Qa4 g5 20. Bg3 f5
21. exf5 Nf6 $132) 15. Bg3 f5 $6 {Black has no choice but to push the f-pawn,
otherwise he has no counterplay. The disadvantage of this continuation is that
the white squares are becoming weak} 16. exf5 Nxf5 (16... Nf6 $142 {Dolmatov}
17. Nf3 Nh5 18. Ne4 Rxf5 19. Nxe5 (19. Nfd2 Nf4) 19... Nxg3 20. Nc6 Nxe2+) 17.
Ne4 h6 18. Nc2 Nf6 19. Bd3 Qe8 (19... Nxe4 {Dolmatov} 20. Bxe4 g4 21. Qxg4 Ne3
22. Qg6 Nxf1 23. Qh7+ Kf7 24. Rxf1 Rh8 25. Qg6+ Kg8 26. Ne3 $40) (19... Bd7 {
Dolmatov} 20. Ne3 Nxe4 21. Bxe4 Nxg3 22. fxg3 $16) 20. Ne3 Nxe4 21. Bxe4 h5 (
21... Nxg3 22. hxg3 a6 23. b4 cxb4 24. axb4 {White is definitely better}) (
21... Nxe3 22. fxe3 Rxf1+ 23. Qxf1 {is in White's favor}) 22. Qd3 (22. Nxf5 {
Dolmatov} Bxf5 23. Bxf5 Rxf5 24. f3 Qg6 $10) 22... Qf7 23. f3 (23. h3 {Dolmatov
} Nxe3 24. fxe3 $18) 23... Nxe3 24. Qxe3 Bh6 25. Be1 Qg7 26. Bd2 $1 Rf6 27. Qd3
g4 (27... Bd7 $2 {Dolmatov} 28. b4 $16) (27... a5 {Dolmatov} 28. h3 Ra7 29. g4
$16) 28. Bxh6 Qxh6 29. fxg4 Bxg4 30. Rxf6 Qxf6 31. Rf1 Qg7 32. h3 Bd7 33. Qf3
$1 {The King side is a White's possession} Be8 (33... h4 {Dolmatov} 34. Qf6 $18
) 34. Qf5 Qf7 35. Qg5+ Qg7 36. Qh4 Qh6 $2 (36... b5 {
allowed Black to stay in the game just a little bit longer, for example:} 37.
