1. e4 {Ftacnik} c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e6 {
Alternate lines are 6... e5 and 6... Ng4 7.Bg5 h6 8.Bh4 g5. Black is ready to
play the regular Scheveningen after 6.Be2} 7. g4 $5 {
Ivanchuk demonstrates his fighting spirit} h6 8. f4 b5 $5 (8... e5 9. Nf5 g6
10. fxe5 dxe5 11. g5 $1 {is in White's favor}) (8... Qc7 {Ftacnik} 9. g5 hxg5
10. fxg5 Nfd7 11. g6 Ne5 12. gxf7+ Nxf7 13. Qe2 Nc6 14. O-O-O Bd7 15. Qc4 Nfd8
16. h4 Rc8 17. Qe2 Be7 18. Qg2 Bf6 19. h5 Ne5 20. h6 gxh6 21. Rxh6 Rxh6 22.
Qg8+ Ke7 23. Nf5+ exf5 24. Nd5# {1-0 Mironov,S-Popov,A/Bankia op (08) 1990}) (
8... Nc6 {Ftacnik} 9. Qf3 (9. h3 Qc7 (9... d5 $5 10. e5 Nd7 11. Qe2 Qh4+ $1 12.
Kd2 Bc5 13. Nxc6 bxc6 14. Bxc5 Nxc5 15. Qe3 Qe7 16. Rd1 Rb8 17. Kc1 a5 $15 {
Shirov,A-Salov,V/Moscow/1992/0|1/44/}) (9... Bd7 10. Qe2 Be7 11. Bg2 Qc7 12.
O-O Nxd4 13. Bxd4 e5 14. Be3 exf4 15. Rxf4 Be6 16. Nd5 Bxd5 17. exd5 O-O $10 {
Balashov,Y-Psakhis,L/Sverdlovsk/1987/0,5/31/}) 10. Qe2 Bd7 $5 (10... e5 $5 11.
Nb3 exf4 12. Bxf4 Be6 13. Nd5 Bxd5 14. exd5+ Ne5 15. O-O-O Nfd7 16. Kb1 g6 17.
Qd2 Bg7 18. Bd3 h5 $132 {Bologan,V-Novikov,I/Nikolaev/1995/0,5/42/}) 11. O-O-O
(11. Bg2 b5 12. e5 $1) 11... b5 $5 12. Bg2 b4 13. Nd5 exd5 14. exd5 Nxd4 15.
Bxd4+ Be7 16. g5 Bb5 17. Qe3 Rc8 18. Rd2 hxg5 19. fxg5 Nd7 20. Bxg7 Rg8 21. Re1
Ne5 22. Bxe5 dxe5 23. h4 Bd6 24. Be4 a5 25. h5 a4 26. g6 {
1-0 Hracek,Z-Oll,L/Parnu-A (06)/1996/ (34)}) 9... Nxd4 10. Bxd4 e5 11. fxe5
dxe5 12. Bxe5 Nxg4 13. Bg3 Bb4 14. a3 Bxc3+ 15. Qxc3 O-O 16. Bd3 Qg5 17. Qd2
Ne5 18. Qxg5 Nxd3+ 19. cxd3 hxg5 20. Kd2 {
Topalov,V-Kolev,At/Elenite (03)/1995/1-0 (54)}) (8... d5 {Ftacnik} 9. e5 Nfd7
10. Qd2 Nc6 11. O-O-O Qc7 12. Bd3 g5 13. Nf3 gxf4 14. Bxf4 Ndxe5 15. Nxe5 Nxe5
16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Bxe5 Bd6 18. Bxh8 Bf4 19. Rhe1+ Be6 20. Re3 d4 21. Bxd4 O-O-O
22. Bf5 Bxf5 23. gxf5 {1-0 Palac,M-Soln,P/Bled op (02)/1996/}) 9. Bg2 Bb7 10.
g5 $6 {This line is double-edged, but after defeat in the previous round,
Ivanchuk tries to create complications at any cost. It is nteresting to
mention that at the same time this variation was tested in the first round of
Groningen International.} (10. a3 Nbd7 11. O-O (11. g5 {Ftacnik} hxg5 12. fxg5
Nh5 13. g6 Ne5 14. gxf7+ Kxf7 15. O-O+ Nf6 16. Nf3 Nxf3+ 17. Bxf3 Qc7 18. e5
dxe5 19. Bxb7 Qxb7 20. Qg4 Rc8 21. Ne4 Rc4 22. Ng5+ Kg6 23. Qg3 Nh5 {
0-1 Shirov,A-Van Wely,L/Tilburg (07)/1996 (41)}) 11... g6 12. Qe2 e5 13. Nb3
exf4 14. Bxf4 Ne5 15. Rad1 Nfxg4 16. Nd5 Bxd5 17. exd5 g5 18. Bg3 h5 19. Nd4
Bg7 20. h3 h4 21. Be1 Nh6 22. Qh5 Nhg4 23. hxg4 Rxh5 24. gxh5 Ng4 25. Nc6 Qb6+
26. Kh1 Kf8 27. Rd3 Re8 28. Rdf3 Kg8 29. Ba5 Qc5 30. Rxf7 Ne3 31. h6 Bxh6 32.
Re7 Rf8 33. Rxf8+ Bxf8 34. Bb4 Qb6 35. Re6 Nxg2 36. Kxg2 Kh7 37. Re4 Qb7 38.
Rg4 Qf7 39. Nd4 Qxd5+ 40. Nf3 Be7 {
0-1 Shirov,A-Van Wely,L/Koop Tjuchem, Groningen NED 1996}) 10... hxg5 11. fxg5
b4 {The necessary counterblow; now White Knight is distracted from center.
After 11... Nh5 White is better.} 12. Na4 (12. gxf6 {Ftacnik} bxc3 13. fxg7
Bxg7 14. bxc3 Bxe4 $1 $17) (12. Nd5 {Ftacnik} exd5 13. gxf6 Qxf6 (13... dxe4
14. fxg7 Bxg7 15. Nf5 Be5 16. Bd4 $10) 14. exd5 Qe5 15. Qe2 Be7 $15) 12... Nh5
(12... Nxe4 $6 13. Qg4 d5 14. O-O-O {with dangerous attack} (14. Bxe4 {Ftacnik}
dxe4 15. O-O-O $40 Nd7 (15... Qa5 16. Nxe6 fxe6 17. Qxe6+ Be7 18. Qg6+ Kf8 19.
Rhf1+ $18) 16. Nxe6 $16)) 13. O-O (13. Bf3 {Ftacnik} g6 14. e5 d5 $15) (13. g6
$5 {Ftacnik} Nd7 (13... Qh4+ 14. Bf2 Qe7 15. gxf7+ Qxf7 16. Nb6 Nf4 17. Bf3 $14
) 14. gxf7+ Kxf7 15. Qg4 Qe7 16. Rf1+ Nhf6 17. Qg3 $14) 13... Nd7 14. g6 ({
Maybe} 14. c3 bxc3 (14... Ne5 15. cxb4 Nc4 16. Qe2 Nxe3 17. Qxe3 {
with the threat 18.g6}) 15. g6 $1 {is more accurate}) 14... Nhf6 15. c3 (15.
gxf7+ {Ftacnik} Kxf7 16. Qg4 Qe7 17. Rad1 (17. e5 $6 Nxe5 18. Qxe6+ Qxe6 19.
Nxe6 Bxg2 20. Ng5+ Kg6 21. Kxg2 Nd5 $17) 17... Ne5 $13) 15... Ne5 (15... bxc3
$2 {Ftacnik} 16. gxf7+ Kxf7 17. Qb3 cxb2 18. Rab1 Rb8 19. Nxe6 Qc8 20. Ng5+ Kg6
21. Qf7+ Kh6 22. Rf3 $18) (15... Qe7 {Ftacnik} 16. Qb3 d5 17. exd5 Bxd5 18.
Bxd5 exd5 19. Rae1 $18) 16. gxf7+ Kxf7 17. cxb4 (17. Qb3 $5 {Ftacnik} Qe7 18.
Qxb4 Neg4 (18... Rh4 19. Nxe6 $1 Kxe6 20. Qb3+ d5 21. Bg5 $18) 19. Bf4 $16)
17... Rh4 $1 {Suddenly, Black Rook becomes very active. White must consider
both 18... Bxe4 and 18... Rg4} 18. Qb3 (18. Bf4 {Ftacnik} Rb8 19. b5 $16) 18...
Qe8 {The critical position of the game} 19. Rac1 (19. Nc3 Rxh2 (19... Rg4 20.
h3 Rg3 21. Nf5 Rg6 22. Rad1 {with very complex play}) 20. Kxh2 Neg4+ 21. Kg1
Nxe3 22. Rf2 Nxg2 23. Kxg2 g5 {leads to complications with unclear outcome}) (
19. Bf4 Rc8 20. Bg3 Rh5 21. Nb6 Rc7) (19. Nc3 $16 {Ftacnik}) 19... Bxe4 20.
Rc7+ {Not a precise moves' order. Better was} (20. Bxe4 Rxe4 21. Rc7+ (21. Nb6
Rb8 22. Nc4 Nxc4 23. Rxc4 Kg8 $10) (21. Bf2 Rg4+ 22. Kh1 Rf4 23. Rc7+ Nfd7 24.
Nc3 $10) 21... Kg8 (21... Ned7 22. Nb6 {and White is on top}) {and if} 22. Nxe6
Rxe3 23. Qxe3 Qxe6 {the position is difficult to estimate}) 20... Kg8 (20...
Ned7 $2 {Ftacnik} 21. Bxe4 $1 (21. Nxe6 $6 Qxe6 22. Rxd7+ Be7 23. Bxe4 Rxe4 24.
Qxe6+ Kxe6 25. Ra7 Rxa7 26. Bxa7 Rxb4 $10) 21... Rxe4 22. Nb6 Rd8 23. Nc6 Kg8
24. Nxd8 Qxd8 25. Rc8 $18) 21. Nxe6 (21. Qxe6+ $2 {Ftacnik} Qxe6 22. Nxe6 Rg4
23. Rf2 Nd5 $19) 21... Rg4 $1 {The coldblooded reply! Discovered checks are
not dangerous for Black, for instance.} {Ivanchuk's hope was the next move...}
22. Rxf6 $2 {Here 22... gxf6 fails to 23.Ng5+} (22. Nxg7+ Kh8 23. Nxe8 Rxg2+ {
mating}) (22. Ng5+ Bd5 $1 $19) (22. Nxf8+ {Ftacnik} Bd5 $19) (22. Rf2 $2 {
Ftacnik} Bd5 $1 23. Qxd5 Nxd5 24. Rxf8+ Qxf8 25. Nxf8 Nxe3 $19) (22. Nf4+ $142
{Ftacnik} d5 23. Nc3 (23. Nc5 Bxc5 24. bxc5 Nd3 25. h3 Rg5 $17) 23... Bxg2 24.
Nxg2 Rxb4 $15) 22... Rxg2+ (22... gxf6 $4 23. Ng5+ $16) 23. Kf1 (23. Kh1 {
Ftacnik} Rg3+ 24. Rf3 Bxf3#) 23... Qb5+ {Ivanchuk obviously overlooked it.} (
23... Qb5+ {Ftacnik} 24. Rc4 gxf6 $19 (24... Qxc4+ 25. Qxc4 Nxc4 $19)) 0-1

