1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Be3 a6 7. Bd3 b5 8.
Nxc6 Qxc6 9. O-O (9. a3 Bb7 10. O-O Ne7 11. Qg4 Ng6 12. f4 Bc5 13. Bxc5 Qxc5+
14. Kh1 O-O 15. Rae1 f6 $11 {
0-1 Minic,D-Taimanov,M/Palma de Mallorca izt 1970 (33)}) 9... Bb7 10. Qd2 (10.
Kh1 Nf6 11. f3 Bc5 12. Qe1 Bxe3 13. Qxe3 Qc7 14. a4 b4 15. Na2 a5 16. c3 bxc3
17. Nxc3 O-O 18. Nb5 Qb8 19. Rfe1 Rc8 $11 {1/2-1/2 Lutz,C-Ribli,Z/BL 1996 (21)}
) (10. Re1 Nf6 11. Bd4 Be7 12. a4 b4 13. Nb1 d6 14. f3 O-O 15. Nd2 Nd7 16. a5
Rfd8 $11 {1/2-1/2 Damaso,R-Horvath,G/EU-Cup Thessaloniki 1996 (41)}) 10... Nf6
11. f3 Qc7 {N/} (11... Bc5 12. Kh1 Bxe3 13. Qxe3 b4 14. Ne2 Rg8 15. Rfc1 $1 $14
{Short,N-Rogers,I Manila ol 1992}) 12. a4 {Topalov made good preparartion to
the game and made first 15  moves in less then 5 minutes.} b4 13. Ne2 (13. Na2
d5 14. Nxb4 dxe4 15. Be2 Rd8) 13... Bd6 (13... d5 $5 14. e5 $140 Qxe5 15. Bf4
Qh5 $1 (15... Bc5+ $2 16. Kh1 Qh5 17. Ng3 Qh4 18. Bg5 Qd4 19. c3 bxc3 20. bxc3
Qe5 21. Bf4 $18) 16. Ng3 Qh4) 14. h3 O-O 15. a5 $5 Bc5 (15... Be7 16. Bd4 d5
$140 17. Bxf6) 16. Bxc5 Qxc5+ 17. Kh1 Bc6 (17... d5 $5 18. e5 Ne4 $5 (18... Nd7
19. f4 $14) 19. Qe1 $1 (19. Qc1 Nf2+ 20. Kh2 Rac8)) 18. c3 bxc3 (18... Rfb8 19.
Rfc1) 19. Qxc3 (19. bxc3 d5 (19... e5 $5) 20. e5 Nd7 21. f4 Bb5 22. Bxb5 Qxb5
23. Rfb1 Qc4) (19. Nxc3 Rfb8) 19... Qxc3 20. Nxc3 (20. bxc3 d5 21. e5 Nd7 22.
f4 Nc5 23. Nd4 (23. Bc2 Bb5) 23... Rfc8 24. Be2 Ne4 $15) 20... Rfb8 $11 {
It is clear now, that black's position not worse.} 21. Rf2 Kf8 (21... Rb4 $5)
22. Na4 Bb5 23. Bc2 (23. Rd2 Bxd3 24. Rxd3 Rb5 25. Nb6 Rd8 26. b4 Ke7 (26...
Rxb4 27. e5) 27. Rc1 Rxb4) 23... d5 ({Interesting was also} 23... Bxa4 24. Bxa4
Ra7 25. Rc1 d5 26. e5 Nd7 27. f4 Ke7 28. Rc6 Rb4 29. b3 f6 $13) 24. Nb6 dxe4 $1
{Simple but nice tactical resource.} ({But after} 24... Ra7 25. exd5 Nxd5 26.
Nxd5 exd5 {Black position is also OK.}) 25. fxe4 (25. Nxa8 e3 26. Nc7 (26. Rff1
Bxf1 27. Rxf1 Rxa8 28. Bd3 Rb8) 26... exf2 27. Nxb5 Rxb5 28. Bd3 Re5 (28...
Rxb2 29. Bxa6 Nd5 30. Bd3 Nb4 31. Bf1 (31. a6 Nxd3 32. a7 f1=Q+ 33. Rxf1 Ra2)
31... Nc2 32. Rc1 Ne3) 29. Rf1 Rxa5 $17) 25... Ra7 26. e5 Nd7 (26... Nd5 $5 27.
Nxd5 exd5 28. Rd1 (28. Bxh7 Re7 29. Re1 Rbe8 30. Bg6 Kg8) 28... Bc4) 27. Nxd7+
Rxd7 28. Bxh7 $1 Rbd8 (28... Rd5 29. Bg6 Be8 30. Raf1 f5 31. Bxe8 Kxe8 $13) 29.
Bg6 Ke8 ({After} 29... Kg8 $1 {
for white it will be not so easy to make draw.For instance:} 30. Be4 Rd2 31.
Rxd2 Rxd2 32. Rc1 g6 33. Rc2 Rd1+ 34. Kh2 Re1 $15) 30. Bh5 g6 31. Bf3 Rd2 32.
Kg1 ({Maybe slightly better was} 32. Rxd2 {but after} Rxd2 33. Rb1 Rd3 (33...
Be2 $6 34. Bxe2 Rxe2 35. b4 Rxe5 36. b5 $1 Kd7 37. bxa6 Rxa5 38. Rb7+ Kd6 39.
Rxf7 Rxa6 40. Rg7 $16) 34. Rc1 (34. Be2 Rb3 35. Bxb5+ Rxb5 36. b4 Kd7 37. Rd1+
Ke7 38. Rd6 Rxb4 39. Rxa6 Rb5 $11) 34... Rd2 35. Bc6+ Bxc6 36. Rxc6 Rxb2 37.
Rxa6 Re2 38. Ra8+ Ke7 39. Ra7+ Kf8 40. a6 Rxe5 41. Rd7 Ra5 42. a7 Kg7 {
ending is drawish}) 32... Rxf2 33. Kxf2 Rd2+ 34. Ke3 Rxb2 35. Kf4 {
I,ll prefer to have my K on g8} Rc2 36. Rd1 Ke7 37. Rd4 Ra2 38. h4 {Topalov los
t pawn, but active position of all his pieces+passed pawn h allow to him with
optimism to look in future.} Rxa5 39. g4 Ra3 {Judit could play now 39... Ra4,
but she understood that after rooks eschanged her winning chances will not big
enough.} 40. Be4 Be2 41. Rd2 Bc4 42. Bc6 (42. h5 $6 gxh5 43. gxh5 f6 (43... f5
44. Bf3 Rd3) 44. h6 (44. exf6+ $6 Kxf6 45. h6 $4 e5+ 46. Kg4 Be6+ 47. Kh4 Rh3#)
44... Rh3 45. h7 f5 46. Bc6 Kf7) 42... Rd3 43. Rb2 (43. Rxd3 $5 Bxd3 44. g5 $1
(44. h5 gxh5 45. gxh5 Bc2 46. Kg5 a5 47. h6 Kf8)) 43... Rb3 44. Rxb3 Bxb3 45.
g5 $1 {It was a  good time to finish game, but Judit has not very good  score
against Veselin, and she decided to continue to torture her  opponent.} (45. h5
$6 gxh5 46. gxh5 a5 47. Kg5 a4 48. h6 Kf8 49. Kf6 Kg8 $19) 45... Bd5 46. Ba4
Bb7 47. Ke3 Bc8 48. Kd4 Bd7 49. Bd1 a5 50. Kc5 Kd8 51. h5 gxh5 52. Bxh5 Be8 53.
Bd1 Kc7 54. Bh5 Kb7 55. Bf3+ Kc8 56. Bd1 Kd8 57. Be2 Ke7 58. Bd1 Kf8 59. Bc2
Kg8 60. Bd1 Kg7 61. Bc2 Kf8 62. Bd1 a4 63. Kb4 Ke7 64. Bc2 (64. Bxa4 $4 Bxa4
65. Kxa4 Kf8 $1 $19) 64... Kd8 65. Bd1 Kc7 66. Bh5 (66. Bf3) (66. Bg4 $5 a3
$140 67. Kxa3 Kc6 68. g6 $1 fxg6 69. Bxe6 Kc5 70. Kb2 Kd4 71. Kc2 Kxe5 72. Bc8
$11) 66... a3 $1 {Last chance!} 67. Kxa3 Kc6 68. Kb4 Kd5 69. Bg4 Kxe5 70. Kc3
$1 ({Veselin avoids last trap} 70. Kc5 $2 Kf4 71. g6 fxg6 72. Bxe6 Ke5 73. Bc8
Bf7 {is desperate for aWhite.}) 70... Bc6 71. Bh5 $1 Be8 72. Bg4 Kf4 73. g6
fxg6 (73... f5 74. Bh5 $1 Bxg6 75. Bxg6 Ke3 76. Kc2 f4 77. Kd1 $11) 74. Bxe6
