placed on c7, defending  the pawn on d5 and keeping control of e5} (16... g6) (
16... c4 $5 {Poluljahov,A  /\ a5, b5}) 17. h4 g6 18. Qb3 $146 {
Only this move is new.White has got a pleasent edge in the following game} (18.
Nh2 $5 {Poluljahov,A} cxd4 19. exd4 h5 20. Nf3 (20. Nf1 $5 {
Poluljahov,A  /\ Ne3 ><d5}) 20... a6 21. Re1 b5 22. Qd1 Qd6 23. Bh3 Ng7 24. Ne5
Bc8 $1 25. Bg2 Be6 $2 (25... Bb7 $11 {Poluljahov,A}) 26. Ne2 $1 {
1-0 Poluljahov,A-Hjartarson,J/New York (open) 67/584 1996 (58)  /\ Nf4+/-})
18... h5 $6 {This weakens g5, an important square . As h4-h5 is not a threat,
it was unnecessary.} (18... Bg7 19. Nh2 (19. Qa2 a6 20. Nh2 c4) 19... Nc7 {
The knight belongs to c7 square!} (19... c4 $5 20. Qc2 a6 21. Nf3 f5 $13) 20.
dxc5 $140 Bxc3 21. bxc3 Qxc5) 19. Qa2 a6 $6 {
Now White forces a welcome simplification to achieve positional superiority} (
19... Nc7 $5 {Was again called for}) (19... c4 20. b3) 20. dxc5 $1 Bxc3 21.
bxc3 Qxc5 {The only way to keep material equal,as after} (21... Nxc5 22. Ng5 {
Black loses the d5 pawn, as h7-h6 is not possible (pawns cannot go back!)} Na4
(22... Ne4 $4 23. Bxe4 $1) 23. Bxd5 (23. Qb3 b5 24. Bxd5 Rxd5 25. Rxd5 Bxd5 26.
Rxd5 Rc8 27. Qb4 $16) 23... Rxd5 (23... Nxc3 24. Bxf7+ Kf8 25. Rxd8+ Rxd8 26.
Rxd8+ Qxd8 27. Ne6+ $18) 24. Rxd5 Bxd5 (24... Nxc3 25. Rd8+) 25. Qxd5 $16) (
21... bxc5 22. Nh2) 22. Nd4 Nxd4 (22... Qxc3 $2 23. Rc2 Qa5 24. Nxe6 fxe6 25.
Rc7) 23. cxd4 (23. Rxd4 Qxc3 24. e4 Qc5 25. exd5 Qd6 $14) 23... Qd6 24. Rc1 {
White establishes control over the c-file} Rac8 25. Rdc2 Rxc2 26. Rxc2 $16 Bc6
$1 27. Rc3 (27. Bf1 Bd7 $5 28. Bxa6 $140 Ra8) 27... Bb5 28. Qb2 $6 {
Too ambitious. I decided to play for an attack, because I was not sure if} (28.
Bf1 Bxf1 29. Kxf1 $16 {<->c,would be enough for victory.In particular, I
thought that Black could give up his 'a' and 'b' pawns for White's 'a',
exchange a pair of pieces, and thereby keep some drawing chances. All the same,
I should have tried it.}) 28... Qe6 (28... Bc4 29. e4 f6 {
the attempt to prevent e4-e5 doesn't work} 30. Qc1 Kg7 31. exd5 (31. Re3 Re8
32. Qc3 (32. exd5 Rxe3 33. Qxe3 b5 $11) 32... b5 33. e5 $36) 31... b5 (31...
Bxd5 32. Rc7+ Rd7 33. Rxd7+ Qxd7 34. Bxd5 Qxd5 35. Qc7+ $18) 32. Re3 Bxd5 33.
Bxd5 Qxd5 34. Re7+ $18) 29. Qc1 Bc4 (29... Kg7 30. Bf1 Bxf1 31. Kxf1 $16) 30.
e4 b5 31. e5 Re8 {
Black had alternatives leading to unclear positions in all cases.} (31... Qg4
32. f4 (32. Rf3 Qxd4 33. e6 (33. Qg5 Rf8) 33... Rf8 34. Qg5 Qg4 $1 $11 (34...
Qg7 35. Rf6 Kh7 36. Qf4 d4 37. Be4 Kg8 (37... Bxe6 38. Bxg6+) 38. e7 Re8 39.
Qd6 $18)) 32... Qe6 33. Re3 a5 34. Kh2 $13) (31... Qb6 32. Qf4 {
-similiar to the game} (32. Qg5 Rf8 33. Rf3 Qxd4 34. e6 {-31...Qg4})) (31...
Rf8 $5 32. Re3 a5 33. Kh2 $13) 32. Kh2 {/\Bh3} (32. Re3 $5) 32... Qb6 {
My opponent misses a chance to equalize by} (32... f5 $1 33. exf6 Qxf6 34. Qh6
(34. Rf3 Qxd4 35. Qg5 Kg7) 34... Rf8 (34... a5 35. Rf3 Qg7 36. Qg5 b4 37. axb4
axb4 38. Rf6 Kh7 39. f4 Rf8 40. Rb6 $14) 35. Rf3 (35. Re3 Qg7) 35... Qg7) 33.
Qf4 Rf8 34. Rf3 {White's task is to put all the pieces in attacking positions
and to breakthrough} (34. Bh3 f5 $5) 34... a5 (34... Kg7 35. Qe3 $1) (34... Be2
35. Re3 Bc4 36. Bh3 Kg7 37. g4 hxg4 38. Bxg4 Qd8 (38... Rh8 39. e6) 39. h5 g5 (
39... Rh8 40. e6) (39... f5 40. e6 Qf6 (40... Qh4+ 41. Rh3 Qxg4 42. Qe5+ $18)
41. Bh3 $18) 40. Qf5 $16) 35. Bh3 {/\e6} Be2 36. Re3 Bc4 (36... Bg4 37. Bxg4
hxg4 38. Qxg4 $18) 37. Rf3 $138 (37. Qh6 $1) 37... Be2 38. Re3 Bc4 39. Qg5 $2 {
being short of time, I missed an easy win} (39. Qh6 Qxd4 40. e6 Qg7 41. Qxg7+
Kxg7 42. e7 Re8 43. Bd7 $18 {I forgot about this last move.}) 39... Qxd4 40. e6
$6 {Mistakes normally come together. After I made this 40th move I realised
how Black could save the game.} (40. Rf3 $5 Qe4 (40... Qd1 41. Rf6 d4 42. Bf5
$18) 41. Rf4 $18 {Was still winning}) 40... Qb2 $4 (40... fxe6 $3 {
Believe it or not, but this move was leading to a draw} 41. Qxg6+ Qg7 42. Bxe6+
Kh8 43. Qxh5+ Qh7 44. Qe5+ Qg7 45. Bxd5 Rxf2+ 46. Kg1 Qxe5 47. Rxe5 Ra2 $11)
41. Rf3 {Now White is winning again} d4 (41... Qg7 42. e7 Re8 43. Bd7 f6 44.
Be6+ (44. Rxf6 Rxe7 45. Rxg6 Rxd7 46. Rxg7+ Rxg7 47. Qxh5 $18) 44... Kh7 45.
Rxf6 Rxe7 46. Rxg6 Qxg6 47. Qxe7+ $18) 42. Rxf7 (42. Rxf7 Rxf7 43. Qxg6+ Rg7
44. Qe8+ Kh7 45. Bf5+) 1-0

