1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 Ng4 7. Bg5 h6 8. Bh4
g5 9. Bg3 Bg7 10. Be2 h5 11. Bxg4 Bxg4 12. f3 Bd7 13. Bf2 Nc6 14. O-O e6 $5 ({
The main alternatives are:} 14... Rc8 15. Nd5 (15. Nxc6 bxc6 16. Bd4 f6 17. Qd3
Rb8 18. Nd1 c5 19. Bf2 O-O 20. Re1 a5 21. Rb1 Be6 22. Nc3 a4 23. Nd5 Qd7 24. b3
axb3 25. axb3 Rb7 26. f4 gxf4 27. Nxf4 Bf7 28. Nd5 Ra8 29. Rbd1 Kh8 30. Ne3 Qb5
$11 {Tiviakov,S-Georgiev,K/Cacak 1996}) 15... e6 16. Nxc6 Rxc6 17. Bd4 Be5 18.
Ne3 f6 19. Rf2 Ke7 20. c3 Qa5 21. Rd2 Rhc8 22. Bxe5 Qxe5 23. Rd4 Qc5 24. Qd2 h4
25. Rd1 b5 26. Kh1 Be8 27. Ng4 Qb6 28. e5 dxe5 29. Rd7+ Bxd7 30. Qxd7+ Kf8 31.
Qh7 Rd6 32. Qh8+ Kf7 33. Qxf6+ Kg8 34. Qxg5+ Kf8 35. Qf6+ Kg8 36. Nh6+ {
1-0 Bologan,V-Ribli,Z/Deutschland 1996}) (14... Ne5 15. Nde2 Rc8 16. Nd5 Be6
17. Bd4 Bxd5 18. exd5 Qa5 19. f4 gxf4 20. Nxf4 Qa4 21. c3 Qxd1 22. Raxd1 Rh7
23. Bxe5 Bxe5 24. Nd3 Bh8 25. Rf4 Kd7 26. Rdf1 Bf6 27. Rb4 $14 {
Lanka,Z-Ftacnik,L/EU-chTM Pula 1997 (69)}) 15. Nxc6 (15. Qd2 {
followed by 16.Rad1 was worth considering.}) 15... Bxc6 16. Bd4 Be5 {
Essential move. Otherwise Whtie has a large advantage.} 17. Qd2 Qf6 18. Bxe5 $6
(18. Ne2 $5 {intending advancement of the queenside pawns seems to be stronger.
}) 18... dxe5 19. a4 O-O 20. b3 $2 ({Strange decision. Much stronger seems} 20.
Ne2) 20... Rfd8 21. Qe3 Qf4 $1 {Transforming game into a perspective ending,
since the threat Rd2 is very unpleasant.} 22. Qxf4 gxf4 23. Rfd1 h4 24. Rxd8+
Rxd8 25. Rd1 Rc8 $1 {
Certainly, exchange of the second rook pair would be in White's favor.} 26. Rd2
Kf8 27. Nd1 Ke7 28. Nf2 f5 29. Kf1 fxe4 30. fxe4 (30. Nxe4 {fails to} Bxe4 31.
fxe4 Rc3 $1) 30... a5 31. Ke2 Be8 $1 {Threatening 31...Rc3.} 32. Kd1 $2 ({
After this move White faces irreolvable problems.Essential was} 32. c4) 32...
Bh5+ (32... Rc3 $2 {is strongly met by} 33. Rd3) 33. Kc1 (33. Ke1 {fails to}
Rc3) 33... Rg8 $1 {Starting the effective operations on the kingside.} 34. Nd3
h3 $1 {Excellent blow. This pawn sacrifice yields Black decisive advantage.}
35. gxh3 Rg1+ 36. Kb2 Bf3 37. Nxe5 Bxe4 {
Intending to play 39...f3 followed by Rg2.} 38. Rf2 Kf6 $1 39. Nc4 (39. Ng4+
Kg5) 39... Kg5 {/\f4-f3, Kg5-f4.} 40. h4+ {A desperate attempt to push own
passed pawn. Clearly, this march cannot yield anything to White.} Kg4 41. h5 f3
42. h6 Kf4 43. Nd2 Rg6 44. h7 Rh6 45. h8=Q Rxh8 0-1

