{Topalov plays this game in a very low key, slow, positional style. But his
handling of the positional problems is fresh and free of preconceptions.} 1. e4
{Hecht} e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 d6 7. Bxc6+ bxc6
8. d4 exd4 9. Nxd4 Bd7 10. Nc3 O-O 11. h3 c5 (11... Rb8 12. Qf3 c5 13. Nf5 Bxf5
14. Qxf5 Qd7 15. Nd5 Qd8 16. Nxe7+ Qxe7 17. b3 Nd7 18. Bb2 $14 {
Siepelt,H-Stobik,D/BL2-S 1996/BL2/1-0 (77)}) 12. Nf3 $146 (12. Nde2 Be6 (12...
Bc6 13. Ng3 Re8 14. Nf5 Bf8 15. Qf3 Bd7 16. Bg5 Bxf5 17. exf5 Be7 18. Re2 $14 {
Adamson,R-Stetson,R/Webb op 1989/EXT 89op2/1-0 (52)}) 13. Nf4 Nd7 14. Ncd5 Bf6
15. Nxf6+ Qxf6 16. Nh5 Qe7 $11 {
1-0 Soltis,A-Haririan,B/Boston op 1988/EXT 88op2 (35)}) 12... Re8 13. e5 dxe5
14. Nxe5 Bd6 15. Bf4 Bf5 16. Rc1 {Very cool defence of c2, but its good becase
its the only weakness in Whites position.} Re6 17. Qf3 Qe8 18. Nd3 c4 19. Rxe6
Bxe6 20. Ne5 Rb8 21. Re1 Qf8 (21... Rxb2 22. Nxc4 Rxc2 23. Bxd6 cxd6 24. Qd3
$16) 22. b3 cxb3 23. axb3 $14 Re8 24. Nd3 c5 25. Bxd6 Qxd6 26. Qf4 Qxf4 27.
Nxf4 Bf5 28. Rc1 $1 {Again, this funny R move. Now the threat is g4, kicking
the B, then Ra1 is coming.} c4 (28... h5 29. Nfd5 Nxd5 30. Nxd5 Be6 31. Nc7 $1
(31. Ne3 f5 $132) 31... Rc8 32. Nxe6 fxe6 33. Ra1 Rc6 34. Kf1 c4 35. b4 c3 36.
Ke2 Rc4 37. Rxa6 Rxb4 38. Kd3 $16) (28... Re5 29. g4 g5 30. Ng2 $16) 29. bxc4
Rc8 30. Ncd5 $1 {Black is not going to get his P back after this.} Nxd5 31.
Nxd5 Kf8 32. Ra1 Bxc2 33. Nb6 Rc7 (33... Rc6 34. Rxa6 Ke8 35. Ra8+ Ke7 36. Nd5+
Kd6 37. Ne3 Bb3 38. Rg8 $16) 34. Rxa6 g6 35. f3 Kg7 36. Ra3 Rc6 37. Rc3 Rxb6
38. Rxc2 Kf6 39. Kf2 Ke5 40. Re2+ Kd6 41. Kg3 Rc6 42. Rd2+ Ke5 43. Rd5+ Ke6 44.
Rd4 Ra6 45. Re4+ Kd6 46. h4 Ra2 47. c5+ Kd7 48. c6+ Kd6 49. Rc4 Kc7 50. Rf4 f5
51. Rc4 h5 52. Rc5 Ra4 53. Re5 f4+ 54. Kh3 Rd4 55. Re6 $18 Rd6 56. Rxd6 Kxd6 {
Hecht: Weiß benutzt die momentane Abwesenheit des schwarzen Königs zum Gewinn
eines Bauern....} 57. g3 Kxc6 58. gxf4 {#  Wie schon im  Endspiel Izeta-Frois/
EU-chT Pula/1997/ gewinnt Weiß trotz der schlechten Bauernstellung durch
vorsichtiges Herumspielen seines Königs um den Doppelbauern zur Mitte. Danach
gewinnt er leicht infolge Zugzwang oder Damengewinn.} Kd5 59. Kg3 Ke6 (59...
Kd4 {Hecht} 60. f5 Ke5 61. fxg6 Kf6 62. Kf4 Kxg6 63. Ke5 $18) 60. Kf2 Kf6 61.
Ke2 Ke6 62. Kd3 Kd5 63. Ke3 Ke6 64. Ke4 Kf6 65. f5 g5 (65... gxf5+ 66. Kf4 $18
(66. Kd5 {Hecht} f4 67. Ke4 Ke6 68. Kxf4 Kf6 69. Ke4 Ke6 70. f4 Kf6 71. f5 Kf7
72. Ke5 Ke7 73. f6+ Kf7 74. Kf5 Kf8 75. Kg6 Kg8 76. Kxh5 Kf7 77. Kg5 $18) (66.
Kf4 Ke6 67. Kg5 Ke5 68. Kxh5 Kf4 69. Kg6 $18)) 66. hxg5+ Kxg5 67. Ke5 h4 68. f6
Kg6 (68... h3 {Hecht} 69. f7 h2 70. f8=Q h1=Q 71. Qg7+ Kh4 72. Qh6+ $18) 69.
