{Shirov plays a new move, with a brand new plan to go with it, but he fails to
prove its value. Whites play could perhaps be improved, so the line is worth
another try.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. O-O Bg4 6. h3 h5 7.
d3 Qf6 8. Be3 (8. Nbd2 {Leads to the drawish main line.} Ne7 9. Re1 Ng6 10. d4
Bd6 11. hxg4 hxg4 12. Nh2 Rxh2 13. Qxg4 Qh4 14. Qxh4 Rxh4 15. Nf3 Rh5 16. dxe5
Nxe5 17. Nxe5 Bxe5 18. c3 {Gipslis in ECO gives +/= here} O-O-O (18... g5 $11)
19. Be3 g5 $11 {Barendregt,J-Zuidema,C/Amsterdam IBM 1965/MCL 08/0-1 (88)})
8... Bxf3 9. Qxf3 Qxf3 10. gxf3 Bd6 11. Nd2 (11. Kh2 f5 12. Rg1 Kf7 13. a4 Ne7
14. Kg2 Ng6 $132 {
1-0 De Vreugt,D-Van de Oudeweetering,A/NLD-ch op 1994/EXT 94ch (38)}) (11. c4
Nf6 12. c5 Be7 13. Rc1 Nd7 14. Nd2 O-O-O 15. Rc3 f5 16. exf5 Rhf8 $15 {
Den Broeder,G-Van der Weij,A/NLD-chT 1993/EXT 93ch/0-1 (74)}) (11. Nc3 Ne7 12.
Kg2 (12. Kh2 f6 13. h4 Ng6 14. Kh3 Nf8 15. Rg1 Kf7 16. Rg2 Ne6 17. Rag1 Rhg8
18. Ne2 {1/2-1/2 Siroky,J-Mrva,V/SVK-chT 1995/EXT 95ch}) 12... Ng6 13. Rg1
O-O-O {1/2-1/2 Siroky,J-Sturc,G/SVK-chT 1995/EXT 95ch}) 11... Ne7 12. Rfb1 $146
{Shirov launches a completely new plan in this position. Rather than trying to
do something on the g-file, he starts play on the Q-side. The main drawback is
that there is little to be had there if Black is cautious.} (12. Rfd1 f6 13.
Kf1 (13. Nb3 Kf7 14. Kf1 g5 15. d4 exd4 16. Nxd4 Ng6 $11 {
1/2-1/2 Dassel,U-Harzheim,L/NRW-I 1989/BIG 80 (23)}) 13... g5 14. Ke2 Ng6 15.
Nf1 Kf7 16. Ng3 Ne7 17. Rh1 h4 18. Nf1 a5 19. a4 {
1/2-1/2 Larsen,O-Notkin,M/Aalborg op 1995/EXT 95op}) (12. Nc4 Ng6 13. Kh1 f6
14. Rg1 Kf7 15. Rg3 Ne7 (15... Nh4 16. f4 exf4 17. Nxd6+ cxd6 18. Bxf4 d5 $10 {
0-1 Ljubojevic,L-Spassky,B/Tilburg 1978/MCL 08/[Ftacnik] (43)}) 16. f4 exf4 17.
Nxd6+ cxd6 18. Bxf4 Rad8 19. Rag1 Rhg8 $11 {
Zaitsev,I-Notkin,M/Podolsk-chT 1993/TD 93\07/0-1 (65)}) (12. Kh1 O-O-O 13. Rg1
Rh7 14. Rg2 c5 15. Rag1 g6 16. Bg5 Re8 17. Bxe7 Bxe7 18. Nc4 Bf6 19. a4 $14 {
Rozentalis,E-Duong Thanh Nha/Montreal op 1995/EXT 95op/1-0 (57)}) (12. Kh2 f6
13. Nc4 O-O-O 14. h4 Kd7 15. Rg1 g6 16. Rab1 Ke6 $13 {
Watanabe,R-Zapata,M/WchJ-U20 Santiago 1990/EXT 90ch/0-1 (46)}) 12... Ng6 13. b4
f6 14. a4 Kf7 15. Kf1 Nf8 16. Ke2 Ne6 {
Now White has to explain the meaning behind the moves a4 and b4.} 17. c3 $6 {
Achange of plan, now White wants to go d4 instead.} (17. c4 $5 {trying for b5
or c5 is at least more in line with the main idea of a Q-side expansion.} Nd4+
(17... b6 18. c5 bxc5 19. bxc5 Bxc5 20. Bxc5 Nxc5 21. Rc1 $16) 18. Bxd4 exd4
19. c5 Bf4 20. Nc4 $13) 17... Rhd8 18. Nc4 (18. d4 exd4 (18... g5 19. d5 cxd5
20. exd5 Nf4+ 21. Bxf4 exf4) 19. cxd4 Nf4+ (19... Bf4 20. Nb3) 20. Bxf4 Bxf4
21. Nb3 Rd6 22. Rd1 Rad8 23. Rd3 $11) 18... b6 19. Kd2 (19. Nxd6+ Rxd6 20. a5
b5 21. Rd1 Rad8 22. Rac1 g5 23. c4 Ke7 24. cxb5 cxb5 25. Bc5 Nxc5 26. Rxc5 c6
$11) 19... Be7 20. Kc2 Rd7 21. Rd1 Rad8 22. Rd2 g6 23. Rad1 Bf8 24. Kb3 {
Finally White threatens d4 again.} c5 $1 $17 25. b5 a5 26. Kc2 Bg7 {
White's play is gone, now Black has all the options.} 27. Rh1 f5 28. Rdd1 f4
29. Bc1 Bf6 30. h4 Kg7 31. Rh2 Kh7 32. Rg2 Kh6 33. Rdg1 Rg7 34. Rh1 Kh7 35.
Rhg1 Rdg8 36. Rh1 Kh6 37. Kd2 g5 38. hxg5+ Nxg5 39. Ke2 Ne6 40. Rgh2 h4 41.
Rxh4+ {The best practical chance} Bxh4 42. Rxh4+ Kg5 43. Rh1 Kf6 44. Bb2 Rg5
45. Rh7 Re8 46. Rd7 Re7 47. Rd5 Rh7 48. d4 exd4 49. e5+ Kf5 50. cxd4 Rg2 51.
Nd6+ {Imaginative counterplay, but the position is still lost.} cxd6 52. exd6+
Kg6 53. d7 Nd8 54. dxc5 bxc5 55. Bc3 Kf7 56. Bxa5 Ke6 57. Rxc5 Rxd7 58. Bc7
Rgg7 59. Bxf4 Nb7 60. Rc6+ Kd5 61. Be3 Rg1 $19 62. Rh6 Kc4 63. Rc6+ Kb3 64. b6
Kxa4 65. f4 Kb5 66. Rc2 Nd6 67. Rc5+ Ka6 68. Rd5 Rgg7 69. Kf3 Nc4 70. Rc5 Nxb6
71. Rc6 Rb7 72. f5 Rgc7 73. Re6 Kb5 74. Re5+ Kc4 75. Ke4 Nd7 76. Ra5 Nf6+ 77.
Ke5 Rc6 78. Bg5 Rb5+ 79. Rxb5 Nd7+ 80. Ke4 Kxb5 81. Kd5 Rc5+ 82. Ke6 Nf8+ 0-1

