Bxf3 Qd8 16. Nb5 O-O 17. Nxc7 (17. Nxa7 $2 Ra8) 17... Rb7 18. Na6 Qb6 19. b5
$16 {1-0 Huzman,A-Salov,V/Amsterdam Donner 1995 (37)}) 9... Ba6 10. Ne5 $1 $146
{A slightly more active move, than in the others last games in this variation.
White trying to use the fact , that black needs two moves  to castle and this
time is quite enough , so that to get positional pluses.} (10. Na4 Bb5 11. Nc3
Ba6 12. Na4 Bb5 13. Nc3 {1/2-1/2 Thiel,K-Rigo,J/Wuppertal-B 1986}) (10. Rb1 c5
11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. b4 Be7 13. b5 Bb7 14. Nd4 Rc8 15. Bd2 Nb6 16. a4 Nc4 17. Na2
a5 18. Nb3 Qb6 19. Qe1 Bd8 20. Bc3 O-O 21. e3 e5 22. Qe2 $14 {
Nikolic,P-Karpov,A/Amber-blind6th rapid 1997/1-0 (55)}) (10. Re1 Bb4 11. Bd2 c5
12. dxc5 Bxc5 13. b4 Bxb4 14. Qa4 Qa5 15. Qxa5 Bxa5 16. Nxd5 Bxd2 17. Nxf6+
Nxf6 18. Nxd2 Rc8 $11 {1/2-1/2 Anand,V-Karpov,A/Amber-blind6th rapid 1997 (24)}
) (10. Bb2 Be7 11. Rc1 O-O 12. Na4 Qb8 (12... Bb5 13. Nc5 Nxc5 14. dxc5 a5 15.
Nd4 Qb8 $10) 13. Ne1 (13. Nc5 Bxc5 14. dxc5 c6 15. Ne5 Qc7 16. f4 $13 {
0-1 Polak,T-Epishin,V/Open1/4/22 1996 (36)}) 13... Bb5 14. Nc3 Rc8 15. Nxb5
Qxb5 16. Nd3 a5 17. Ba1 Bd6 18. e3 Rcb8 19. Bc3 a4 20. b4 $16 {
1-0 Arbakov Valentin-Epishin Vladimir/Biel 1996 (40)}) 10... Bd6 (10... Bb7 $2
11. Bf4 c5 (11... Bd6 12. Rc1 O-O 13. Nb5 a6 14. Nxd6 cxd6 15. Nc4 $1 (15. Nc6
Qb6) 15... dxc4 16. Bxb7 Ra7 17. Bg2 cxb3 18. Bxd6 $18) 12. Nb5 $16) (10...
Nxe5 $2 11. dxe5 $32 Bb4 (11... Nd7 12. Nxd5 $1 exd5 13. Qxd5 Nb6 (13... Rb8
14. e6 $18) 14. Qc6+ Qd7 15. Bg5 $1 (15. Rd1 Qxc6 16. Bxc6+ Ke7 17. Bxa8 Nxa8
18. Bg5+ f6 19. exf6+ gxf6 20. Bf4 $16) 15... Rc8 16. Rfd1 Bb5 17. Rxd7 Bxc6
18. Bxc6 Nxd7 19. Rd1 $18) 12. exf6 Bxc3 13. fxg7 Bxg7 14. Rb1 O-O 15. Ba3 Re8
16. Rc1 $16) 11. Nc6 (11. Bf4 Bxe5 (11... O-O $142) 12. dxe5 (12. Bxe5 Nxe5 13.
dxe5 Nd7 14. f4 c5) 12... Nh5 (12... Ng4 13. Qd4 c5 14. Qa4 Qb6 15. Bxd5 $1
exd5 16. Nxd5 Qb7 17. e6 $1 $18) 13. Be3 Nxe5 14. f4 Nc6 15. b4 (15. f5 Nf6 (
15... O-O 16. Bc5 Ne7 17. fxe6 fxe6 18. Rxf8+ Qxf8 19. Nxd5 $18) 16. Bc5 Ne7
17. fxe6 fxe6 18. Qd4 O-O 19. Qe5 Qd7 20. Bh3 Bc8 21. e4 {
looks very good for white.}) 15... Bb7 16. Bc5 Nf6 17. e4 {
with strong intiative.} (17. b5 Ne7)) 11... Qc8 12. a3 (12. Bb2 Qb7 $140 13.
Rc1 Qxc6 $2 14. Nxd5 Qxd5 15. Bxd5 exd5 16. Rc2 O-O 17. Qc1 $16 {
But 13... 0-0 gives to black comfortable position.}) (12. Re1 $2 Bb7 13. Na5
Bb4) 12... O-O 13. Bg5 (13. Bf4 $5 Qe8 (13... Qb7 $6 14. Na5 Qb6 15. b4 {
and white is clearly better.}) 14. Nb4 $1 (14. Rc1 Nb6 (14... Bxa3 $2 15. Ra1
Nb6 16. Rxa3 Qxc6 17. Qa1 $1 Bb7 18. Rc1 Qd7 19. Na4 $1 $16) 15. Bxd6 cxd6 16.
Nb4 Bb7 $11) 14... Bb7 15. Nd3 Bxf4 16. gxf4 $14 (16. Nxf4 c5 17. dxc5 Nxc5 18.
b4 $14)) 13... Qe8 {
Black has to play against annoying knight on c6, in order to play c7-c5.} (
13... Qb7 $2 14. Na5 Qb6 15. b4 $16) (13... Bb7 $6 14. Na5 c5 15. Rc1) 14. Qd2
(14. b4 h6 (14... Nb6 15. Na5 (15. Ne5 Nfd7) 15... Nc4 16. Nxc4 (16. Nb3 Bb7
17. Bxf6 gxf6 18. e4 $16) 16... Bxc4 17. Bxf6 gxf6 $11) 15. Bxf6 (15. Bd2 Nb6
16. Ne5 Nc4 $11) 15... Nxf6 16. Na5 (16. Ne5 Bb7 {also good for black.} (16...
Bxe5 17. dxe5 Nd7 18. Qd4 c5 $1 (18... Qe7 $2 19. b5 $16) 19. bxc5 Rc8 $11))
16... c6 17. Rc1 (17. f4 Bc7 18. Na4 (18. Nb3 Bc4 $132) 18... Bxa5 19. bxa5 Rb8
20. Nc5 Bc4 21. Qd2 Nd7 $11) 17... e5 (17... Rc8 18. f4 $14) 18. Nxc6 $5 Qxc6
19. Nxd5 Qb5 20. a4 (20. Nxf6+ gxf6 21. Bxa8 Rxa8 22. Qd2 $6 Qxe2 23. Qxh6 Qf3
$17) 20... Qxe2 21. b5 Qxd1 22. Nxf6+ gxf6 23. Rfxd1 Rac8 $11) 14... Nb6 (14...
h6 15. Bf4 $1) 15. Na5 {after this move black gets a competent play.} (15. Nb4
$1 Bb7 (15... Bxb4 $6 16. axb4 Bb7 17. Ra5 $16) 16. Bxf6 gxf6 17. e4 dxe4 18.
Nxe4 (18. Bxe4 Bxe4 19. Nxe4 Kg7 20. Rac1 $14) 18... Bxe4 19. Bxe4 Rc8 (19...
Bxb4 20. Qh6 f5 21. Bxa8 $18) 20. Nc6 $16) 15... c5 16. dxc5 Bxc5 17. Bxf6 (17.
Rfc1 Rc8 18. b4 Be7 $11) 17... gxf6 18. Rfc1 (18. b4 Be7 {
with next 19...f5 and 20...Bf6}) 18... Rc8 19. e4 d4 (19... dxe4 $2 20. Nxe4
Be7 21. Rxc8 Bxc8 (21... Nxc8 22. Qh6) 22. b4 $16) 20. Nd1 (20. Ne2 d3 (20...
e5 $2 21. Bh3 Rc7 22. Qh6 Bc8 $8 23. b4 Bd6 24. Bxc8 Nxc8 25. Qxf6 $18) 21. Nf4
Qb5 (21... Qd7 22. Nh5 Bd4 23. Qh6 f5 24. exf5 exf5 25. Nc6 $40) 22. Bf1 (22.
Nh5 $2 Bd4 (22... Bxf2+) 23. Qh6 Qg5 $19) 22... Rfd8 23. b4 Bf8 24. Rxc8 Nxc8
25. Rd1 Qa4 $11) 20... d3 21. e5 (21. b4 $6 Bd4 22. Rxc8 Qxc8 23. Rc1 Qd7 {
and black has even better chances with d3 pawn.}) 21... Bd4 (21... fxe5 22.
Qg5+ Kh8 23. Qf6+ (23. Qxe5+ $2 f6 $17) 23... Kg8 24. Nc6 $5 Bd6 {
and white has to make draw.}) 22. Rxc8 Qxc8 (22... Nxc8 23. exf6 Bxf6 24. Rc1
Qb5 25. Ne3 $13 (25. b4 $5)) 23. Rc1 (23. Nc6 Qd7 24. Rc1 Rc8 25. Qf4 fxe5 26.
Qg5+ Kf8 27. Qh6+ Kg8 28. Qg5+ $11) 23... Qd7 24. Bc6 (24. Nc6 {see 23Nc6})
24... Qe7 $6 (24... Qd8 25. b4 (25. Bb7 Bxb7 26. Nxb7 Qd5 27. Qxd3 (27. exf6
Bxf6 28. Nc5 Rd8 29. Ne3 Qd4 30. b4 $13) 27... Rb8 28. Na5 Nd7 29. Qc4 Qxc4 30.
Rxc4 Nxe5 $11) 25... Bxe5 (25... fxe5 26. b5 Bc8 27. Bg2 $14) 26. b5 Bc8 27.
