with a comfortable Maroczy bind position for Black.}) 10. d5 Na7 (10... Ne5 11.
Ng3 b5) 11. Nc1 (11. b3 $1 b5 12. Rc1 $1 Bd7 13. Ng3 $14) 11... b5 12. cxb5
axb5 13. Nxb5 Nxb5 14. Qxa5 Rxa5 15. Bd2 Ra8 16. Bxb5 Rb8 17. a4 Bd7 18. Bxd7
Nxd7 19. b3 f5 $13 {Gervais-David, Cappelle la Grande 1997}) (8... cxd4 9. Nxd4
Nc6) 9. d5 Ne5 10. Ng3 b5 11. cxb5 Qb6 12. a4 axb5 13. Bxb5 Ba6 14. O-O Qa5 {
Black's play is not very impressive losing a tempo with his Q so early.} 15.
Bxa6 $6 {White has to keep his B on b5, taking back with the P.} (15. Ra2 $1 c4
(15... Qb4 16. Rfa1 Nc4 17. Qe2 Bxb5 18. axb5 Rxa2 19. Rxa2 {/\ Ra4}) (15...
Nc4 16. Qe2) (15... Bxb5 16. axb5) 16. Nh1 Nd3 17. Nf2 Nb4 18. Ra3 $16) 15...
Rxa6 16. Nb5 Qxd2 17. Bxd2 Nc4 18. Bc3 Nd7 $1 19. Bxg7 (19. Ra2 Bxc3 20. bxc3
