started well and the winner would get a clear lead.} 1. d4 {Epishin} Nf6 2. c4
c5 3. d5 b5 4. Nf3 g6 5. cxb5 a6 6. Qc2 $5 {
A rather rare move, occasionally used by Korchnoi and I.Sokolov.} Bg7 ({
Interesting is} 6... Nxd5 $5 7. Qxc5 Bb7 8. e4 Nf6 9. Nc3 Bg7 10. Qe3 O-O 11.
Bd2 d5 12. exd5 Nxd5 13. Nxd5 Qxd5 14. bxa6 Nxa6 15. Bc3 Bxc3+ 16. bxc3 Nc5 17.
