Ng4 14. Bg5 f6 $5 {This ugly move is necessary to prevent the e5 advance. With
his Bg7 hemmed in Black's compensation is nebulous.} 15. Bd2 Qa6 {
Otherwise White has attacking chances.} 16. Qxa6 Rxa6 17. h3 Nh6 18. Rfd1 Nf7
