minimalen Stellungsvorteil , weil der schwache Bb7 vom Pd5 eingeschränkt ist.}
c6 12. O-O a5 13. b5 {
Dieser Zug gefällt mir nicht, weil er Schwarz starkes Gegenspiel verschafft.} (
13. a3 axb4 14. axb4 Rxa1 15. Qxa1 Nd7 16. Qb2 (16. Rd1 Qc7 17. Qb1 Re8 18. b5
c5 19. Qf5 cxd4 $2 (19... Rd8 $1 20. Nxd5 Bxd5 21. Qxd5 Ne5 $1 22. Qe4 Nxf3+
23. Bxf3 cxd4 24. exd4 Bxd4 $1 $11) 20. Nxd5 Bxd5 21. Qxd5 Nc5 22. Nxd4 $16 {
1-0 Van der Sterren,P-Lutz,C/BL9495 1995/BL 90 (48)}) 16... Qc7 17. Ra1 b5 18.
e4 dxe4 19. Nxe4 Be7 20. Rc1 Qf4 21. Nc5 Nxc5 22. dxc5 Bf6 23. Qd2 Qc7 24. Rd1
Rd8 25. Qe3 Bc8 26. h3 Be6 $15 {
0-1 Tsvetkov,I-Donev,I/Sofia-ch Student 1986 (45)}) (13. bxa5 {Ftacnik} Rxa5
14. a4 c5 (14... Bc8) 15. Qb3 Na6 16. Rfb1 Nb4 17. Na2 Nxa2 18. Rxa2 Ba6 19.
Bxa6 Rxa6 20. Qb5 Qa8 21. dxc5 bxc5 22. Qxc5 Rxa4 23. Rxa4 Qxa4 24. h3 {
Lautier,J-Kramnik,V/Belgrad Investbanka/1997/}) 13... c5 14. Re1 $146 {
Üblich ist 14.Rc1 mit leichtem weißem Vorteil.} (14. Rc1 {Ftacnik} Nd7 (14...
Qd6 $2 15. dxc5 bxc5 16. Ne4 Qb6 17. Nxc5 {
Ivanov,I-Horvitz,R/Midwest Masters 1985}) 15. dxc5 Nxc5 16. Nd4 Rc8 (16... Qd6
17. Bg4 Rad8 18. Nce2 {Nikolic,P-Beliavsky,A/Groningen PCA 1993}) 17. Bg4 Rc7
18. Na4 (18. Nce2 Be5 19. g3 g6 20. Bh3 Qd6 21. Rc2 h5 {
Lutz,C-Van der Sterren,P/Munich SKA 1994}) 18... Ne4 19. Qd3 Rc4 20. Nb2 Rc5
21. Na4 Bxd4 22. exd4 Rc4 23. Nc3 Qc7 {
Gretarsson,H-Jussupow,A/Groningen FIDE Wch/1997 (33)}) 14... Re8 15. Rc1 Nd7
16. g3 (16. dxc5 {Ftacnik} Nxc5 17. Nd4 Qd6 $11) 16... Nf8 17. Na4 $6 (17. dxc5
$142 bxc5 18. Na4 c4 19. Nd4 (19. Nc5 {Ftacnik} Qe7 (19... Rb8 20. Nxb7 Rxb7
21. a4 Ne6 $11) 20. Nxb7 Qxb7 21. a4 Ne6 22. Bf1 Nc5 $11) 19... Ne6 $11) 17...
c4 $1 {Ftacnik: Fixing the structure, so the weak spots b6,c6 will be less
accessible. The bishops will enable black to spread his pieces in such a way,
as to enable activity on the kingside.} (17... cxd4 $6 {Ftacnik} 18. Nxd4 $14)
18. Bf1 Qd6 19. Bg2 Rad8 20. h4 Ne6 21. Nc3 g6 22. Nd2 Ba8 (22... Ng7 $2 {
Ftacnik} 23. Nxc4 $1 $16) 23. h5 $6 {Hansen,Cu: A serious positional mistake.
Whites Ns are too far away from the K-side (f5) to make any use of the weaked
square the textmove creates. However on the long term the posibility f7-f5
might be useful for black Der Anfang eines schlechten Planes.} (23. f4 $142 $5
{/\ Nf3, Ne5.} Ng7 24. Bh3 (24. Nf3 {Ftacnik} Nf5 $15)) (23. a4 $11 {Ftacnik})
23... g5 24. Nf1 Be7 {Hansen,Cu: The first part of a regrouping of the black
forces that improves his position considerably} 25. g4 $6 {Noch eine bedenklich
e Entscheidung, die zur Schwächung der Diagonale b8 - h2 führt.} (25. e4 $142
dxe4 26. d5 Bxd5 27. Nxd5 Qxd5 28. Qxd5 Rxd5 29. Rxe4 $44) (25. a4 {Ftacnik} f5
$15) 25... Qd7 26. Ng3 Ng7 27. a4 Bb4 {Ftacnik: Kramnik would gladly use
weakness of b8-h2 diagonal, but the plan needs a bit more preparation.  Hansen,
Cu: It becomes clear that white will have to perform a miracle to make any of
is active possibilities e3-e4 or f2-f4 work. While it seems much more likely
that an evertual f7-f5 will have a positive effect on blacks position} (27...
Bd6 $6 {Ftacnik} 28. Bxd5 Bxg3 29. Bxa8 Bxf2+ 30. Kxf2 Rxa8 31. e4 $14) 28. Bh3
(28. Qf3 {Ftacnik} Kf8 (28... Bb7 29. e4 $5 (29. Nf5 Nxf5 30. gxf5 Qd6 $15)
29... dxe4 30. Ngxe4 Qxd4 31. Red1 (31. Nf6+ Kh8 32. Rxe8+ Nxe8 33. Qxb7 Qxf6 (
33... Qf4 $2 34. Qxf7 $1) 34. Nd5 Qe6 35. Nxb6 Rd4 36. Qa8 $13) 31... Bxe4 32.
Nxe4 Rxe4 33. Rxd4 Rexd4 34. Qc6 $14) 29. Rc2 $13) 28... Bb7 29. Qc2 Bd6 30.
Nf5 (30. Nce2 {Ftacnik} Rc8 $15) 30... Nxf5 31. gxf5 Bb4 {Hansen,Cu: Whites
has made f7-f5 impossible. But now he can only sit and wait to see whether
black can improve his position by putting pressure on f5 or launch an attack
on the K-side by Bxc3, followed by Re4} 32. Kg2 Qd6 33. f3 (33. Bg4 {Ftacnik}
Re7 $17) 33... Re7 34. Re2 Rde8 35. Rce1 Qf6 36. Bg4 (36. e4 $2 {Ftacnik} dxe4
37. fxe4 Qxd4 $19) 36... Bd6 37. Qd1 Bb4 38. Qc2 Rd8 39. Rd1 Bc8 {Ftacnik: Blac
k has achieved maximum, now the pawn f5 causes white lot of troubles.   Hansen,
Cu: /\40..Bxc3 41.Qxc3 Bxf5 Schwarz gruppiert in Ruhe seine Figuren um,
während Weiß nur abwarten kann.} 40. e4 $2 {
Der letzte Zug vor der Zeitkontrolle kostet die Partie. Jetzt ist alles vorbei.
} ({Mit dem passiven:} 40. Na2 Rde8 41. Kf2 (41. e4 {Hansen,Cu} Bxf5 $1 $19)
41... Qd6 42. Rh1 {hätte Weiß die Schotten dicht machen können.}) (40. Rde1 {
Ftacnik} Bxc3 41. Qxc3 Bxf5 42. Bxf5 Qxf5 $19) 40... Bxc3 41. e5 (41. Qxc3 dxe4
42. fxe4 (42. Rxe4 {Ftacnik} Rxe4 43. fxe4 Bb7 44. Qe3 c3 45. d5 c2 46. Rc1 Rc8
$17) 42... Bb7 43. Bf3 g4 $1 44. Bxg4 Rxe4 45. Rxe4 Bxe4+ 46. Kf2 Bd3 $19)
41... Rxe5 $3 {Eine außerordentliche Lösung im Kramnik - Stil, die das weiße
Zentrum vernichtet. Das Läuferpaar und die starken Freibauern entscheiden die
Partie.} 42. dxe5 (42. Rxe5 Bxd4 $1 43. Re2 Bc3 $19 {/\d5-d4}) 42... Bxe5 {
Ftacnik: The triumph of strategical concept, despite an exchange sacrifice
black controls the whole board and pawns c4-d5 will one day start rolling.  
Hansen,Cu: Blacks two passed pawns in the centre gives him a winningadvantage}
43. Rde1 Bc7 44. Re8+ Kg7 (44... Rxe8 $2 {Ftacnik} 45. Rxe8+ Kg7 46. Rxc8 $18)
45. Rxd8 Bxd8 46. Rd1 Bb7 47. f4 (47. Bh3 {Ftacnik} Bc7 48. Kg1 Bd6 $19) 47...
