{This game is a nice model for how to conduct the white attack in the Spanish
main lines when Black has exchanged on d4. Topalov plays in the centre at
first to distract Black from attacking on the Q-side. Then at the appropriate
moment he shifts to a K-side operation.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4
Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 O-O 9. h3 Nd7 10. d4 Nb6 11. Nbd2 exd4
12. cxd4 Nb4 13. Nf1 c5 14. a3 Nc6 15. Be3 (15. Ng3 c4 16. Bc2 d5 17. e5 a5 18.
Be3 b4 19. axb4 axb4 20. Rxa8 Nxa8 21. Nh2 b3 22. Bb1 Nc7 23. Qh5 g6 24. Qh6
Re8 25. Ng4 Bxg4 26. hxg4 Bf8 27. Qh3 Ne6 $17 {
0-1 Svidler,P-Adams,M/Groningen 1997/CBM 63 (36)}) (15. d5 Ne5 16. Nxe5 dxe5
17. Be3 Bd6 18. Qd2 Bd7 19. Rec1 Qe7 20. Qa5 Rfb8 21. Nd2 Be8 22. Bd1 Nd7 $13 {
0-1 Shirov,A-Piket,J/Linares 1997/CBM 57 (40)}) (15. Bc2 Nxd4 16. Nxd4 cxd4 17.
b3 Be6 18. Bb2 Bf6 19. Bxd4 Be5 20. Nh2 Bxd4 21. Qxd4 Qc7 22. Re2 Qc5 $11 {
0-1 Bologan,V-Zagrebelny,S/Kstovo 1998/EXT 99 (31)}) (15. Bf4 Nxd4 16. Nxd4
cxd4 17. Qxd4 Be6 18. Bxe6 fxe6 19. Bg3 Nc4 $15 {
0-1 Bologan,V-Piket,J/Germany 1997/GER-chT (44)}) 15... c4 (15... Na5 16. Bc2
Nbc4 17. Bc1 cxd4 18. Nxd4 Bf6 19. Rb1 d5 20. exd5 Bb7 21. Nf5 Qxd5 22. Qxd5
Bxd5 23. b3 Nb6 24. Be3 Rab8 25. N1g3 Be6 26. Ne4 $14 {
1-0 Karpov,A-Ivkov,B/Bugojno 1980/MCD (58)}) (15... a5 16. Rc1 c4 17. Bc2 d5
18. Ne5 Bb7 19. Nxc6 Bxc6 20. e5 Na4 21. Rb1 Ra6 22. Ng3 g6 23. Bh6 Re8 24. e6
$40 {1-0 Topalov,V-Piket,J/Monte Carlo 1997/CBM 57 ext (37)}) 16. Bc2 d5 17.
Ne5 $1 {Topalov keeps the central tension while building up against the black
K. This way Blacks Q-side play is at least postponed. See the game 0-1 Svidler,
P-Adams,M/Groningen 1997/CBM 63 (36) for an example of how Black can play when
White closes too early with e5.} (17. e5 a5 $132) 17... Qc7 18. Ng3 g6 19. Qf3
Be6 20. Nxc6 Qxc6 21. Bh6 Rfe8 22. e5 {
Now the time is ripe for a pure attack on the black K.} a5 23. Nh5 $1 {
This sacrifice is the key to opening up the black box.} Nd7 (23... gxh5 24.
Qg3+ (24. Qxh5 f5 25. Re3 Kh8 26. Bg7+ Kxg7 27. Rg3+ Kh8 28. Qh6 Rg8 29. Bxf5
$18) 24... Bg4 25. e6 $40) 24. Qg3 b4 25. Ng7 Bf8 $2 (25... Rec8 26. Nf5 (26.
Nxe6 Qxe6 27. f4 c3 28. b3 Qb6 29. Rad1 bxa3 $132) 26... Bxf5 27. Bxf5 $16) 26.
Nxe8 Bxh6 27. Nd6 b3 28. Bf5 $18 Nb6 29. f4 Bxf5 30. Nxf5 Bf8 31. Nh4 Na4 32.
f5 $40 (32. Rab1 $18) 32... Nxb2 33. e6 Nd3 (33... Bg7 $5) 34. exf7+ Kxf7 35.
Re6 b2 36. Rf1 Qb7 37. Nxg6 $1 Bg7 38. Qe3 Bf6 39. Rxf6+ Kxf6 40. Qe6+ Kg7 41.
f6+ Kh6 (41... Kxg6 42. f7+ Kg7 43. Qf6+ Kf8 44. Qd6+ Kg7 45. f8=Q+ Rxf8 46.
Qxf8+ Kg6 47. Qf6+ Kh5 48. g4#) 42. Ne7 1-0

