28... Nxb2 29. Nbd4 $16) 27. Nd2 e5 28. Nf5 (28. Ne4 Rd8 (28... exd4 $2 29.
Nxf6+ gxf6 30. Rxe8 $18) 29. Nf5 Qe6) 28... Rd8 29. Ne4 Qe6 30. Bh4 (30. b3 $14
) 30... Qc6 (30... g6 $2 31. Nd4 $18) 31. b3 Qxb5 (31... Nd6 $5 32. Qxc6 Nxc6
33. Nfxd6 Bxd6 34. Rd1 Be7 35. Rxd8+ Nxd8 36. g4 Ne6 $11) 32. axb5 h6 33. g4 (
33. Ra1 Ng5 34. Bxg5 hxg5 $11) 33... Ng5 34. Bxg5 {
Anand sidesteps the chance to eat many pawns for the single sacrificed piece.}
(34. Nxh6+ $5 gxh6 35. Nxf6+ Kh8 36. Bxg5 hxg5 37. Rxe5 Nd7 38. Rd5 Be7 39. Ne4
Re8 $13) 34... hxg5 35. Ra1 Rbd7 36. Ne3 Rd3 37. Nc4 Nd7 38. b4 (38. Rfd1 Nc5
