1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2 e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. O-O
O-O 9. Kh1 b6 10. a4 Bb7 11. f3 Nc6 12. Nd5 (12. Bg5 Nb4 13. Nb1 h6 (13... Rc8
14. Na3 h6 15. Bh4 g5 16. Bf2 d5 17. c3 Nc6 18. exd5 Nxd5 19. Nc4 b5 20. axb5
axb5 21. Nca5 Nxa5 22. Nxa5 Ba8 23. Bxb5 {1-0 Palac,M-Boric,M/Pula/1999/ (28)})
14. Bxf6 Bxf6 15. Na3 Qc7 16. Qd2 Nc6 17. Nc4 Rfd8 18. a5 bxa5 19. Nbxa5 Nd4
20. Nxb7 Qxb7 21. Bd3 Bg5 22. Qf2 {
1-0 Ivanchuk,V-Topalov,V/Monte Carlo/1998/ (59)}) 12... Nxd5 13. exd5 Nb4 14.
c4 a5 $1 15. Bd2 Na6 16. Bc3 {Black's set up on the queenside is not nice, but
it certainly slows down white's build up with his pawn majority.} (16. f4 Bf6
17. Bc3 exf4 18. Bxf6 Qxf6 19. Qd2 Rae8 20. Bd3 Qe5 21. Rae1 Qg5 22. Rxe8 Rxe8
23. Rxf4 Nc5 24. Nxc5 bxc5 25. Kg1 g6 26. g3 Qe7 27. Re4 {
1/2-1/2 Adams,M-King,D/England/1998/ (27)}) 16... Bg5 $5 17. Bd3 (17. g3 Bc8
18. f4 exf4 19. gxf4 Bf6 20. Nd4 $13) 17... Bc8 18. Qc2 g6 19. g3 Bh3 $1 (19...
f5 20. f4 exf4 21. gxf4 Bf6 22. Nd4 Nb4 23. Bxb4 Bxd4 24. Bc3 $11) 20. Rf2 Nb4
21. Qe2 (21. Bxb4 $5 axb4 22. Nd2 f5 23. Bf1 Bxf1 24. Nxf1 Qc7 $11) 21... Qd7 (
21... Nxd3 22. Qxd3 Rc8 $11) 22. Nd2 f5 23. Bxb4 axb4 24. b3 Qc7 25. Qe1 e4 $5
{The pawn sacrifice is very profound and depends on the activity of all black
pieces.} (25... Qc5 26. Bf1 $11) 26. fxe4 Qg7 $1 27. e5 (27. exf5 Rae8 28. Qg1
(28. Qb1 Qd4 $17) (28. Re2 $2 Rxe2 29. Bxe2 Bxd2 $19) 28... Be3 $17) (27. Ra2
Qc3 $1 (27... Rae8 28. Nf3 Bf6 (28... fxe4 29. Bxe4 (29. Nxg5 exd3 $17) 29...
Bh6 30. Ng1 $16) 29. Rae2 Bc3 30. Qc1 $14) 28. Bf1 (28. Nf3 Qxe1+ 29. Nxe1 fxe4
$19) 28... Bxf1 29. Rxf1 Bxd2 30. Qxd2 fxe4 $15) 27... dxe5 28. Bf1 Bg4 (28...
Bxf1 29. Nxf1 e4 $15) 29. Be2 h5 $1 30. Bxg4 hxg4 31. c5 (31. Rd1 Be7 $15 (
31... e4 32. Nb1 $1 {xb4})) 31... bxc5 32. Nc4 e4 33. Rd1 Bf6 {The result of
the whole operation is rather gloomy for white. He can claim only one asset in
pawn d5, but black controls the whole board and can roll over his enemy with
pawns.} (33... Qc3 34. Qxc3 (34. d6 Qxb3 35. Qf1 e3 36. Rb2 Qxa4 37. Qd3 Qc6+
38. Kg1 $17) 34... bxc3 35. Ne5 Rfb8 36. Nxg6 Rxb3 $19) 34. d6 Bd4 35. Ra2 Rae8
36. a5 e3 $1 37. Qf1 g5 (37... f4 $5 38. gxf4 Rxf4 39. Qg2 (39. Qxf4 e2 40.
Rxe2 (40. Re1 Qb7+) 40... Rxe2 41. a6 Qa7 $19) 39... Rf2 $17) 38. Qg2 f4 39.
Qd5+ Kh8 (39... Rf7 $2 40. d7 Rd8 41. a6 Rdxd7 42. a7 $3 $16) 40. gxf4 gxf4 41.
d7 Rd8 {
The pawn mass e3-f4-g4 is much more dangerous than the lonely hero on d7.} 42.
Rxd4 (42. Qh5+ Qh7 43. Qxg4 f3 44. Rxd4 Qb1+ 45. Qg1 Qxg1+ 46. Kxg1 cxd4 $19)
42... cxd4 43. Qh5+ Kg8 44. Rg2 (44. Qd5+ Kh7 45. Qh5+ Qh6 $19) 44... g3 45.
Qd5+ (45. hxg3 f3 $19) 45... Kh7 46. Qh5+ Qh6 47. Qd5 Qg6 48. a6 f3 $1 (48...
e2 49. Rxe2 Qb1+ 50. Kg2 f3+ 51. Kh3 fxe2 52. Qh5+ Kg7 $19) (48... f3 $1 49.
Rxg3 Qb1+ 50. Rg1 Qxg1+ $1 51. Kxg1 f2+ $19) 0-1

