1. d4 {Ftacnik} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 b6 7.
Nf3 Bb7 8. e3 d6 {Is the main line.} 9. b3 Ne4 (9... Nbd7 $5 {-is the main
line.See comments to Timman,J-Karpov,A/FIDE-ch,NLD/INA,1993/CBM 36(1/2-1/2)
(Ftacnik)(19)}) ({Slightly worse is:} 9... a5) 10. Qc2 f5 ({
In my opinion better is:} 10... Nd7 $5) 11. Bb2 (11. Be2 Nd7 (11... Ng5 $5) 12.
O-O Ng5 13. Nxg5 Qxg5 14. d5 Qg6 15. Bb2 a5 16. Rad1 e5 17. f4 $14 {
1-0 Kozul,Z-Grosar,A/Nova Gorica 1997/CBM 56 ext (58)}) 11... Ng5 $6 $146 {
Ftacnik: 'Black wants to benefit from pressure along a8-h1 diagonal, but the
idea is tactically unsound.'} (11... Nd7 $142 12. Bd3 $5 {
-transfers to 9...Nbd7} (12. Be2 $5 {/\0-0,Ne1,f3}) (12. Rd1 $5)) 12. d5 $1 {
-is the best reaction to-11...Ng5} ({Senseless:} 12. Be2 $6 {in view of} Nxf3+
13. gxf3 $11) 12... exd5 $140 ({Dubious:} 12... Nxf3+ 13. gxf3 exd5 14. Rg1 $40
) ({After:} 12... e5 $6 13. Be2 {white has a big positional advantage.}) 13.
O-O-O c5 $2 ({Can be recommended for black:} 13... dxc4 14. Bxc4+ Kh8 (14... d5
$2 15. Nxg5 Qxg5 16. Rxd5 $1 Kh8 17. h4 Qh5 (17... Qxg2 $2 18. Rdd1 $1 Qxh1 19.
Rxh1 Bxh1 20. Qc3 Rf6 $8 21. Qxf6 gxf6 22. Bxf6#) (17... Qg6 $2 18. h5 $18) 18.
Rh3 $1 Bxd5 19. Rg3 $1 $18) 15. Qc3 $1 (15. Nxg5 $6 Qxg5 16. h4 Qh6 $13) 15...
Qe7 $8 16. Qxg7+ Qxg7 17. Bxg7+ Kxg7 18. Nxg5 $14 Kg6 $140 19. Ne6 Rc8 20. Nf4+
Kf6 21. Nd5+ {with a positional advantage in the endgame.}) 14. cxd5 Ba6 ({
After:} 14... Nd7 15. Bd3 {white has a strong initiative.}) ({Dubious:} 14...
Ne4 {in view of:} 15. g4 $40) 15. h4 $1 Nxf3 (15... Ne4 $5 16. g4 $1 {
(Huzman,A)} Nxf2 17. Qxf2 fxg4 (17... Bxf1 $4 18. Rhxf1 fxg4 19. Qg3 $18) 18.
Bxa6 Rxf3 ({Identically-} 18... Nxa6 19. Qe2 Rxf3 20. Qxa6) 19. Qe2 Nxa6 20.
Qxa6 {+/=/+/-}) 16. gxf3 Bxf1 17. Rdxf1 $16 {with the idea Rfg1,Rg5,Rhg1->} Nd7
18. Rfg1 {Ftacnik: 'From higher point of view black is quite lost. White will
increase pressure along a1-h8 diagonal and g file. In proper moment the h file
can be open with the march of h pawn.'} Rf7 (18... Ne5 {Ftacnik} 19. f4 Ng4 20.
f3 Nf6 21. Qxf5 $18) 19. Rg5 c4 (19... g6 $143 20. Rhg1) (19... Qf8 $143 20.
Rhg1 Ne5 21. f4 Ng4 22. e4 $1) 20. bxc4 Rc8 21. Rxf5 $1 (21. Rhg1 $6 Ne5 22.
Kb1 $14) 21... Rxc4 $6 ({Slightly better is:} 21... Rxf5 22. Qxf5 Rxc4+ 23. Kb1
$16) 22. Qxc4 Rxf5 23. Bxg7 $1 {After this move white has a forcing win!
Ftacnik: 'Beautiful idea opens access to black king.'} Kxg7 $8 24. Qg4+ Kf6 $8
25. e4 Re5 (25... Qc7+ $144 {-see 26...Qc7+}) 26. f4 Qc7+ (26... Rxe4 $2 27.
Qg5+) ({Also loses:} 26... Re7 27. Rg1 Kf7 28. Qh5+ $1 Kf8 $8 29. Qh6+ Kf7 30.
Rg7+ Ke8 31. Rg8+ $18) ({Slightly better:} 26... Re8 27. Rg1 Qc7+ 28. Kb1 Ke7
29. Qg5+ Nf6 $8 30. e5 $18) 27. Kb1 Qc3 {Ftacnik: 'An act of desperation,
since the retreat of the rook will cost the life of her royal master.'} (27...
Rxe4 28. Rg1 Re7 29. Qg5+ Kf7 30. Qh5+ {and mate in 8}) (27... Re7 28. Rg1 {
and mate in 5}) (27... Re8 $142 28. Rg1 Ke7 29. Qg5+ Nf6 30. e5 $18) 28. fxe5+
Nxe5 29. Qe6+ Kg7 30. Rg1+ Ng6 31. Qe7+ Kg8 32. Qe8+ Kg7 33. Qe7+ $138 Kg8 34.
Qe8+ Kg7 35. Qb5 $1 $18 Kf7 36. h5 Ne5 37. Qb2 Qf3 (37... Qd3+ 38. Qc2 Qxa3 39.
Qc7+) 38. Qc2 Kf6 39. Ka2 b5 40. Rg3 Qf4 41. Qe2 Qc1 42. f4 $1 Qxf4 43. Rg2 1-0

