1. e4 {Tyomkin,D That is a rapid chess game, and as it usually happens in this
kind of chess, players make mistakes much more often. But sometimes those
games are much more spectacular, because of the same reason - even top guys
make mistakes quite often and the evaluations vary each few moves.} d6 2. d4
Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Be2 O-O 6. O-O c6 7. a4 Nbd7 8. a5 Qc7 $146 (8...
e5 9. dxe5 dxe5 10. b3 (10. a6 Qc7 (10... b6 11. Qd6 Nc5 12. Qxd8 Rxd8 13. Nxe5
Nfxe4 14. Nxe4 Bxe5 15. Nxc5 bxc5 16. Ra5 $1) 11. axb7 Bxb7 12. Be3 Ng4 13. Bg5
Nc5 14. Bc4 h6 15. b4 Nxe4 16. Nxe4 hxg5 17. Nfxg5 Nh6 18. Qd6 $16 {
1/2-1/2 Loginov,V-Lukin,A/St.Petersburg 1996/CBM 56 ext (91)}) 10... Re8 11.
Bc4 h6 12. Qe2 Qc7 13. Rd1 Bf8 14. Nh4 Kg7 15. Bxh6+ $1 Kxh6 16. Bxf7 Bb4 17.
Bxg6 $16 {1-0 Sutovskij,E-Delemarre,J/Bratislava 1993/TD (40)}) 9. Be3 e5 10.
dxe5 dxe5 11. h3 Rd8 12. Qb1 {Such an interesting monouvre of queen.White
tranfers the queen to line "a",changing the defender of a5-pawn.} Nf8 13. Qa2
Be6 14. Qa3 h6 15. Rfd1 N8d7 16. Nd2 (16. Qa4 $142 Bf8 17. Bc4 b5 18. axb6 axb6
19. Qb3 $11) 16... Bf8 17. b4 (17. Qa4 Nc5 {forcing favourable exchnge of Be3.}
) 17... c5 18. b5 c4 19. Qb2 b6 20. axb6 axb6 21. Nf3 (21. Ndb1 $5 Rxa1 22.
Qxa1) 21... Rxa1 22. Qxa1 Rc8 23. Nd5 Bxd5 24. exd5 Ne4 $15 {
coming to the block on d6.} 25. Nd2 Nd6 26. g4 $6 {
It weekens the kingside and creates an attacking targets for black.} (26. Qa6
f5 27. f3 Re8) 26... Bg7 27. Qb1 f5 28. Nf3 f4 29. Bc1 g5 {
The main problem of white that he can not block e4-square.} 30. Ba3 Nc5 31. Nd2
(31. Bb2 $2 Nce4 $17) 31... c3 32. Nc4 e4 33. Nxd6 Qxd6 34. Bxc5 bxc5 $1 (34...
Qxc5 $2 35. d6 f3 36. Bxf3 $1 exf3 37. Qb3+ Kh7 38. Rd5 Qc4 39. Qxc4 Rxc4 40.
d7 Bf6 41. Rf5 (41. d8=Q Bxd8 42. Rd7+ Kg6 43. Rxd8 Rb4 $132) 41... Rd4 42.
Rxf6 Rxd7 43. Rxf3 Rd5 $16) 35. f3 $2 (35. Qa2 $1 f3 36. Bf1 Rf8 (36... Qf4 $2
37. d6+ Kh8 38. Qe6 $18) (36... Bd4 37. Qa6 Bxf2+ 38. Kxf2 Qh2+ 39. Ke3 Qf4+
40. Kf2 $11) 37. Qa6 Qf4 38. Qe6+ Kh8 39. d6 Qd2 $132) 35... Rb8 36. Qb3 (36.
fxe4 $2 f3 37. Bxf3 Qg3+ 38. Bg2 Be5 39. Rd3 Qh2+ 40. Kf1 Bd4 $19) 36... Bd4+
37. Kg2 Kg7 38. Qc4 Qe5 39. d6 $138 (39. Ra1 exf3+ (39... Re8 40. Ra7+ Kh8 41.
Kh1 $1 $14) 40. Bxf3 Qe3 41. Qe2 Rxb5 42. Ra7+ $11) 39... Qxd6 40. Ra1 Qe7 41.
Qd5 exf3+ 42. Qxf3 Re8 43. Bd3 Qc7 44. b6 (44. Ra6 Re3 45. Rg6+ Kf8 46. Qa8+
Ke7 47. b6 f3+ (47... Qe5 48. Qb7+ Kf8 49. Qc8+ Ke7 50. Qb7+ $11) 48. Qxf3 Qb8
49. Rg7+ Kd6 50. Qf7 Bxg7 51. Qxg7 $17) 44... Qxb6 45. Qd5 Qc7 46. Rb1 Re7 47.
Qf5 f3+ $1 48. Qxf3 c4 49. Be4 Qe5 50. Re1 (50. Bf5 Qe2+ (50... Bc5 $2 51. Rb7
$11) 51. Qxe2 Rxe2+ 52. Kf3 Re3+ 53. Kg2 Be5 $17) 50... Rf7 51. Qe2 Rf2+ 52.
Qxf2 Bxf2 53. Kxf2 Qd4+ 54. Kf1 Qd2 55. Re2 Qf4+ 56. Kg2 Qc1 57. Bf3 Kf6 58.
Rf2 $2 {White missed a wat to create simple fortress:} (58. Bd5 $11) 58... Ke5
$19 {Now black king has an entry through the queenside.} 59. Re2+ Kd4 60. Re4+
Kc5 61. Re2 Kb4 62. Rf2 Ka3 63. Be4 Kb2 64. Bf5 {
White cannot keep the bishop on big diagonal, because of sacrifice on-c2.} Qe3
{The next step of blacks plan is to capture big diagonal a8-h1 by queen and
then to insert the king.  But the win of black is still a big question.} 65.
Bg6 Qe5 66. Bf5 Qd5+ 67. Kg1 Kc1 68. Rf1+ Kd2 69. Rf2+ Ke3 70. Rf1 Qd2 71. Kh1
Qe2 72. Ra1 $2 (72. Kg1 $142) 72... Kf4 73. Rg1 h5 74. Bc8 h4 $2 (74... Qxc2
$19) 75. Bf5 Kf3 76. Bc8 $6 (76. Bh7 Ke3 77. Rg2 (77. Bf5 Qf3+ 78. Kh2 Kf2)
77... Qf1+ 78. Kh2 Kf3 79. Rg1 Qf2+ 80. Kh1 Qa7 81. Bf5 Ke2 $19) 76... Qxc2 77.
Bb7+ Kf4 78. Bc6 Ke5 79. Bg2 Qd2 80. Rf1 c2 81. Ra1 0-1

