$16) 11. Nf3 d6 12. Nbd2 e6 13. dxe6 fxe6 14. Bd3 d5 15. O-O $14)) 9... e6 10.
Nf3 exd5 (10... c4 $15 {Alterman}) 11. Qxd5 (11. exd5 b4 $15 (11... Re8 {
Alterman} 12. O-O d6 $15 13. Qxb5 Ba6 $19)) 11... Qb6 $1 $15 12. Nbd2 (12. Qxa8
$2 {Alterman} Bb7 13. Qxb7 Qxb7 $17) (12. O-O {Alterman} Bb7 13. Qd3 c4 14. Qc2
Re8 15. Nfd2 d5 16. a4 a6 17. axb5 (17. Bf3 d4 (17... dxe4 18. Bxe4 Nc6 $15)
18. cxd4 Qxd4 19. axb5 Qxb2 (19... axb5 20. Rxa8 Bxa8 21. Nc3 b4 $15 (21... b4
22. Nd5 Bxd5 (22... c3 23. Nc7 $132) 23. exd5 Rc8 $15)) 20. Qxb2 Bxb2 21. Ra2
c3 22. e5 Bxf3 23. Nxf3 a5 $17) 17... axb5 18. Rxa8 Bxa8 19. Bf3 dxe4 20. Nxe4
Nd7 $15) 12... Bb7 13. Qb3 c4 $1 14. Qd1 ({Differently after:} 14. Qc2 $2 Re8 {
'=/+' Alterman.} 15. O-O $140 d5 {
black has a material and positional advantage.}) (14. Qc2 $15 {Alterman}) 14...
d6 $1 {'!?' Alterman.  Alterman: 'Black do not change a pawn d on e
calculating hereafter to attack it.'} (14... Re8 $15 {Alterman}) (14... d5 {
Alterman} 15. exd5 Bxd5 16. O-O Nc6 $15) 15. a4 ({Also after:} 15. O-O Nd7 {
with the idea Nc5,Rfe8 black has a big positional advantage.}) 15... a6 16.
axb5 axb5 17. Rxa8 Bxa8 18. O-O Nd7 19. Re1 ({Badly:} 19. b3 {in view of:} Bxc3
20. bxc4 $140 b4 $17) ({Apparently better is:} 19. Qb1 {/\Bd1-c2(><Pe4)}) 19...
Nc5 20. Bf1 Re8 21. Qc2 $6 ({Slightly better is:} 21. Qb1) 21... h6 {
'-/+' Alterman.} ({In my opinion slightly better is:} 21... h5) 22. g3 (22. Nd4
