1. c4 e6 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. e4 d5 4. e5 Ne4 5. Nf3 Be7 6. h4 $5 $146 {An interesting
novelty. White prepares attack on king side in case of short castle and also
prevents Ne4-g5.} Nxc3 ({After the game Topalov suggested:} 6... Nc6 $142 7. d4
f6 8. Bd3 $14) 7. dxc3 dxc4 8. Qa4+ Bd7 9. Qxc4 Bc6 10. Qg4 Bxf3 11. gxf3 (11.
Qxf3 Qd5 {and black is only slightly worse in the endgame.}) 11... Bf8 $4 {
Decisive mistake: black looses too much time.  Correct was:} (11... g6 12. h5
Qd5 $1 {and "Black is OK"}) 12. f4 Nd7 13. Be3 c6 14. O-O-O {
Due to the mistake on the 11th  move, white has now big development advantage.}
Qa5 (14... h5 15. Qh3 g6 (15... Qc7 16. f5 $36) 16. Bc4 $1 {
following with the sacrifice on e6.}) 15. f5 $3 (15. Kb1 O-O-O $11) 15... Qxa2
(15... Nxe5 16. Qe4 exf5 17. Qxf5 $40) 16. fxe6 Qxe6 (16... Nxe5 17. exf7+ Qxf7
18. Qe4) 17. Qf4 $1 $18 Rd8 {Black was loosing also after:} (17... Qxe5 18. Bh3
) (17... Nxe5 18. Bh3 Qf6 19. Rhe1) 18. Bc4 Qe7 19. Rhe1 h5 (19... Nxe5 20. Bd4
$18) 20. Qg3 (20. e6 fxe6 21. Bxe6 $18) 20... Nxe5 21. Rxd8+ Kxd8 22. Bf4 (22.
Bg5 $2 f6 23. Rxe5 Qd6 $13) 22... Nxc4 23. Rxe7 Kxe7 (23... Bxe7 24. Qd3+) 24.
Qd3 $1 1-0

