1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 d6 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 g6 7. g3 Bg7 8. Bg2
O-O 9. O-O Re8 10. Bf4 {
Nikolic's favourite line against the Benoni requires subtle play from Black.}
Na6 $5 (10... a6 $143 11. a4 Ne4 12. Nxe4 Rxe4 13. Nd2 Rb4 14. Ra2 $1 Qe7 15.
b3 g5 16. Be3 Bd4 17. Bxd4 Rxd4 18. e3 Rb4 19. Nc4 Nd7 20. f4 Rb8 21. Qd3 g4
22. Rd1 Nf8 23. Qc3 $16 {Nikolic,P-Hracek,Z/EU-chT Batumi/1999/}) ({
A playable alternative is} 10... Qb6 11. Rc1 Nh5 12. Bd2 Bg4 13. h3 Bxf3 14.
Bxf3 Nf6 15. g4 h6 16. Rb1 Nbd7 17. Bg2 a6 18. b4 cxb4 19. Na4 Qc7 20. Bxb4 b5
21. Nc3 Qb6 22. e3 a5 23. Ba3 b4 $15 {
Vaulin,A-Tunik,G/Naberezhnie Chelni/ 1988/}) 11. Nd2 {
After this typical Benoni move White's B lands on the uncomfortable square e3.}
(11. Nb5 Bf8 12. Re1 Nc7 13. Nxc7 Qxc7 14. Rc1 a5 15. b3 Bd7 16. Nd2 Nh5 $1 17.
Ne4 Bf5 18. Rxc5 Qd8 19. Rc4 Nxf4 20. gxf4 b5 21. Rd4 Bg7 22. Ng3 Bc2 23. Qxc2
Bxd4 24. Qd3 Qb6 $15 {Kaidanov,G-Romanishin,O/Groningen PCA/1993/}) ({
White's main move is} 11. Re1 {/\e4} Nc7 (11... Bg4 12. Nd2 (12. h3 Bxf3 13.
Bxf3 Qd7 14. e4 Rad8 15. Kg2 c4 16. e5 (16. Be3 Nb4 17. Bxa7 Nd3 18. Re2 b5 19.
Bd4 h5 20. a4 Nh7 21. Nxb5 Ng5 22. Re3 Qxh3+ 23. Kg1 Nxf2 $1 24. Kxf2 Qh2+ 25.
Kf1 Bxd4 $40 {Adorjan,A-Romanishin,O/Debrecen/1990/}) 16... dxe5 17. Rxe5 Nb4
18. Rxe8+ Rxe8 19. Qd2 Nd3 20. a4 h5 21. Be3 a6 22. a5 h4 23. g4 Qc7 24. Ra4
Nd7 $36 {Cech,P-Stocek,J/CZE-chT/1999/}) 12... Nh5 13. Be3 Qd7 14. a4 Bh3 15.
Bf3 Bg4 16. Bg2 Bh3 17. Nc4 Bxg2 18. Kxg2 Nc7 19. Qd3 f5 20. Bd2 Rf8 21. f3 $14
{Sorokin,M-Robledo,N/Buenos Aires/1997/}) (11... Ne4 12. Nxe4 Rxe4 13. Nd2 Rd4
14. a3 Rxf4 15. gxf4 Bxb2 16. Ra2 Bg7 17. e4 b5 18. e5 Bf5 19. Nf3 Nc7 20. exd6
Ne8 21. d7 Nd6 22. Ne5 $13 {1/2,Gleizerov,E-Moskalenko,V/Alushta/1993/}) (11...
Nh5 12. Bg5 Qd7 13. e4 b5 14. Bf1 Nc7 15. e5 dxe5 16. d6 b4 17. Na4 Ne6 18. Bc4
Nd4 19. Nxc5 Qxd6 20. Nxd4 Qxc5 21. Rc1 Qf8 22. Bd5 Rb8 23. Rc7 Qd6 24. Nb5 $1
{1-0 Scheeren,P-Ligterink,G/Hilversum/1984/}) 12. e4 Bg4 13. h3 Bxf3 14. Bxf3
Qd7 15. a4 h6 16. Bg2 Nh5 17. Be3 b5 18. axb5 Nxb5 19. Qa4 a6 20. g4 Nf6 21.
Nxb5 Qxb5 $11 {1/2,Barbero,G-Frias,V/Wijk aan Zee-B/1991/}) 11... Nh5 12. Be3
Nc7 13. a4 b6 14. Bf3 $146 (14. Nc4 Ba6 15. Na3 (15. Qb3 Qd7 16. Ne4 $2 Bxc4
17. Qxc4 Bxb2 18. Rab1 Bg7 19. Rb3 Nf6 20. Nxf6+ Bxf6 21. Bf3 Rab8 22. Rfb1 Rb7
23. h4 Reb8 24. Bg4 Qd8 25. Bd2 Bd4 26. e3 Be5 27. f4 Bg7 28. e4 Bd4+ 29. Kg2
Qe8 30. Bf3 a6 31. Ba5 b5 $19 {Kapelan,M-Davies,N/Vrsac/1989/}) 15... Nf6 (
15... Rxe3 $5 16. fxe3 Qe7 $44) 16. Bg5 h6 17. Bf4 Ng4 18. Re1 Ne5 19. Qc2 Qd7
(19... Bc8 $5 $13) 20. h3 b5 $6 21. axb5 Bxb5 22. Bd2 Ba6 23. b3 Qe7 24. f4 Nd7
25. e4 Rab8 26. Nc4 $36 {Rossetto,H-Ocampo,R/Mar del Plata/1972/}) 14... Ba6
15. Re1 Rxe3 $5 (15... Qe7 $132 {was certainly also playable, but in a rapid
game Topalov wants to unbalance the position as soon as possible.}) 16. fxe3 (
16. Bxh5 $4 Rxc3 $19) 16... Nf6 $44 {White's problem is that he has active
possibilities with his crippled P. And without open files for the R an extra
exchange has little significance.} 17. Qc2 Qe7 18. e4 (18. Nf1 h5 {
is very similar.}) 18... h5 19. e3 (19. b3 Nd7 20. Nc4 h4 $36) 19... Bh6 20.
Nd1 Re8 21. Nf2 Nd7 22. b4 (22. Nc4 $142 $5 Bxc4 23. Qxc4 Ne5 24. Qe2 a6 $44)
22... Ne5 23. b5 $6 (23. bxc5 bxc5 $44 (23... dxc5 $5 $13 {/\Rf8,Ne8-d6}))
23... Bc8 24. Bg2 h4 $36 {Closing the << robs White of any possible <=> on
this side of the board. White doesn't find any targets for the rest of the
game and Black's minor pieces just take his position apart in the end.} 25. Ra2
(25. Nc4 hxg3 26. hxg3 Bg7 $15 {><g3}) 25... hxg3 26. hxg3 Qg5 27. Nf1 Bg7 28.
Qe2 a6 $5 29. Rb1 (29. bxa6 $2 Bxa6 30. Nh3 $8 Qe7 31. Qd2 Bc4 $17) 29... Qd8
30. Bh3 Bb7 31. Nd3 (31. Nd2 Qg5 32. Kg2 Ra8 $36) 31... f5 $1 {|^[+]} 32. Nxe5
Bxe5 33. exf5 (33. Bg2 $5 Qg5 34. exf5 gxf5 $13) 33... Qg5 34. Rd2 axb5 35.
axb5 gxf5 36. Qf3 Rf8 {><b5,d5,e3,g3} 37. Bg2 (37. e4 $5 {/\} fxe4 38. Qxe4
Rxf1+ 39. Rxf1 Qxd2 40. Qg6+ Bg7 41. Be6+ Nxe6 42. Qxe6+ $11) 37... Kg7 38. Rc1
Rf7 $1 $17 39. Rc4 (39. Rb1 c4 $17) 39... Nxb5 40. Rh4 Nc3 41. Bh3 (41. Rh5 Qg6
$19 {o^b,c}) 41... Ne4 $19 42. Rg2 Qg6 43. g4 (43. Qd1 Nc3 44. Qh5 Qxh5 45.
Rxh5 Bxd5 $19) 43... Ng5 44. Qxf5 $6 (44. Qd1 f4 45. Kh1 Qe4 $19 {->}) 44...
Nf3+ (44... Rxf5 45. gxf5 Nf3+ 46. Kf2 Qxg2+ $19) 0-1

