1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f3 e6 7. Be3 b5 8. Qd2
Nbd7 9. g4 h6 10. O-O-O Bb7 11. h4 b4 12. Na4 Qa5 13. b3 Nc5 14. a3 Nxa4 15.
axb4 Qc7 16. bxa4 d5 17. e5 Nd7 18. f4 Nb6 19. f5 Nxa4 20. fxe6 O-O-O $6 {
Dubious novelty, that sets high stakes on the effects of the counterplay
against white king. Unfortunatelly white's central pawns will be too strong.} (
20... Nc3 21. exf7+ Kxf7 22. Bd3 Bxb4 23. Rdf1+ Kg8 24. Qf2 Re8 25. e6 Rf8 26.
Qf7+ Rxf7 27. exf7+ Qxf7 28. Rxf7 Kxf7 29. Rf1+ Ke7 30. Nf5+ Kd8 31. Nxg7 {
1-0 Selin,O-Rogovoi,M/St Petersburg/2000/ (60)}) 21. exf7 Nc3 (21... Qxf7 22.
Bd3 Qe7 23. Bf5+ Kb8 24. Ne6 Qxb4 25. Qxb4 Bxb4 26. Rd4 Bc5 27. Nxd8 Bxd4 28.
Bxd4 Rxd8 29. e6 $18) 22. e6 Bxb4 23. Qd3 Na2+ (23... Qa5 24. Kd2 $1 Ne4+ 25.
Ke2 Ng3+ 26. Kf3 Nxh1 27. Bg2 $16) (23... Ba3+ 24. Kd2 Ne4+ 25. Ke2 Ng3+ 26.
Kf3 Nxh1 27. Qxa3 Qg3+ 28. Ke2 $18) 24. Kb2 $1 Bc3+ 25. Kb1 {White's excellent
defensive triangel with the king has showed the limits of black's attack.} (25.
Kxa2 $2 Qa5+ $19) 25... Nb4 (25... Qb6+ 26. Nb5 Qxb5+ (26... d4 27. Qc4+ Kb8
28. Bf4+ Ka8 29. Qxa2 Bxh1 30. e7 $18) 27. Qxb5 axb5 28. e7 d4 29. exd8=Q+ (29.
Bxb5 Bxh1 30. Rxh1 dxe3 31. Kxa2 e2 32. exd8=Q+ Kxd8 33. Bxe2 $18) 29... Rxd8
30. Rh2 Rf8 31. Bxd4 $18) 26. Bf4 $1 (26. Qf5 g6 $19) 26... Qc5 (26... Qxf4 27.
Qxc3+ $18) (26... Nxd3 27. Bxc7 Kxc7 28. Rxd3 Bb4 29. Re3 $18) 27. Qf5 {
Black king could be mated too so Topalov's strategy triumphs.} g6 (27... Bxd4
28. e7+ Rd7 29. e8=Q+ Rxe8 30. fxe8=Q#) 28. Qe5 1-0

