1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nd7 5. Nf3 Ngf6 6. Bg5 Be7 7. Nxf6+ Bxf6
8. h4 O-O (8... h6 9. Bxf6 Qxf6 10. Qd2 $14 {Die eingeschobenen Züge h4 und h6
begünstigen Weiß, denn im Falle der kurzen schwarzen Rochade gibt es mit
g2-g4-g5 einen klaren und starken Plan.}) 9. Bxf6 {Possible continuation,
however promising nothing to white.The main line is considered to be 9.Qd2.} (
9. Qd2 Qe7 (9... e5 10. Bxf6 $1 (10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Qxd8 Nxf3+ $10) 10... Qxf6
11. O-O-O exd4 (11... e4 12. Ng5 $16 {>< Pe4}) 12. Qxd4 Qxd4 13. Rxd4 {
Weiß hat nur einen winzigen Vorteil, aber die einzigen Partien mit diesem
Endspiel endeten beide 1-0.} Nf6 (13... Re8 14. Bc4 Nb6 15. Re1 Bd7 16. Bb3
Rxe1+ 17. Nxe1 Kf8 18. Nd3 $14 {Brodsky,M-Doroshkievich,V/Rostov op 1993}) 14.
Bc4 a6 15. Re1 b5 16. Bd5 $14 {
Morovic Fernandez,I-Nogueiras,J/Capablanca mem-A 1996}) 10. O-O-O Rd8 11. Qe3
b6 12. Bd3 Bb7 13. Ne5 Rac8 14. Kb1 h6 15. f4 $36 {
Weinzettl,E-Rohler,S/Graz op 1994}) (9. Bd3 c5 10. c3 cxd4 11. cxd4 e5 $1 12.
Qc2 $2 h6 13. Bxf6 Qxf6 14. Ng5 exd4 $17 {Pinkas,K-Schmidt,W/POL-ch 1993}) 9...
Qxf6 10. Qe2 $5 {Preventing e5,but closing to the bishop the way out.} (10. Qd2
e5 (10... c5 11. O-O-O cxd4 12. Nxd4 e5 13. Nf3 $14) 11. O-O-O exd4 12. Qxd4
Qxd4 13. Nxd4 Nf6 14. Be2 Bg4 $11) 10... b6 11. Qe4 Rb8 12. Bd3 g6 13. Ne5 (13.
Qc6 $6 Qd8 14. Ne5 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Bb7 16. Qc3 Bxg2 17. Rg1 Bf3 $17) 13... c5 14.
Bb5 {Making black to take on e5.Doesn't work} (14. h5 $2 cxd4 15. Ng4 Qg5 16.
hxg6 hxg6 17. Nh6+ Kg7 18. Qxd4+ Nf6 $19 {and white knight is trapped on h6.})
14... Nxe5 15. Qxe5 (15. dxe5 Bb7 16. Qe2 (16. Qe3 Qf5) 16... Qf4 17. g3 Qf3
$15) 15... Qxe5+ 16. dxe5 Bb7 $11 {At this stage a draw agreement could come,
but we must not forget that we are talking about not 'conventional' chess...}
17. O-O Rfd8 18. Rfd1 Kf8 19. f3 ({After} 19. f4 $5 $11 {
the game would end up quicker.}) 19... Ke7 20. Kf2 Rd5 21. c4 $5 Rxe5 (21...
Rdd8 $11) 22. Rd7+ Kf6 23. Rad1 a6 24. Rc7 $5 (24. Ba4) 24... axb5 (24... Bxf3
$5 25. Rdd7 Rf8 26. gxf3 axb5 27. cxb5 Rh5 28. Kg3 (28. Rb7 Rxh4 29. Rxb6 Ra8
$1 $17) 28... g5 29. hxg5+ Rxg5+ 30. Kh2 h5 31. Rb7 Ke5 $13) 25. Rdd7 {
Winning back the bishop.} Rf8 26. Rxb7 bxc4 27. Rxb6 Rh5 28. g3 g5 29. hxg5+
Rxg5 30. a4 Ra8 31. Rbb7 Rg7 32. Rdc7 Rxa4 1/2-1/2

