Bb7 {Ftacnik} 15. Qh6 Bg7 16. Qh5 Qd7 17. cxb5 $16) 15. d7 $1 {
Cutting black position on two halfs and penetrating via d6 and d5.} Bb7 (15...
e4 {Ftacnik} 16. dxc8=Q Qxd2+ 17. Rxd2 Rfxc8 18. Nd5 $18) 16. Qd6 $1 {
Ftacnik: 'Shirov strives to prove, that there is lot of potential in passed d
pawn. Black has two unconnected halves of the board and his queen fullfils the
sorry task of blockading d7 pawn.'} e4 (16... Be7 17. Qh6 f6 18. Rh3 (18. cxb5
$5 axb5 19. Bxb5 Nd4 20. Rh3 $40) 18... Rf7 19. Rg3+ Kh8 20. Qh5 Rf8 21. Qxf5
$18) (16... Qe7 17. Qc7 $1 Rab8 18. Nd5 Qd8 19. Qd6 Bg7 20. Rh3 $36) 17. Nd5 $1
Bg7 (17... Bxb2+ {Ftacnik} 18. Kxb2 exf3 19. gxf3 bxc4 20. Bxc4 $18) 18. Ng5
Nd4 $6 (18... h6 {Ftacnik} 19. cxb5 axb5 20. Bxb5 Nd4 21. Ne7+ Kh8 22. Qg6 $3
fxg6 23. Nxg6+ Kg8 24. Bc4+ $18) 19. Ne7+ $1 {Every move of white deserves an
exclamation mark because of the depth of Shirov's plan.} Kh8 20. Rh3 $1 (20. b4
{Ftacnik} f6 21. Ne6 (21. bxc5 Qa5 22. Qxd4 (22. Nf7+ Rxf7 23. Rxd4 Bh6+ 24.
Kb2 (24. Kd1 Qa4+ 25. Ke1 Qa5+ $11) 24... Qb4+ $11) 22... fxg5 23. Qd2 Bc3 $16)
21... Nxe6 22. Qxe6 $16) 20... f4 (20... h6 {Ftacnik} 21. b4 f6 22. Ne6 Nxe6
23. Qxe6 $18) (20... Qa5 {Ftacnik} 21. Qxc5 Qxa2 22. Rxd4 Qa1+ 23. Kc2 Qxf1 24.
Qxf5 $18) 21. Kb1 b4 (21... f6 {Ftacnik} 22. Ne6 Nxe6 23. Qxe6 Rb8 24. Nf5 $18)
(21... h6 {Ftacnik} 22. b4 e3 23. bxc5 e2 24. Bxe2 Nxe2 25. c6 $18) 22. Be2 $1
$18 {Threatening to come to h5. '!' Ftacnik.  Ftacnik: 'Beautifull trick of
calling in last reserves via the square, that seemed to have been unaccesible.
Topalov's king on h8 has very feeble defense.'} f3 (22... Nxe2 23. Qxc5 Nd4 (
23... f5 24. Ne6 Qb8 25. Nxg7 Nc3+ 26. Ka1 Kxg7 (26... Nxd1 27. Ne8 $18) 27.
