Nxe7+ Kh8 ({or} 21... Kh7 $5 {/\} 22. Kb1 $2 b5 $1 $19) 22. Kb1 b5 $1 23. Rxd8
$1 Rxd8 (23... bxc4 $2 24. Rxf8+ Kh7 25. Rxf7 $16) 24. Qf1 {
(Sherzer-Al Vajda, Budapest FS GM 2001)} Nfd3 $1 25. cxd3 (25. fxe6 Qxe7 26.
cxd3 Qxe6 $17) 25... Qxe7 $17)) (14. Rhe1 c5 $1 15. Nxd7 Qxd7 16. f5 cxd4 17.
fxe6 fxe6 18. Qb3 Nd5 19. Re4 Bc5 20. Rg4 Kh8 21. Nh5 Qf7 $1 $15 {and it is not
easy for White to get back the sacrificed P, Feygin-Dautov, Gersenkirchen BL
2000/2001}) 14... Qc7 15. c4 (15. Rhe1 {- Hracek-Dautov, Lippstadt 2000 CBM 78}
) (15. Kb1 c5 {
This looks more straightforward, there is no need for preparation.} (15... Rad8
16. Ne2 h5 $1 {This is the typical defensive reaction in this variation,
otherwise 17.g4 comes.} 17. Bc3 g6 18. Rhg1 Qd6 19. g4 hxg4 20. Qd3 Qd5 21. Ng3
Kg7 22. h5 (22. Ne2 Rh8) 22... Nxe5 (22... gxh5 23. Nxh5+ Nxh5 24. Rxg4+ Kh8
25. Qh3 $16) (22... Nxh5 $2 23. Nxh5+ gxh5 24. Nxg4 $1 hxg4 25. Rxg4+ Kf6 26.
