Bxf6 Bxf6 7. Nf3 Nd7 8. Bc4 O-O 9. Qe2 c5 10. O-O-O Qb6 11. Nxf6+ Nxf6 12. dxc5
$14 {Magem Badals,J-Dizdar,G/Erevan olm 1996}) 6. Nf3 h6 7. Nxf6+ (7. Bxf6 Nxf6
8. Bd3 Be7 9. O-O Nxe4 10. Bxe4 O-O 11. c3 Qd6 12. Re1 c5 13. Qe2 cxd4 14. cxd4
Bf6 15. Rad1 Rb8 16. Ne5 $14 {Gligoric,S-Akopian,V Erevan 1989/}) 7... Nxf6 8.
Bxf6 (8. Bh4 c5 9. Bb5+ Bd7 10. Bxd7+ Qxd7 11. Qe2 Be7 12. O-O-O O-O 13. dxc5
Qc6 $1 14. Kb1 Rfd8 $10 {Anand,V-Ivanchuk V Linares m/2 1992 Inf 55/283/}) 8...
Qxf6 9. Bb5+ (9. g3 Bd6 10. Bg2 O-O 11. O-O e5 12. dxe5 Bxe5 13. Nxe5 Qxe5 14.
c3 c6 15. Re1 Qc7 16. Qa4 Be6 17. Rad1 Rfd8 18. h4 a5 19. b3 Rxd1 20. Rxd1 Rd8
21. Rxd8+ Qxd8 {
1/2-1/2 Vallejo Pons,F-Illescas Cordoba,M/Torneo de Pamplona 9th 1998}) (9. Bd3
a6 (9... Bd6 10. Qe2 Bd7 11. Be4 O-O-O 12. O-O Rhe8 13. c4 c6 14. Rad1 e5 15.
c5 Bc7 16. d5 cxd5 17. Rxd5 $14 {Kovalev,A-Dolmatov,S/BL9293 1993}) 10. Qe2 c5
11. O-O-O cxd4 12. Kb1 Bd6 13. h4 Bd7 14. Be4 Bb5 $15 {
Maier,C-Legky,N/ch-FRA (team) 1999}) 9... c6 10. Bd3 a6 $5 {Shirov used this
continuation against Topalov in advanced chess in Lion and won, so Anand
decides to check it out wether Topalov has come to Dortmund with an
improvement!} (10... Bd6 11. O-O (11. c3 O-O 12. Qe2 Rd8 13. O-O c5 14. Rad1
cxd4 15. cxd4 $14) 11... Bd7 (11... O-O 12. Qe2 c5 13. c3 Rb8 14. Ne5 Bxe5 15.
dxe5 Qe7 16. Rad1 Rd8 17. Qe4 g6 18. Qe3 Kg7 19. Be4 $14 {
Morovic Fernandez,I-Hergott,D/North Bay op 1996}) 12. Qe2 O-O 13. Ne5 Rfd8 14.
Qe4 g6 $13 {Kovalevskaya,E-Edzgveradze,N/Moscow-W 1996}) (10... g6 11. c3 (11.
Qe2 Bg7 12. h4 O-O 13. h5 g5 14. c3 Qe7 15. Qe4 Rd8 16. Qh7+ Kf8 17. Ne5 $40 {
Kreiman,B-Zifroni,D/Graz op 1997}) 11... Bg7 12. Qe2 O-O 13. O-O (13. O-O-O $5
{/\Kb1,h4,h5/}) 13... Rd8 14. Rad1 Bd7 15. Ne5 Be8 16. f4 $16 {
Smyslov,V-Dolmatov,S/Rostov 1993}) 11. c3 c5 12. Ne5 Bd6 13. Qe2 $146 {
Here comes Topalov's novelty. In the game with Shirov he played Ftacnik:
'Anand has chosen Shirov's play as an inspiration in this line, white sensibly
admitts the importance to support the most valuable piece in the center.'} (13.
Qa4+ Ke7 14. O-O Bxe5 15. dxe5 Qxe5 16. Rae1 Qc7 17. Qh4+ g5 18. Qh5 Bd7 {
Black managed to survive white's attack and to convert his material advantage
into a point after very sharp battle.} (18... Bd7 {Ftacnik} 19. f4 c4 20. fxg5
Qc5+ 21. Kh1 cxd3 22. Rxf7+ Kd8 {0-1 Topalov,V-Shirov,A/Leon/2001/ (49)}))
13... cxd4 14. cxd4 Bd7 ({After} 14... Bb4+ 15. Kf1 {White loses a castling
option but his rook can be brought into play over the h-file.} O-O 16. Qe4 Rd8
17. h4 {with initiative.  '|^' Ftacnik.}) 15. O-O ({After a tempting} 15. Qe4
$5 {black can hold by} Bxe5 16. dxe5 Qf5 $1 {with slightly worse position.} (
16... Qf5 $1 {Ftacnik} 17. Rc1 $14)) 15... Qf4 ({In case of} 15... Rd8 16. f4 {
Black's position is too passive.}) 16. g3 {'!' Ftacnik.} (16. Rfd1 Bxe5 17.
dxe5 Bc6 18. Rac1 Bd5 $1 (18... O-O $2 19. Rc4 Qg5 20. Rg4 Qe7 21. Qe3 Kh8 22.
Qg3 $40 (22. Qg3 {Ftacnik} f5 23. Rd4 (23. exf6 Qxf6 24. Rg6 Qxb2 $13) 23...
Bd5 24. b3 $14)) 19. Rc7 O-O $14 {'~~' Ftacnik.}) 16... Qxd4 17. Nxd7 Kxd7 18.
Qf3 $36 {White is regaining a pawn. Due to unsecure position of the black king
Topalov's position is better.} Ke7 {Ftacnik: 'Black has to be very careful in
the defense, despite compact position the centralized king can easily become
indifensible.'} (18... Kc8 {Ftacnik} 19. Be4 Kb8 20. Rfd1 Qb6 21. Qxf7 $16) 19.
Qxb7+ Kf6 20. Rad1 Qa7 (20... Qg4 {Ftacnik} 21. Bxa6 Rhb8 22. Qc6 Be5 23. b3
$16) 21. Qf3+ Ke7 22. Qg4 g5 (22... Be5 {Ftacnik} 23. Rd2 $14) 23. Bc4 Qb6 24.
Rd3 $1 {An excellent maneuver. This rook has a lot to do on the third rank.}
Rad8 (24... Qxb2 25. Re1 Qf6 26. Rf3 Qg6 27. Rxf7+ $1 Qxf7 28. Rxe6+ Kf8 29.
Rxd6 $18) 25. Rf3 $1 {Veselin is aiming at the black king.} ({
Not so promising was} 25. Rb3 Qc6 (25... Qc5 {Ftacnik} 26. Qe2 a5 $14) 26. Qe2
a5) 25... Be5 (25... Qxb2 $4 26. Rxf7+ $1 {with the checkmate in two.}) 26. Re1
f6 ({Extremely risky is} 26... Rd4 $6 27. Rxf7+ $1 Kxf7 28. Qf5+ Ke7 (28... Bf6
29. Rxe6) 29. Qxe5 Rf8 30. Bxe6 Qd6 $1 31. Qg7+ Kd8 32. Qxh6 $18 {
and white is winning '+/-' Ftacnik.}) 27. Qh5 {White is threatening with 28.
Rxe5. Black has to defend against tacktical blows on every move.} (27. Qe4 $5 {
Ftacnik} Rd4 28. Qg6 $40) 27... Qb4 {'!' Ftacnik.  Ftacnik: 'Black's position
is not bad, but white's attack can not be underestimated.'} (27... Qxb2 28. Rb3
Qd2 29. Rb7+ Rd7 30. Reb1 Rxb7 {'!?' Ftacnik.} (30... Rc8 $5 {Ftacnik} 31.
Rxd7+ (31. Qxh6 Rxc4 32. Qg7+ Ke8 $11) 31... Qxd7 32. Bxa6 $14) 31. Rxb7+ Kd6
32. Qf7 $1 Qe1+ 33. Bf1 Bd4 34. Rd7+ Ke5 35. Rxd4 Kxd4 36. Qg7 $3 $40 {
'!!' Ftacnik.} (36. Qg7 $3 Ra8 37. Qd7+ Ke5 38. Qc7+ Kf5 39. Qc2+ Ke5 (39...
Kg4 40. h3+ Kh5 41. g4+ Kh4 42. Qg6 $18) 40. Qc5+ Ke4 41. Qc6+ $18)) 28. Rxe5 {
'!' Ftacnik.} ({A similar position emerges after} 28. Re4 $5 Qd2 $1 (28... Qxb2
{Ftacnik} 29. Rb3 Qc1+ 30. Kg2 $18) 29. Rxe5 Qc1+ 30. Kg2 Qxc4) 28... Qxc4 29.
Re1 ({On} 29. Rc3 {black would have sacrificed the queen} Qxc3 $1 (29... Qxa2
$2 30. Rc7+ Kd6 31. Rec5 $18) 30. bxc3 fxe5 31. Qe2 Rd6 32. Qxe5 Rh7 {
with good drawing chances. '+/=' Ftacnik.}) 29... Qxa2 {
With every pawn capture Vishy is getting closer to desired draw.} 30. Qg6 Rhf8
31. Qxh6 Qxb2 ({In case} 31... e5 {
white could conduct the following combination} 32. Qg7+ Rf7 33. Rxe5+ $1 fxe5
34. Qxg5+ Ke6 ({after} 34... Ke8 35. Qxe5+ Kd7 {
White closes out the game with an incredible} 36. Rc3 $3 {(total domination!)}
Qb1+ 37. Kg2 Rxf2+ {(there is no other choice)} 38. Kxf2 Qxb2+ 39. Ke3 $3 {
Black is forced to trade the queens '!' Ftacnik.} Qb6+ 40. Qd4+ Qxd4+ 41. Kxd4
{the emerged endgame is hopeless for Black '+-' Ftacnik.}) 35. Rxf7 Rd1+ 36.
Kg2 Kxf7 (36... Qd5+ 37. Rf3) 37. Qh5+ Ke6 38. Qxd1 Qxb2 {with big advantage
in the queen ending. After the move which was played in the game the same
tactical idea works.} (38... Qxb2 {Ftacnik} 39. h4 $16)) 32. Qg7+ Rf7 33. Rxe6+
$1 $16 {'!' Ftacnik.} Kxe6 34. Re3+ Qe5 35. Rxe5+ fxe5 36. Qxg5 Rdf8 37. Qg4+
Kd5 38. Qd1+ Kc5 39. Qc2+ Kb4 $2 {Very stupid mistake Ftacnik: 'Anand is
probably playing serious innaccuracy in the time trouble, chances for
successful defense were promised after the correct 39...Kb6.'} ({After} 39...
Kb6 $1 40. Qb2+ (40. h4 Rxf2 41. Qxf2+ Rxf2 42. Kxf2 a5 $11 (42... a5 43. h5 a4
$11)) 40... Kc6 41. Qa2 (41. Qxe5 {Ftacnik} Rxf2 42. Qe6+ Kb7 (42... Kb5 43.
Qd5+ Kb6 44. Qd4+ Kb5 45. Qxf2 Rxf2 46. Kxf2 $18) 43. h4 R2f6 $14) 41... Rxf2
42. Qxa6+ Kd5 $14 {White can't exchange his queen for two black rooks to his
advantage,which means that black is very close to a draw here!} (42... Kd5 43.
Qb7+ (43. Qd3+ Kc6 44. Qc4+ Kd6 $11) 43... Kd4 $1 44. Qb6+ Kd3 45. Qxf2 Rxf2
46. Kxf2 Kd2 47. Kf3 Kd3 $11)) 40. Qb2+ $18 Kc5 (40... Kc4 41. Qe2+ Kd5 42.
Qd3+ $1 Kc5 43. Qxa6 $18) (40... Ka4 41. Qa1+ $1 Kb4 42. Qxa6 $18) 41. Qxe5+
Kb6 42. h4 a5 43. h5 Rd7 44. Qe6+ Kc7 45. h6 1-0

