1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 d6 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 g6 7. Nd2 Bg7 8. e4 {
The Classical line is not played too often nowadays, with aggressive lines
like f4 and Bb5+ or h3 and Bd3 being more popular.} O-O 9. Be2 Re8 10. O-O Na6
11. f3 Nc7 12. a4 Nd7 13. Kh1 b6 {Topalov has this year in a rapid game
against Kramnik revived this line, in which the relevant games were played
about 20 years ago.} 14. Ra3 $5 $146 {This otherwise typical manoeuvre for the
Classical line is here a novelty. Later on however the R will find no scope on
the 3-rd rank.} (14. Nc4 Ne5 15. Ne3 f5 (15... Rb8 16. Qc2 $14) 16. f4 Nf7 17.
exf5 gxf5 18. Bd3 Nh6 19. Ne2 $5 (19. Qc2 Qf6 $5 (19... Rf8 20. Bd2 a6 21. Rf3
Rb8 22. Rg3 Qh4 23. Rg5 Ng4 24. Nxg4 fxg4 25. Ne4 Ne8 26. g3 Qh6 27. f5 Bb7 28.
Rf1 $40 {Dydyshko,V-Lukov,V/Polanica Zdroj/1983/}) 20. Bd2 Bd7 21. Rf3 Kh8 22.
Raf1 Re7 23. Rh3 Qf7 24. Nc4 Qg6 (24... Nxd5 $5 25. Nxd6 Qe6 $13 {Kramnik}) 25.
Rg3 Ng4 26. h3 h5 $1 27. Ne3 Nxe3 28. Rxg6 Nxc2 29. Bxc2 Ne8 30. Rg5 Nf6 31.
Bxf5 Bxf5 32. Rxf5 Rae8 $44 {Kramnik,V-Topalov,V/Monaco act/2001/}) (19. Qh5
Rf8 (19... Qf6 20. Nb5 Re7 $13 {Kramnik}) 20. Bd2 Qf6 21. Rf3 Qg6 22. Qh4 Qf6
23. Qh3 Ba6 24. Bc2 Kh8 25. Rg3 Rae8 26. Rg1 Bc8 27. Ncd1 Qf7 28. Rg5 $1 $40 {
Rytov,B-Beliavsky,A/Vitebsk/1970/}) 19... Qh4 20. Ng3 Rf8 (20... Ng4 $142 $5
21. Nxg4 Qxg4 $132) 21. Qc2 Ng4 22. Nxg4 Qxg4 23. Ra3 Kh8 24. Be2 Qh4 25. Nh5
Bd4 26. Be3 Nxd5 27. Bxd4+ cxd4 28. Qd2 Bb7 29. Bf3 {
1-0,Taimanov,M-Ree,H/Wijk aan Zee/1970/}) 14... Qe7 (14... Ne5 15. f4 Nd7 16.
Nc4 {/\} Nf6 17. e5 $1 dxe5 18. d6 $36) 15. Nb5 (15. Nc4 Ne5 (15... Ba6 16. Bf4
Bxc4 17. Bxc4 $14) 16. Ne3 {also was interesting, as here after} f5 (16... a6
$5) 17. f4 Nf7 18. exf5 $14 {the R can be useful on a3.}) 15... Nxb5 16. Bxb5 (
16. axb5 f5 $13 {
and the weakness on a7 is rather abstract, while Black has concrete [+]<=>.})
16... Rd8 (16... a6 17. Bc6 Rb8 18. Rb3 $1 Rf8 19. Nc4 Ne5 20. Nxb6 Qc7 21. a5
Nxc6 22. dxc6 Qxc6 23. Nd5 $16) 17. a5 (17. Nc4 Ne5 18. Nxe5 Bxe5 $132) 17...
a6 $5 18. Bc6 (18. Bxd7 Bxd7 19. axb6 (19. Nc4 b5 20. Nb6 Ra7 $11 {/=/+}) 19...
Bb5 20. Re1 Rab8 $132) (18. axb6 Nxb6 19. Bc6 Bb7 (19... Rb8 $143 {-18.Bc6})
20. Bxb7 Qxb7 21. Qc2 (21. f4 f5 $13) 21... Rf8 $5 $132) 18... Rb8 19. axb6
Nxb6 20. b3 $1 ({Aggressive, but double-edged was} 20. f4 Nd7 (20... Bb7 21.
Bxb7 Qxb7 22. f5 $36) 21. Qc2 Rb4 $132) 20... Be5 $5 {
/\Qh4 A provocative move, Black lures White's f-pawn forward.} (20... f5 21.
exf5 gxf5 22. Re1 $14 {<->e}) (20... Bb7 21. Bxb7 Qxb7 22. Nc4 $14) (20... Nd7
21. Nc4 Ne5 22. Bf4 $14) 21. f4 (21. Nc4 Nxc4 22. bxc4 Rb1 $11) 21... Bg7 (
21... Bd4 $142 $5 22. f5 Nd7) 22. f5 Nd7 23. Bxd7 $1 (23. Nc4 Ne5 24. Nxe5 Bxe5
25. Qf3 Qh4 $5 (25... Qf6 26. fxg6 $14) 26. g3 Qf6 $132) 23... Bxd7 24. Qf3 Bd4
25. f6 Qf8 26. Nc4 (26. g4 $6 Qh6 27. Nc4 Qh4 {><>>}) 26... Bb5 27. Be3 Bxe3
28. Qxe3 h5 $1 {Black must first free his K from back-rank mates, then he can
open the position.} 29. h4 (29. h3 $5 $14 {was possibly stronger, as later on
in some lines the pawn will be en prise on h4.}) 29... Kh7 30. Rfa1 (30. e5
dxe5 31. Qxe5 Re8 32. Qf4 Re2 33. Rd1 Rbe8 $13) 30... Bxc4 (30... Re8 31. Rxa6
$1 Bxa6 32. Rxa6 Rbd8 33. Qf4 $16) 31. bxc4 Rb4 32. Rc3 (32. Qe2 Qh6 {/\Qf4}
33. g3 Rdb8 $132 {and White must beware of surprises on the 2-nd rank.}) (32.
Ra4 $5 Rdb8 33. Rxb4 cxb4 $1 (33... Rxb4 34. Rxa6 Rxc4 35. Ra7 $36) 34. Rxa6 b3
35. Rb6 b2 (35... Qd8 36. Rxb3 Rxb3 37. Qxb3 Qxf6 38. Qg3 Qf1+ $11) 36. Qb3
Rxb6 37. Qxb6 Qc8 38. Qxb2 Qxc4 $11) (32. Rxa6 Rxc4 $132) 32... Re8 $1 33. Rxa6
Rb1+ 34. Kh2 Rf1 $11 35. Rca3 {White already had no suitable way to protect
his Pf6, so Kramnik decides to force a draw.} (35. Qg3 $2 Rxe4 $36) 35... Rxf6
36. e5 Rf5 $1 {The most accurate.} (36... Rxe5 $143 37. Qxe5 dxe5 38. Rxf6 e4
39. g3 Qe7 40. Rf2) 37. e6 $8 (37. Rxd6 $2 Rexe5 38. Qxc5 $8 Qe7 39. Rh3 Re1
$19 {->}) 37... fxe6 38. Ra7+ Kg8 39. Qg3 Qf6 (39... g5 40. dxe6 Rxe6 41. hxg5
$14) 40. Ra8 Rxa8 41. Rxa8+ Kg7 (41... Kf7 42. Ra7+ Ke8 43. Qb3 Qxh4+ 44. Kg1
Qe1+ 45. Kh2 $11) 42. Ra7+ Kg8 (42... Kh6 43. Qe3+ g5 44. dxe6 Qe5+ $11) (42...
Kg8 43. Ra8+) 1/2-1/2

