$5 (7... Na6 8. Ng3 Nb4 9. f5 exf5 10. a3 f4 11. axb4 fxg3 12. hxg3 a6 (12...
Nc8 13. b5 $1 $14 {- Sutovsky-Dautov, Julian Borowski-A 3rd Essen 2001 CBM 83})
13. Bg5 b5 $1 {- Bruzon Bautista-Gonzales, CUB-ch Holguin City 2002 CBM 89} (
13... Qb8 14. Bd3 Qa7 {This is a rather sophysticated Q manoeuvre.} 15. Ne2 b5
16. c3 Bxd3 17. Qxd3 Ng6 18. Nf4 Nxf4 19. gxf4 {
and White's P chain can easily be mobilized.} h6 20. f5 $16 {
Svidler-Galkin, RUS-chT Tomsk 2001})) (7... h5 8. f5 $1 exf5 9. g5 {
- Nataf-Grabarczyk, Hasselbacken 2001 CBM 85}) 8. h4 $6 {
The is too much of P moves on the >>.} (8. dxc5 $142 {
is the natural reaction in the [+].} Nec6 9. Be3 (9. f5 $6 {
is again self-destructive.} exf5 10. Qxd5 Na6 $5 (10... fxg4 {comes also into
consideration, White's P majority on the << is counterbalanced on the other
flank.} 11. Qxd8+ (11. Bf4 Bxc2 (11... Nd7 12. O-O-O Nxc5 {looks also playable.
}) 12. Qxd8+ Kxd8 13. Rc1 Bg6 14. Bg2 Nd7 $15 {
and White has to show something for the P.}) 11... Kxd8 12. Be3 Nxe5 13. O-O-O+
Kc8 14. Bg2 Na6 15. Rd5 f6 $1 {strengthening the strong N in the [+].} (15...
Nd7 16. Rhd1 Bxc5 17. Bxc5 Ndxc5 18. Nb5 $1 $14) 16. Rhd1 Be7 $13) 11. Qxd8+
Rxd8 $13) 9... Nd7 10. Ng3 (10. f5 $6 {is again dubious in view of} exf5 11.
gxf5 Bxf5 12. Nxd5 Bxc5) 10... Ndxe5 $1 {This was the idea, but} (10... d4 11.
Bxd4 Bxc2 12. Qxc2 Nxd4 13. Qa4 Bxc5 14. O-O-O $14 {
and White has the better development.}) (10... Bxc5 $6 11. Bxc5 Nxc5 12. f5 $16
) 11. Nb5 $1 {is the real answer!} (11. fxe5 d4 $13) 11... a6 (11... d4 12. Bd2
$1 Bxc5 (12... a6 13. Nd6+ $16) 13. fxe5 Nxe5 14. Qe2 f6 15. Ne4 $14) 12. Nd6+
Bxd6 13. cxd6 Nc4 14. Bxc4 dxc4 15. O-O $14) 8... h5 $1 9. f5 $1 {
otherwise the whole >> collapses.} exf5 10. g5 {
This old blockading idea is not so effective, because the [+] is not closed.}
Nec6 11. Bg2 cxd4 12. Nxd5 (12. Nxd4 Bb4 $15) 12... Nd7 13. Nxd4 Ndxe5 14. Nb5
{'!?' Ftacnik.  Ftacnik: 'White has to play creatively, since with completed
development second player might be very satisfied with his prospects.'} (14.
Bf4 {Ftacnik} Bd6 15. Qd2 O-O $11) 14... Rc8 (14... Bd6 $5 {Ftacnik} 15. Nf6+
Ke7 16. Nd5+ Kf8 17. Nxd6 Qxd6 18. Bf4 Qc5 $13) 15. Qe2 {'!' Ftacnik.} Bd6 (
15... Bc5 $5 16. Bf4 (16. b4 $1 {Ftacnik} Bd6 17. Bf4 $16) 16... O-O 17. O-O-O
Qa5 18. Rhe1 Rfe8 19. Kb1 $13) (15... f6 {Ftacnik} 16. Bf4 $40) 16. Nxd6+ (16.
Bf4 $5 {Ftacnik} Bb8 17. O-O-O Kf8 18. Rh3 $16) 16... Qxd6 17. Bf4 O-O 18.
O-O-O {White still blockades the vital f4 square, but the fight arises now on
the other side of the board.} Qc5 {'?!' Ftacnik.  leaving the pins with ease!
Ftacnik: 'White's bishops pair is very dangerous, so it was  important for the
defender to play accurately.'} (18... Qe6 {Ftacnik} 19. Rh3 Ng4 20. Qb5 $14)
19. Rh3 {'!' Ftacnik.} (19. b4 $6 {is again a suicide move:} Nxb4 20. Nxb4 Nc4
$1 $44) 19... Rfe8 (19... Nc4 $5 {
grabbing the |^ on the << was worthy of consideration:} 20. Rc3 (20. c3 Rfe8)
20... Nb4 21. Kb1 Qb5 22. Ne7+ Kh7 23. Bf1 $1 (23. Nxc8 Na3+ $19) 23... Rfe8
$17) 20. Rc3 Qa5 21. Ra3 (21. Re3 $2 Qxa2 $1 22. Bxe5 Na5 $1 23. Ra3 Nb3+ 24.
Rxb3 Qxb3 $17) 21... Qc5 22. Re3 (22. Rc3 $11) 22... Nd4 $2 {
Black has lost the thread.} (22... Re6 $1 {
was required with a complicated struggle.} 23. Bxe5 (23. Rc3 Qa5 $13) (23. Kb1
Kh8 $13) 23... Rxe5 24. Rxe5 Nxe5 25. c3 Nc6 $13) 23. Rxd4 $1 Qxd4 24. Rxe5 {
Now White gets the material advantage and an active ^^ in an opened position.}
(24. Bxe5 Qxh4 (24... Qg4 {Ftacnik} 25. Qxg4 fxg4 26. c3 $16) 25. Bf4 Rxe3 26.
Qxe3 Kh7 27. Kb1 $14) 24... Kh7 (24... Rxe5 25. Bxe5 Qg1+ 26. Qf1 $14 {
and the _|_ is clearly better for White because of his chances on the <<.}) (
24... Qg1+ 25. Qf1 $14) 25. Qd1 {'?!' Ftacnik.  Ftacnik: 'Not the best way to
realize solid advantage, Topalov hopes to eliminate even a traces of
counterplay. '} (25. Qe3 Qxe3+ (25... Qc4 26. Nc3 $14) 26. Rxe3 $14) (25. Rxe8
Rxe8 26. Qf1 $14) 25... Qf2 {'!' Ftacnik.  Black wants to complicate matters,
therefore avoids the exchange of queens.} (25... Qxd1+ 26. Kxd1 $14) 26. Bf3
Rxe5 27. Bxe5 f4 $2 {'!' Ftacnik.  Black finally wants to free his entombbed B,
but this was not the right place.} (27... Qxh4 28. Bf4 Rd8 (28... Qf2 29. Bxh5
$16) 29. Qd2 Re8 30. Kd1 $14) 28. Bc3 $1 Rd8 {'?' Ftacnik.} (28... Qxh4 29. Qd4
Rxc3 30. Nxc3 Qxg5 {gave at least a lot of pawns for Black...} 31. Nd5 $16 (31.
Qxa7 $16 {Ftacnik})) 29. b3 (29. Bxh5 $18 {was simpler}) 29... Kh8 30. Be1 {
leaving the long /^ can only be explained by the usual lack of time.} (30. Bd4
$18 Qxh4 (30... Qh2 {Ftacnik} 31. Bxg7+ Kxg7 32. Qd4+ Kh7 33. Nf6+ Kg7 34.
Nxh5+ Kf8 35. Qxd8#) 31. Bxg7+ Kxg7 32. Qd4+ Kh7 33. Nf6+ Kg7 34. Nxh5+) 30...
Qc5 31. Kb2 Bf5 (31... Bxc2 {Ftacnik} 32. Qxc2 Rxd5 33. Bxd5 Qxd5 34. Qc4 Qg2+
35. Ka3 $18) 32. c4 b5 33. Bb4 Qf2+ 34. Qe2 Qxe2+ (34... Qg1 35. Bxh5 $16 (35.
Bc3 {Ftacnik})) 35. Bxe2 bxc4 36. bxc4 {and the _|_ is simply winning again.}
Bg4 37. Bd3 f3 38. Kc3 Be6 39. Ne3 Bh3 40. Nd1 $138 (40. Nd1 Bf5 $1 41. Nf2
Bxd3 42. Nxd3 Re8 43. Bc5 a6 44. Bd4 Kh7 45. c5 $16 {Black lost on time in a
