1/2-1/2 Glek,I-Gurevich,M/Zwolle NED 2002/The Week in Chess 384 (56)}) 13...
Qxf6 14. Bb5 Rd8 15. Rhe1 Qb6 16. Bc4 Nc5 17. Qxe5 Be6 18. Bxe6 Nxe6 $132 {
1/2-1/2 Kasparov,G-Anand,V/Kopavogur 2000/EXT 2001 (28)}) 9. Qd2 cxd4 10. Nxd4
{This variation is not a new one for Topalov who won a very nice game against
Shirov one year ago.} h6 {Bareev decides that the castle is too risky, however
his king struggles to find a safe shelter.} (10... O-O 11. O-O-O h6 {
