correct 19...Nb6! would justify black's concept.'} (19... Nb6 $1 20. Nxe6+ (20.
Qb4 {Ftacnik} Qxb4 21. Rxb4 Rad8 $11) 20... fxe6 21. Qf4+ e5 22. Qe4 ({
No good is} 22. Qf7+ Kb8 23. Qxg7 Ka7 $17 {and black king escapes}) 22... Kb8
23. Rd7 Ra7 24. Rxg7 $36 {and despite of the fact that white's initiative is
extremly strong black may still defend.} Qxf2 25. Qxe5+ Ka8 26. Re7 Rc8 $15)
20. Qa5+ Qb6 21. Qe1 $1 Kb7 22. Qe2 {
Now the pawn on b5 becomes a target for the white pieces.} Ka7 (22... Nc7 23.
