15. f4 {would favour White.}) (14... cxd4 {Ftacnik} 15. cxd4 d5 16. exd6 Nxd6
17. Nf4 Qd7 18. c5 $14) 15. Nf4 (15. cxd5 {
would allow Black to take control over the light squares:} Bxd3 16. Qxd3 Qxd5
17. Nf4 Qc4 $15) 15... Nc7 (15... dxc4 {Ftacnik} 16. Bxh7+ $5 (16. Be4 {Ftacnik
} Qe7 17. d5 exd5 18. Nxd5 Qe6 19. exf6 Nxf6 20. Nxf6+ Qxf6 21. Qc2 h6 $15)
16... Kxh7 17. Nxe6 Qe7 18. Nxf8+ Qxf8 19. Rfe1 $13) 16. exf6 (16. cxd5 Bxd3
17. Qxd3 exd5 $11) 16... Qxf6 (16... dxc4 {Ftacnik} 17. fxg7 $5 (17. Be4 {
Ftacnik} Qxf6 18. Qc2 g6 19. dxc5 Nb3 20. Rcd1 Nxc5 21. Bxc5 bxc5 22. Ne2 $11)
17... Rxf4 18. Bxh7+ Kxh7 19. Bxf4 cxd4 20. Qe4+ Kxg7 21. Be5+ Kf8 22. Bxd4 $13
) 17. cxd5 Bxd3 18. Qxd3 cxd4 19. cxd4 Nxd5 20. Nxd5 exd5 $11 {After more or
less forced simplifications we reach about equal position.  Ftacnik: 'The
position is quite equal as black can organize his defence along the white
squares.'} 21. Bf2 Nc4 22. Rfe1 Rfe8 23. Bg3 Qg6 24. Qb3 {White has to avoid
the queen swap as the black pawns on the queenside with a knight support 
would become very dangerous.} h6 (24... a6 $5) 25. Qb5 Qf7 26. a4 Kh7 27. h3
Ra8 28. Be5 a6 29. Qb3 Qg6 30. f4 {behind his well-positioned bishop White
will now try to coordinate his pieces and create some pressure on the kingside.
Black has enough defensive resources, of course.} Rf8 31. Rc3 Ra7 32. Rg3 Qf5
33. Kh2 (33. Qf3 {Ftacnik} Rd7 34. Rc1 $11) 33... Raf7 34. Rg4 Rd7 35. Rc1 Rff7
36. Rc3 Rb7 37. Qd1 (37. Rcg3 {Ftacnik} Qe4 38. Rg6 Rfe7 $11) 37... Qe4 38.
Rgg3 Qf5 39. Rb3 b5 {'!' Ftacnik.  reminding White that the "b" pawn is also
not without importance. Ftacnik: 'Even the defender can show some teeth and
start his counterplay with passed b pawn.'} (39... Rfe7 $11 {Ftacnik}) 40. axb5
Rxb5 41. Rxb5 axb5 42. Rb3 Rb7 43. Qe1 Qe4 $15 44. Qxe4+ $2 {The endgame
unexpectedly is going to be very difficult for White. It was better to avoid
the exchange.} (44. Qf2 b4 $17) (44. Qc3 $142) (44. Qb4 {Ftacnik} Ne3 45. Rb2
Rb6 $1 $15) 44... dxe4 45. d5 g5 (45... b4 46. d6 (46. g4 $2 Nd2 47. Rb2 e3 $17
) 46... e3 (46... Nd2 $4 47. Rxb4) 47. Kg1 Kg6 48. Bd4 Nxd6 49. Bxe3 $11) (
45... e3 $5 {Ftacnik} 46. Kg1 g5 47. d6 Kg6 $15) 46. g4 (46. Kg3 Kg6 $17) 46...
e3 (46... Rf7 47. Rxb5 gxf4 48. Bd4 e3 49. Rb8 Re7 50. Kg2 Nd2 51. d6 Rd7 52.
Rf8 f3+ (52... e2 53. Bf2 f3+ 54. Rxf3 $11) 53. Rxf3 $11) 47. Kg3 e2 $2 {
missing the win.} (47... Re7 $1 48. Rb1 e2 49. Re1 (49. Kf2 gxf4 50. Bxf4 Nb2
$1 51. Bd2 Nd3+ 52. Kg3 e1=Q+ 53. Bxe1 Re3+ $19) 49... Nxe5 50. fxe5 Rxe5 51.
d6 Kg7 52. d7 Rd5 53. Rxe2 Rxd7 $19) 48. Kf2 Re7 49. Ke1 {'!' Ftacnik. 
Ftacnik: 'An elegant way to neutralize black's e2 pawn, Topalov still keeps a
pull in the endgame.'} (49. Rxb5 $2 {Ftacnik} e1=Q+ 50. Kxe1 gxf4 $19) 49...
Nxe5 50. d6 Re6 51. fxe5 Rxe5 52. Rb2 Re8 53. Rxb5 Kg7 54. Rb6 Re3 55. d7 Rd3
