1. e4 {Mueller,Karsten} c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 d6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Qxd4 Bd7 6. Bxc6
Bxc6 7. Nc3 Nf6 8. Bg5 e6 9. O-O-O Be7 10. Rhe1 O-O 11. Kb1 h6 12. Bh4 Qa5 13.
Qd2 Qh5 14. h3 g5 15. Bg3 e5 16. Qd3 Rad8 17. Nd2 d5 18. Bxe5 dxe4 19. Qe3 Nd5
20. Nxd5 Rxd5 21. Bd4 f5 22. f3 Rfd8 23. c3 Rxd4 24. cxd4 f4 25. Qb3+ Bd5 26.
Qc2 e3 27. Ne4 Qf7 28. Nc3 Be6 29. d5 Bf5 30. Ne4 Rxd5 31. Rxd5 Qxd5 32. Rd1
Qe6 33. Ka1 h5 34. a3 Kf7 35. Qa4 Bxe4 36. fxe4 Bf6 37. Qc2 Qc6 38. Kb1 g4 39.
hxg4 hxg4 40. Qd3 Qe6 41. g3 f3 42. Qxe3 Be5 43. Qg5 Bxg3 44. Qh5+ Kg7 45. Qg5+
Kf7 46. Qh5+ Kg7 47. Ka1 f2 48. Qg5+ Kf7 49. Qh5+ Kg7 50. Rh1 $6 {
Too risky. Draw by perpetual was the best option for White.} Be5 $1 51. Qh7+
Kf8 52. Qxb7 g3 53. Rc1 {'?' Mueller,Karsten.} (53. Rd1 $142 {Mueller,Karsten})
53... Qc4 $3 {The winning move.} 54. Qa8+ (54. Rxc4 {The queen is invulnerable:
} f1=Q+ 55. Ka2 Qxc4+ {, and Black wins.}) 54... Ke7 55. Qxa7+ Bc7 $1 (55...
Bc7 $1 {The shortest way to the victory. After} 56. Qxc7+ (56. Rxc4 f1=Q+ 57.
Ka2 Qxc4+) 56... Qxc7 57. Rxc7+ Kd6 58. Rc1 (58. Rf7 g2 59. Rxf2 g1=Q+) 58...
g2 {Black's pawns are unstoppable.}) 0-1

