1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. c4 e6 6. Nc3 Be7 7. g3 dxc4 {Black want
s to take control over the vital blockading square >< d5 even at an expence of
a tempo.} (7... Nh6 8. Bg5 $5 {
This is a critical idea, White wants to exchange his bad B for his counterpart.
} (8. Bxh6 $5) 8... dxc4 (8... Bxg5 9. hxg5 Qxg5 10. Rxh5 Qe7 11. cxd5 (11. g4
Bg6 (11... Bxg4 $2 12. Rxh6 $1 $18) 12. Rh3 O-O) 11... exd5 $13 {
Minasian-Savchenko, Elista ol (Men) 1998 CBM 66 ext} (11... exd5 12. f4 Bg6 (
12... O-O $2 {runs into a devastating -> on the >> after} 13. Be2 Qd7 14. Rh4
$16 {/\ g4}) 13. Rh3 Nd7 14. Bd3 (14. g4 {can be met by the brave} O-O-O $1 (
14... f5 15. g5 Nf7 16. Rxh8+ Nxh8 17. Qe2 $1 Nf8 18. O-O-O Ne6 (18... O-O-O
19. Bh3 Ne6 20. Qe3 Nf7 21. Nge2 $16) 19. Qf3 O-O-O (19... Qf7 {/\ Bh5} 20. Be2
) 20. Nge2 $14 {with space advantage and a bad black B.}) 15. f5 Nxf5 $1 16.
gxf5 Bxf5 17. Rxh8 Rxh8 18. Nf3 Bg4 $44 {/\ f6}) 14... O-O-O $5 {
- Minasian-Savchenko, Elista 1998 CBM 66} (14... Bxd3 15. Qxd3 Nf6 $5 (15...
O-O-O 16. O-O-O Qe6) 16. O-O-O Nfg4 17. Rd2 O-O-O 18. Nf3 Qd7 {
with good chances for a successful blockade on the important /^ h3-c8.})) (
11... Bg4 $4 12. Rxh6 $1 $18 {is similar to the previous note.}) (11... cxd5
12. Bb5+ ({The tempting} 12. Nb5 $6 {allows Black to equalize in the _|_ after}
Qb4+ 13. Qd2 Qxd2+ 14. Kxd2 Nc6 15. Nd6+ Ke7 $11) 12... Nc6 13. f3 O-O 14. Nge2
$36)) 9. Bxe7 (9. Bxc4 Bxg5 10. hxg5 Qxg5 11. Rxh5 Qg6 12. Be2 Nd7 13. Nh3 $14)
9... Qxe7 10. Qxh5 {It is hard to get back the c4 P after that...} (10. Bxc4 {
looks more natural.} Nd7 $13) 10... Qb4 $5 (10... Na6 11. a3 O-O-O 12. Qg5 f6
$13) 11. Qe2 (11. O-O-O $6 {White is pushing too hard, this idea of the
exchange sacrifice cannot be correct.} Bg4 12. Qg5 Bxd1 13. Qxg7 Qf8 (13... Rg8
14. Qxh6 Bg4 15. Qd2 $14) 14. Qxf8+ Kxf8 15. Nxd1 c5 $1 $15 {Black has to open
up the position for his rooks, Ponomariov-Bareev, Wijk aan Zee 2003 CBM 93} (
15... b5 16. Bg2 Nf5 (16... a5 17. Ne3 $14) 17. Ne2 $44 {
and the rooks have no open lines.})) 11... Nd7 (11... Bd3 12. Qd2 Bxf1 13. Kxf1
Nf5 (13... c5 14. a3 Qb6 15. dxc5 Qxc5 $11 {Ftacnik}) 14. Nf3) 12. Qd2 (12.
O-O-O Bd3) 12... O-O-O 13. Ne4 Qxd2+ 14. Nxd2 Nb6 15. Ngf3 Bg4 $13) (7... Nd7
8. cxd5 cxd5 (8... exd5 {Now Black has to blockade both >< f5 and >< e6!} 9.
Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 {Now it is not so easy for Black to blockade the >>.} Nf8 (
10... Nh6 11. Nge2 Nf8 12. Nf4 g6 13. e6 $1 {
This breakthrough is White's main threat.} Qd6 14. exf7+ Nxf7 15. b4 Bf6 16. b5
c5 17. dxc5 Qxc5 18. Bd2 Ne5 19. Qxd5 Qxd5 20. Ncxd5 Nf3+ 21. Ke2 Nxd2 22.
Nxf6+ Kf7 23. N6d5 Ne4 24. Rhc1 $18 {
