Kosanovic-Tadic, Novi Sad op 1989}) 9. Bd3 $14) 8. Bxc4 Nd7 9. Be2 {
attacking >< h5 and leaving the vulnerable c4 square.} (9. Nf3 Nb6 10. Bd3 Bxd3
11. Qxd3 Nh6 $13 {
The exchange of the light-squared B is strategically important for Black.})
9... c5 {Surprisingly Black opens up the position, which usually favours for
the better developed party.} (9... Qb6 10. Nf3 O-O-O 11. O-O f6 $132) (9... Nb6
10. Bxh5 $16) 10. Nf3 (10. Be3 Qb6 11. Bb5 O-O-O $132) 10... Nh6 11. d5 exd5
12. Bxh6 {
