1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. d4 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. Be3 Na6 8. O-O
Ng4 9. Bg5 Qe8 10. dxe5 dxe5 11. Nd2 f6 {The best choice.} ({After} 11... Nf6
12. Nd5 {white keeps a minimal advantage.}) 12. Bh4 h5 13. h3 (13. a3 Be6 14.
h3 Nh6 15. b4 Rd8 16. Bg3 Nb8 17. Qc2 Nc6 18. Nb3 f5 19. Nd5 Qf7 $13 {
1/2-1/2 Van Wely,L-Comas Fabrego,L/Mondariz 2000/CBM 79 (91)}) 13... Nh6 14.
Re1 $6 {I do not like this strange theoretical continuation,as in my opinion
it's simply waste of time.} (14. a3 $142 Be6 15. b4 {with complicated play})
14... c6 15. a3 Be6 16. b4 Rd8 $1 $146 {Slightly improving on black's previous
play.Perhaps already white should fight for the equality.} (16... Nc7 17. c5
Qf7 18. Bg3 Rad8 19. Qc2 f5 20. Bh4 Bf6 21. Bxf6 Qxf6 22. Nc4 Nf7 {and black ha
s easily solved his opening problems .1/2-1/2 Iskusnyh,S-Chuprov,D/Smolensk
2000/CBM 77 (85)}) 17. Qc2 (17. c5 $142 Nc7 (17... g5 18. Bg3 g4 19. h4 $1 f5
$140 20. exf5 Nxf5 21. Bxa6 $1 Nxg3 (21... bxa6 22. Bxe5 $16) 22. fxg3 bxa6 23.
Nce4 $14) 18. Qc2 g5 19. Bg3 h4 (19... Qg6 20. Nf3) (19... Qf7 $5) 20. Bh2 g4
21. hxg4 Nxg4 22. Nf3 Qh5 23. Rad1 h3 24. Bg3 $1 hxg2 25. Kxg2 Qh3+ $3 26. Kxh3
(26. Kg1 $2 Ne3 $1 $19) 26... Ne3+ 27. Kh2 Nxc2 28. Rxd8 Rxd8 29. Rc1 Nd4 (
29... Nxa3 30. Ra1) 30. Nxd4 Rxd4 31. Rd1 {and white should hold the endgame})
17... g5 18. Bg3 Qg6 ({Even stronger was immediate} 18... h4 19. Bh2 g4 $1 20.
hxg4 Nxg4 21. Nf3 Qh5 22. Rad1 h3 23. Bg3 $140 hxg2 24. Kxg2 Qh3+ $3 25. Kxh3
Ne3+ 26. Kh2 Nxc2 $17) 19. c5 $2 {Ignoring black's plans on the kingside.} (19.
Nf3 $142 $1 Qf7 (19... g4 $140 20. hxg4 hxg4 21. Nh4 Qf7 22. Nd1 $13) 20. Nd1
$1 $11) 19... h4 20. Bh2 g4 $1 {
By this breakthrough black obtains a very dangerous initiative.} 21. hxg4 Nxg4
22. Bxg4 $2 {probably missing white's 23move} (22. Rad1 h3 23. Bg3 Ne3 $1 $19)
(22. Bc4 $142 Nc7 23. Rad1 h3 24. Bg3 Bh6 25. Qa2 Bxd2 26. Bxe6+ Nxe6 27. Rxd2
Rxd2 28. Qxd2 Nd4 $17) 22... Bxg4 23. f3 (23. Kh1 Bh6 24. Nc4 h3 $1 25. f3 Bxf3
26. gxf3 Rd2 $1 27. Rg1 Qg2+ $19) ({Doesn't help} 23. Nc4 h3 $1 (23... Bf3 $143
24. Bg3 hxg3 25. gxf3 $13) 24. Bg3 hxg2 25. Kxg2 Qh5 26. Re3 $8 Bh3+ 27. Kg1 f5
$1 28. exf5 Bh6 29. Rd3 (29. Rxe5 Qf3 30. Qe4 Qxc3 $19) 29... Bxf5 30. Qd1 Bg4
{and black wins}) 23... Bh6 $1 {
nice tactical blow,afer which white loses material.} 24. Rad1 Bxd2 25. Rxd2
Bxf3 $17 26. Re3 Bg4 27. Red3 ({Maybe more stubborn was:} 27. Rd6 $142 Rxd6 (
27... Nc7 $2 28. Bxe5) 28. cxd6 Nb8 {still with clear advantage}) 27... Rxd3
28. Rxd3 Nc7 29. Qf2 Qg5 30. Qd2 Ne6 31. Qxg5+ Nxg5 32. b5 $6 (32. Kf2 Kf7 33.
Ke3 Ke7 $17 {and black should easily convert his extra pawn}) 32... cxb5 33.
Nxb5 Nxe4 34. Nxa7 Nxc5 $19 {
The rest doesn't require any commets,black is completely winning.} 35. Rc3 Ne4
36. Rc4 Bf5 37. Kh1 Rd8 38. Bg1 Rd1 39. Kh2 Rd2 40. Nc8 Kf8 41. Be3 (41. Kh1 h3
42. gxh3 Ng3#) 41... Re2 42. Bc5+ Kf7 43. Nd6+ Nxd6 44. Bxd6 h3 0-1

