1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 6. Ndb5 d6 7. Bg5 a6 8.
Na3 b5 9. Bxf6 gxf6 10. Nd5 f5 11. Bd3 Be6 12. c3 Bg7 13. Qh5 O-O 14. O-O f4
15. Rad1 (15. Rfd1) (15. Nc2) 15... Ra7 $5 {Controlling the seventh rank is
important for two main reasons:   1.The rook can be quicker transferred to the
kingside (usually to f7, but sometimes to g7 as well).  2.Often after the
opening of the b1-h7 diagonal the pawn on h7 needs protection. For instance
now Black is ready for f7-f5, which wasn't very good right away.} (15... f5 16.
exf5 (16. Bc2 Bxd5 $5 17. Rxd5 Ne7 18. Rd2 d5 19. exd5 Qd6 $44) 16... Bxd5 17.
f6 Rxf6 18. Bxh7+ Kf8 19. Rxd5 Ne7 20. Qf3 (20. Be4 $5) 20... Nxd5 21. Qxd5 $44
) (15... Kh8 {was considered good enough for Black, but Svidler might have had
an improvement in mind over one of Anand's games.} 16. g3 Rg8 17. Kh1 Bf8 18.
Be2 Rg5 19. Qf3 f5 20. gxf4 exf4 21. Nxf4 Bxa2 22. c4 (22. exf5 Rxf5 23. Qe4
Rf7 24. Bh5 Rf6 25. c4 Ne5 26. c5 $2 Rc8 $1 $132 {
0-1 Anand,V-Topalov,V/Monte Carlo 2001 (30)}) 22... fxe4 (22... Qf6 23. exf5
Rc8 24. Qc3 Qxc3 25. bxc3 Ne5 26. Ne6 Rxf5 27. Nxf8 Rfxf8 28. Rxd6 {
1/2-1/2 Maletin,P-Yudin,S/Essentuki 2003 (29)}) 23. Qxe4 Qe8 24. Bf3 Qxe4 25.
Bxe4 Rc8 26. Ne6 Re5 27. Bxc6 Rxc6 28. Nxf8 b4 29. Nc2 Bxc4 $11 {was approximat
ely equal in Anand,V-Hernandez,G/Merida 2001, although White succeeded to win
later on.}) 16. Nc2 ({After} 16. g3 {Black can try} f5 17. Bb1 (17. exf5 $2 {
This doesn't work now because the rook protects pawn h7:} Bxd5 18. f6 Bxf6) (
17. Bc2 $5) 17... Bxd5 18. Rxd5 fxg3 19. fxg3 f4 $13 20. gxf4 $6 exf4 {
and Black is fine - open diagonal for the bishop and a good square e5. Once
again the rook from a7 plays an important role after 21.e5? Bxe5 the pawn on
h7 is protected.}) 16... Kh8 17. Ncb4 $146 (17. g3 Rg8 18. Rfe1 $6 (18. Kh1
$142 Bf8 19. Be2) 18... Bf8 19. Qe2 Qh4 $40 {
0-1 Jedlicka,L-Cichy,M/Svetla 1994 (41)}) 17... Nxb4 18. Nxb4 Qd7 (18... Qc8 $5
{keeping the seventh rank free for an eventual transfer of the rook from a7
deserved attention.}) 19. Be2 (19. h3 Rg8 20. Nd5 f5 $13) 19... f5 20. exf5
Rxf5 21. Qh4 (21. Qf3 d5 $36 22. Nxd5 $2 e4 $17) 21... Bf6 22. Qh6 Bg7 23. Qh4
Bf6 24. Qh6 Bg7 1/2-1/2

