1. Nf3 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. c4 g6 4. Nc3 Bg7 5. e4 O-O 6. Be2 Bg4 7. Be3 Nfd7 8. Rc1
c5 9. d5 b5 10. cxb5 a6 11. bxa6 ({Deserve attention} 11. a4 axb5 12. axb5 Nb6
13. O-O Bxf3 14. gxf3 N8d7 15. f4 Ra5 16. Kh1 $14 {
1-0 Izoria,Z-Romero Holmes,A/France 2003/EXT 2004 (38)}) 11... Nxa6 12. O-O Qa5
13. Nd2 Bxe2 14. Qxe2 Rfb8 $1 $146 {This standard move in fact appears to be a
serious improvement,Black builds up the pressure on queenside and he can
comfortably to defend his e7-pawn with Kf8.} (14... Nc7 15. Bg5 $1 Rfe8 16. f4
e6 17. dxe6 Nxe6 18. Nc4 Qa6 19. Nd5 Qxa2 20. Be7 Nd4 21. Qd3 $16 {
1-0 Graf,A-Romero Holmes,A/Istanbul 2003/CBM 96 (30)}) 15. Nc4 Qb4 16. a3 {
A questionable choice,allowing Black to get a very comfortable square for his
queen.} ({Strangely enough, but i didn't manage to find a decent way for White
to fight for advantage.Black keeps good counterplay in all lines.} 16. Bd2 Ne5
(16... Nb6 17. Nd1 Qa4 $1 {also not bad} (17... Qb5 $143 18. b3 $1 $14)) 17.
Nd1 (17. Nxe5 Bxe5 18. b3 Qa3 $44) 17... Qa4 $1 (17... Qb5 18. b3 $1) 18. Bg5
Nxc4 19. Rxc4 Qxa2 20. Bxe7 Rb6 $44) (16. f4 Nb6 17. Nxb6 Rxb6) (16. Rc2 Ne5
17. Nd2 Qb7 18. a3 Nc7 $132) 16... Qb3 17. Rc2 (17. f4 {was critical} {
but after forced} Nc7 (17... Nb6 $2 18. Na5) 18. e5 Nb6 (18... Nb5 $2 19. Ne4
$16) 19. exd6 exd6 20. Nxd6 Nbxd5 21. Bxc5 Qxb2 22. Rc2 Nxc3 23. Rxb2 Nxe2+ 24.
Rxe2 Bf8 $1 $11 {White is unable to hold his extra pawn}) 17... Nc7 18. Bg5 Kf8
$1 (18... Nb6 $143 19. Ne3 $1 (19. Nxb6 Rxb6 20. Bxe7 f6 21. e5 $8 fxe5 22. Ne4
Nb5 $44) 19... Nc8 20. Ng4 $1 {with good attacking prospects}) 19. f4 {
White has to hurry up in order not to get into the worse position.} h6 20. Bh4
Nb6 {Just in time!} 21. Nxb6 (21. Ne3 Na4 $1 22. Nxa4 Rxa4 {and Black is fine}
23. Nc4 $140 Nb5 24. Bf2 Nc3 $1) 21... Rxb6 22. e5 (22. Rf3 Nb5 23. Nxb5 Qxb5
24. e5 Qxe2 25. Rxe2 Rab8 $44) 22... Nxd5 23. Nxd5 Qxd5 24. Rd2 Qe6 25. Qf3
Rab8 26. Re1 dxe5 ({After} 26... dxe5 27. fxe5 c4 $1 {
Black even slightly better,due to White's weak pawns.}) 1/2-1/2

