1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d5 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5 c5 (6... h6 $5 {
It's main line.See comments to Popov,V-Loginov,V/St.Petersburg,2003/CBM 95(1-0)
(Golod,V)(25)}) 7. a3 $5 {Rare move.Besides White has two alternatives:} (7.
Nf3 {
You can see my annotations to game: Zhu Chen-Short,N/Dubai,2002/CBM 89(0-1)(25)
}) ({and} 7. dxc5 $5 {You can see comments to Alterman,B-Kortschnoj,V/
Groningen,1993/CBM 39(1/2-1/2)(Chekhov,V)(40)}) 7... Bxc3+ ({
Also twice were checked up in previous games:} 7... cxd4) 8. Qxc3 $5 ({On:} 8.
bxc3 {you can find five games in Mega DataBase 2004.}) 8... cxd4 $5 $146 {
This continuation is the next attempt to bring in a "new word " in theory of
this variation.} ({
The games which have reached this position were continued as follows:} 8... c4
$5 {In this position I have found three games in Mega DataBase 2004.For an
example we shall consider latest of them:} 9. g3 Be6 10. Nh3 $5 Nbd7 11. Nf4
Qb6 12. Bg2 O-O 13. O-O h6 14. Bxf6 Nxf6 15. e3 Rad8 $11 {
Arlandi,E-Sokolov,A/Geneve,2001(1/2-1/2)(30)}) 9. Qxd4 ({It was very badly:} 9.
Bxf6 $2 {because of:} dxc3 10. Bxd8 $140 cxb2 11. Rb1 Kxd8 12. Rxb2 Kc7 {
=/+/-/+}) 9... Nc6 10. Qf4 ({Again impossibly:} 10. Bxf6 $4 {in view of:} Nxd4
11. Bxd8 Nc2+ 12. Kd1 Nxa1 $19) 10... d4 $1 {The correct decision! There is no
sense to spend a tempo for the following move:} (10... h6 $143 11. Bxf6 Qxf6
12. Qxf6 gxf6 13. Rd1 $14) 11. Bxf6 {
Differently, Black receive a excellent pieces game:} (11. Nf3 Qa5+ 12. Qd2 (12.
Nd2 $6 Nd5 13. Qe4+ Be6 $15) 12... Qf5 13. Bxf6 (13. Qd3 $143 Ne4 14. Bh4 Nc5
$36) 13... Qxf6 14. e3 (14. Rd1 $2 Bg4 $1 $15 15. Nxd4 $140 $4 O-O-O $19) 14...
dxe3 15. Qxe3+ Kf8 16. Be2 Qxb2 17. O-O $44) 11... gxf6 $6 {
A strange decision. From my point of view, it was a much better:} (11... Qxf6
$5 12. Qxf6 gxf6 13. g3 (13. Rd1 $5 Bf5 14. Nf3 O-O-O $11) (13. e3 Bf5 $5 $11)
13... Bf5 14. Bg2 O-O-O 15. Nf3 (15. Kd2 $143 Na5 16. Rc1+ Kb8 $36) 15... Rhe8
$11) 12. Nf3 $6 ({Can be recommended:} 12. b4 $5 {(against Qa5+)} Be6 13. Nf3 {
with obvious advantage of White.}) 12... Qa5+ $1 13. Qd2 {
White had no other worthy alternative:} (13. b4 $4 Nxb4) (13. Nd2 Qe5 $11)
13... Qxd2+ 14. Kxd2 {
+/=/= After queens was exchanged White can hope only for the minimal advantage.
} (14. Nxd2 $143 Be6 15. g3 Bd5 16. Rg1 Ke7 17. Bg2 Bxg2 18. Rxg2 Rac8 $11)
14... Bf5 ({Pretty dubiously:} 14... Bg4 $6 15. g3 (15. h3 $5) 15... Bxf3 16.
exf3 O-O-O 17. Rc1 $14) 15. b4 {
Probably it was possible to continue the game without this move:} (15. Rc1 $5
Na5 (15... Be4 16. e3 $14) 16. Nxd4 $140 Rd8 17. e3 $1 (17. Ke1 $143 Rxd4 $140
18. Rc5 Nb3 19. Rxf5 Rd2 $132) (17. Ke3 $2 Rxd4 $1 18. Kxd4 Nb3+ 19. Kc3 Nxc1
