$146 {Topalov comes up with a very important novelty in a popular variation.
With exchange sacrifice black wants to grab the initiative.} (14... Nc4 15.
Bxc4 Rxc4 (15... Bxc4 16. Nd5 Bxd5 17. Rxd5 f5 18. gxf6 Nxf6 19. Rdd1 Rf7 20.
Qe2 Qc7 21. Rd3 Qc4 22. Qd1 {1/2-1/2 Hracek,Z-Ftacnik,L/Germany 2003/ (22)})
16. Nd5 Bxd5 17. Rxd5 f5 18. gxf6 Rxf6 19. Qe2 Rc8 20. Kb1 Qd7 21. Rdd1 Qh3 22.
Nd2 {Shirov,A-Sutovsky,E/Reykjavik 2003/1-0 (35)}) 15. Bxb6 (15. bxc3 Na4 16.
Rd3 Qc7 $44) 15... Bxg5+ 16. Kb1 (16. Nd2 Bh4 17. Rg3 Bxg3 18. hxg3 Rc7 $15)
16... Bh4 $1 17. Rg3 (17. Bxd8 Bxf2 18. Rg2 Rxf3 19. Be2 Nf4 20. Bxf3 Nxg2 21.
Be7 (21. Bxg2 Rxd8 $19) 21... Re8 22. Bxd6 Ne3 23. Rd2 Bg1 24. h4 (24. Bxe5 $2
Nc4 $19) 24... Nc4 $19) 17... Bxg3 18. hxg3 Rc7 19. Nc5 (19. Bxc7 Qxc7 $17)
19... Qe7 (19... Bc8 20. Qh2 Nf6 21. Qd2 Ne8 22. Nd3 Qf6 23. Bxc7 Nxc7 24. f4
b5 $15) 20. Nxe6 fxe6 21. Bxc7 Qxc7 22. Bh3 {White can not be satisfied with
the outcome of the opening. He can claim obly very meagre compensation for the
pawn.} Re8 (22... Kf7 23. f4 exf4 24. gxf4 Nf6 25. Bg2 e5 $15) 23. Rd3 Nf6 24.
Qa7 (24. Qd2 d5 $17) 24... Kf7 (24... d5 25. Rb3 Re7 26. a3 $15) 25. Rc3 Qd7
26. Qb6 Re7 (26... Rc8 $2 27. Rxc8 Qxc8 28. Qxd6 $14) 27. Rd3 d5 (27... Ne8 28.
Qb3 $13) 28. exd5 Nxd5 29. Qc5 Qb5 (29... Qc6 30. Qxc6 bxc6 31. Bf1 $11) 30.
Qd6 (30. Qxb5 axb5 31. Bf1 b4 32. Rd2 h5 $15) 30... Nb4 ({
Much more compact was to idea to support the king with the other jump} 30...
Nf6 $5 31. Bf1 Rd7 32. Qb8 e4 $1 33. fxe4 Qb4 34. Rxd7+ Nxd7 35. Qf4+ Nf6 $17)
31. Rd2 Qc4 32. b3 Qc3 33. f4 (33. Bg4 Nc6 34. Rh2 Qe1+ 35. Kb2 Qxg3 $15) 33...
Qxg3 $2 {Black is getting nervous, this move throws out the advantage.} (33...
e4 $1 34. Re2 a5 35. Qe5 Qxe5 36. fxe5 Rc7 37. Bg2 Nd5 38. Kb2 Nc3 39. Re1 Kg6
40. Bxe4+ Nxe4 41. Rxe4 Kf5 $17) 34. Qxb4 Qxh3 35. fxe5 Qe3 36. Qd6 h5 $6 (
36... b5 37. Rd1 Qe2 38. Rd4 $11) 37. Rd1 Qf2 (37... Qe2 38. Rg1 Qf2 39. Qd1
Kg8 40. Rh1 g6 $11) 38. Qd3 Qg2 39. Rf1+ Kg8 $2 {
A losing retreat, Topalov did not manage to adjust his ambitions to survival.}
(39... Ke8 $5 40. Qc4 Qc6 41. Qh4 Rd7 42. Qxh5+ Kd8 43. Rf4 $14) 40. Qd8+ Kh7
41. Rf8 Qg1+ 42. Kb2 Qg5 (42... Qc5 43. Rh8+ Kg6 44. Qd3+ Kg5 45. Qg3+ Kf5 46.
Rxh5+ $18) 43. Qd3+ $1 {Very fine move, that decides the game. Black is forced
to open up access to his king.} g6 (43... Qg6 44. Rh8+ $18) 44. Qd6 Kg7 45. Qb8
Qh6 46. Qd8 $1 1-0

