1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f3 e6 7. Be3 b5 8. g4
Nfd7 9. Qd2 Nb6 10. a4 bxa4 11. Nxa4 Nxa4 12. Rxa4 Be7 13. g5 $146 {Topalov doe
sn't move his bishop from f1, since he hopes to win a6 pawn or use the piece
on c8-h3 diagonal.} (13. Be2 O-O 14. O-O Bb7 15. Rfa1 Nd7 16. Nb3 Rb8 17. Ba7
Rc8 18. Na5 Ba8 19. Bxa6 Ne5 20. Be2 f5 21. gxf5 exf5 22. Nc4 Qe8 {
1/2-1/2 Anand,V-Kasparov,G/Kopavogur 2000/ (41)}) 13... O-O 14. h4 Bd7 $5 ({
It seems more natural to develop the bishop to b7, but the pawn e6 could have
become vulnerable.} 14... Bb7 15. h5 Nd7 16. g6 Nc5 17. Rb4 $5 a5 18. Rxb7 $1
Nxb7 19. gxf7+ $44) 15. Ra1 Nc6 16. Rxa6 Qc7 $6 {
It seems, that this move is inferior to the direct} (16... Rxa6 17. Bxa6 Qa8
18. Nxc6 Bxc6 19. Be2 d5 $5 20. exd5 Bxd5 21. Kf2 (21. O-O $6 Qb8) 21... Rd8
22. Qc1 Qb7 $44 {Anand was not sure, if the compensation would be sufficient.})
17. Kf2 Nxd4 18. Bxd4 e5 (18... Rxa6 19. Bxa6 Ra8 20. Bd3 e5 21. Be3 Be6 22. h5
$14) 19. Be3 Rxa6 20. Bxa6 f5 21. gxf6 Bxf6 (21... gxf6 $6 22. Rg1+ Kf7 23. Ke1
$16) 22. Qd5+ Kh8 23. Bc4 (23. Be2 $5 Qxc2 24. Qxd6 Rd8 25. Qb4 Be6 {
when black pieces are very active.}) 23... Be8 24. Be2 Bf7 25. Qd2 Bh5 (25...
Qc6 $5 26. c4 Bxc4 $1 27. Qc3 (27. Rc1 Bxh4+ 28. Kg2 d5 $1 $17) 27... d5 28.
exd5 Bxd5 29. Qxc6 Bxc6 30. b4 $14) 26. b3 Qe7 27. Kg2 Qf7 (27... Bxh4 $4 28.
Rxh4 $1 Qxh4 29. Bg5 $18) 28. Rh3 (28. Qxd6 Be7 29. Qd1 Qg6+ 30. Kh3 (30. Kf2
$6 Qxe4) 30... Qf6 31. Bg5 Qe6+ 32. Kh2 h6 33. Be3 Qf6 $132) 28... Be7 29. b4 {
It will not be easy to get far with the b pawn, since it can not easily be
supported by white pieces.} h6 30. b5 (30. c4 Qf6 31. b5 Bf7 32. Rg3 $14) 30...
Qg6+ 31. Kh2 Qe6 32. Qd3 (32. b6 Be8 33. Qd5 $14) 32... Be8 $1 33. Qb3 Qc8 (
33... Qxb3 $5 34. cxb3 Bd7 35. Rg3 Bxh4 36. Rg1 Rb8 37. Ba7 Rb7 38. b6 Bf2 39.
Ba6 Bxg1+ 40. Kxg1 Bc6 41. Bxb7 Bxb7 42. Bb8 d5 43. exd5 Bxd5 44. Kf2 e4 $11)
34. b6 Bf7 35. Qb1 $2 (35. Qb2 $1) 35... Qc3 $2 {
Paying back with the faulty move himself, Anand misses ingenious shot.} (35...
Be6 $1 36. b7 Qc3 $3 37. Ba7 (37. b8=Q Qxe3 $1 $15) 37... Qd2 38. Qd1 Qb4 $11)
36. Bd3 $1 Rb8 (36... d5 37. b7 Bd6 38. Qb6 Qa3 39. Bc1 Qc5 40. Qxc5 Bxc5 41.
exd5 Rb8 42. c4 Rxb7 43. f4 $16) 37. Qg1 $1 {Topalov has managed to
consolidate his position and now is ready to attack on the kingside.} Bc4 $6
38. Qg6 $1 Bxd3 39. Rg3 $1 Bf6 (39... Qxc2+ 40. Rg2 Qxg2+ 41. Kxg2 $18) 40.
cxd3 Rxb6 {Desperation, but the threat of 41.Bxh6 was otherwise unstoppable.} (
40... Qe1 41. Bxh6 Qf2+ 42. Kh3 Qf1+ 43. Kg4 Qf2 44. Bg5 Rf8 45. Kh3 Bxg5 46.
Qxg5 $18) 41. Bxb6 Qb2+ 42. Rg2 Qxb6 43. Rc2 Bd8 (43... Qd8 44. Qf5 $18) 44. h5
1-0

