1. Nf3 c5 2. c4 g6 3. e4 Bg7 4. d4 d6 5. d5 (5. Nc3 {/\} Bg4 (5... Nf6 6. Be2 {
-E91}) 6. d5 $14 (6. dxc5 dxc5 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. Be3 Bxc3+ (8... Bxf3 9. gxf3
Bd4 10. O-O-O e5 11. Nb5 Kd7 12. f4 $36) 9. bxc3 b6 10. Ne5 Be6 11. O-O-O+ Ke8
12. Bd3 f6 13. Nf3 Nc6 14. e5 Nxe5 15. Nxe5 fxe5 16. Rhe1 Nf6 17. Bg5 Kf7 18.
Rxe5 Rhd8 19. h3 Rd6 20. Rde1 {Browne,W-Forintos,G/Wijk aan Zee/1974/} Rxd3 21.
Rxe6 Rd7 $14 {/~~})) 5... e6 6. Nc3 exd5 7. exd5 {Timman after a long
tournament, which has not gone well for him, strives for simpler play.} (7.
cxd5 $142 {
is the only principled continuation, transposing into Benoni positions.} Nf6 {
-A70} (7... Bg4 {-A43})) 7... Bg4 8. Be2 Ne7 $1 $13 {One of the points of
delaying the development of the Ng8. Now Black's N gets a chance to get to f5
and potentially d4. After} (8... Nf6 9. O-O O-O 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Bxf3 $14 {
-E91 White transposes into a pleasant King's Indian line, the ^^ gives him a
long-lasting pull.}) 9. O-O (9. Qb3 b6 (9... Nd7 $2 10. Qxb7 O-O 11. O-O Nf5
12. Bg5 Qb8 13. Qxd7 Qxb2 14. Nd2 Bxc3 15. Bxg4 Bxd2 16. Bxd2 Qxd2 17. Bxf5
gxf5 18. Qxd6 $18 {Finegold,B-Ivanov,A/New York/1992/}) 10. Qa4+ (10. O-O O-O {
-9.0-0}) (10. Ne4 O-O {/\} 11. Bg5 f5 $1 $32 {|^}) 10... Nd7 11. O-O O-O 12. h3
Bxf3 13. Bxf3 Ne5 $13 (13... Nf5 14. Bg4 Bxc3 $5 15. bxc3 Ne5 16. Bxf5 gxf5 $13
)) 9... O-O (9... Nd7 10. Nb5 (10. Ne4 Nf5 11. h3 Bxf3 12. Bxf3 O-O 13. Bg4 Nd4
$1 $13 {/\} 14. Nxd6 $2 f5 15. Bf3 Ne5 $17) 10... Nb6 11. Bf4 Nbc8 12. Qd2 O-O
13. a4 (13. Bh6) 13... Nf5 14. Ra3 a6 15. Nc3 Nb6 16. Qd3 Re8 17. h3 Bxf3 18.
Bxf3 Nd7 (18... Nd4 $142 $1 $15) 19. Bg4 Ne5 20. Bxe5 Rxe5 21. Bxf5 gxf5 (21...
Rxf5 22. f4 {><Rf5}) 22. Ne2 Qf6 23. f4 Re4 24. Ng3 Qd4+ 25. Qxd4 Bxd4+ 26. Kh2
Ree8 27. Nxf5 Rad8 28. Rb3 {Ward,C-Ivanov,A/London/1989/}) 10. Qb3 $146 {
This Q sortie achieves no immediate and concrete advantage and seems rather
artificial.} (10. Bf4 Nf5 (10... Bxf3 11. Bxf3 Nf5 12. Ne4 $14) 11. Ng5 $5 Bxe2
12. Qxe2 h6 (12... Nd7 $142 $132) 13. Nge4 g5 14. Qg4 $1 Ne7 15. Bxd6 f5 16.
Qh3 fxe4 17. Nxe4 $44 {Elschner,A-Zielinska,M/Bundesliga-W/2001/}) (10. Re1 Nf5
11. Bg5 Qb6 12. Rb1 h6 13. Bd2 Nd7 14. Qa4 Qd8 15. Qd1 Re8 16. b3 {
Szeberenyi,A-Fogarasi,T/Budapest/2004/} Bxf3 17. Bxf3 Nd4 $11) 10... b6 11. Ng5
(11. h3 Bxf3 12. Bxf3 Nf5 13. Ne2 $11) 11... Bxe2 12. Nxe2 Nd7 13. Qh3 {
Consistent with White's 10-th move, but the Q will find nothing to do here,
more to the pointseems} (13. Ne4 $11) 13... Nf6 14. Bd2 $6 {
Now Black wins tempi and starts fighting for the initiative.} (14. Nc3 $142 h6
(14... Re8 15. Nce4 Nexd5 16. cxd5 Nxe4 17. Qxh7+ Kf8 18. Nxe4 Rxe4 19. Bh6
Bxh6 20. Rae1 $1 $36) 15. Nge4 $11) 14... h6 15. Nf3 g5 $1 16. Ne1 $8 (16. g4
Qd7 $17) 16... Ne4 (16... b5 17. cxb5 Nexd5 (17... Qd7 $5) 18. Nc3 $13) (16...
Re8 17. Qd3 {/\Bc3=}) 17. Bc1 (17. Rd1 $142 $5 $132) 17... f5 $32 {|^} 18. Qd3
Qd7 $15 {Topalov has achieved a promising position, which he systematically
improves after further inaccuracies from White.} 19. Rb1 (19. f3 Nf6 20. Nc2 f4
$15 (20... b5 $5 $36)) 19... Rae8 20. b3 Ng6 21. Bb2 $2 {
Natural, but allows Black to strengthen his grip on the position.} (21. f3 $142
Ne5 (21... Nf6 22. Bb2 $132) 22. Qc2 Nf6 23. Nd3 (23. Ng3 f4 24. Nf5 Nxd5 $1
25. Nxg7 Nb4 $17) (23. Bb2 f4 $15) 23... f4 $15) 21... Bxb2 22. Rxb2 Qg7 23.
Rc2 f4 {()>>,/\g4,f3->} 24. Nc3 {Now Black takes full control of the open <->e
and increases his advantage in the _|_.} ({
However, White's position is already very unpleasant even after} 24. f3 Nf6 25.
Qd1 Nh4 26. Rd2 Nf5 $17 {><e3,<->e}) 24... Nxc3 25. Qxc3 $8 (25. Rxc3 f3 $1 $40
{/\} 26. Nxf3 Nf4 27. Qd2 Qxc3 $19) 25... Qxc3 26. Rxc3 Re2 $17 {<->e} 27. a3
Rfe8 28. Nd3 Rd2 (28... Kf7 {/\Rd2,Kf6,Re4,Ne5 keeps both R on the board and
was possibly even better, White can hardly move.} 29. f3 $6 {/\Rf2 runs into}
Ra2 30. b4 Ree2 $19) (28... Ra2 29. b4 {/\} Ree2 $4 30. Nc1 $16) 29. Re1 {
Now White exchanges a pair of R, as now Black doesn't have Rd3. The _|_
however remains very difficult.} Rxe1+ 30. Nxe1 Ne5 31. h3 Kg7 32. Kf1 (32. Nf3
Rd1+ 33. Kh2 Nd3 $19) 32... Kf6 33. g4 (33. Nf3 Ra2 $17) 33... fxg3 $1 {
Black has to open the position to make progress.} 34. Rxg3 (34. fxg3 Rh2 35.
Nf3 Nxf3 $5 (35... Rxh3 36. Kg2 {><Rh3}) 36. Rxf3+ Ke5 37. Re3+ Kd4 38. Re6 Rb2
$17) 34... Kf5 35. Re3 h5 36. a4 (36. Nf3 Rd3 $1 37. Rxd3 (37. Ke2 Rxe3+ 38.
Kxe3 Nxf3 39. Kxf3 h4 $1 40. Ke3 (40. Ke2 Ke4 41. f3+ Kf4 42. Kf2 a6 43. b4
cxb4 44. axb4 Ke5 45. Ke3 a5 $19) 40... g4 (40... Ke5 $19) 41. hxg4+ Kxg4 42.
Ke2 Kf4 $19) 37... Nxd3 38. Kg2 Kf4 $17 {/-+}) 36... Rb2 37. Ng2 (37. Nf3 Ng6
$1 {/\Nf4-/+}) 37... h4 $1 {><h3} 38. Rc3 (38. Ne1 Ng6 (38... g4 $5 39. hxg4+
Kxg4 $19 {o^h4}) 39. Ng2 Nf4 40. Nxf4 gxf4 41. Re6 Rxb3 42. Rxd6 Rb4 $19) 38...
Ke4 39. Re3+ Kf5 40. Rc3 Rb1+ 41. Ke2 Rh1 42. Re3 a5 $22 (42... Ng6 $2 43. Re6
$1 $132 {/\Ne3}) 43. Rc3 (43. Ne1 Ng6 44. Nd3 Nf4+ 45. Nxf4 gxf4 46. Re6 (46.
Rc3 Ke4 {-see game}) 46... Rxh3 47. Rxd6 Rxb3 $19) 43... Ng6 $1 44. Rf3+ Nf4+
45. Nxf4 gxf4 $19 {_|_R,()} 46. Rc3 (46. Kd3 Rc1 47. Kd2 Ke4 $1 48. Rxf4+ (48.
Rd3 Rd1+ $19) 48... Kxf4 49. Kxc1 Kf3 $19) 46... Ke4 47. Kd2 Rb1 $22 48. f3+ (
48. Kc2 Rf1 $19) (48. Rd3 Rd1+ $19) (48. Ke2 f3+ $1 49. Kd2 (49. Rxf3 Rb2+ $19)
49... Rf1 50. Re3+ Kf4 51. Re6 Rxf2+ 52. Kd3 (52. Ke1 Re2+ $1 $19) 52... Rb2
$19) 48... Kf5 {Now the Ph3 is defenceless and the game is decided.} 49. Rc1
Rxb3 50. Re1 (50. Ke2 Rb2+ 51. Kf1 Rb4 $19) 50... Rxf3 51. Re6 Rxh3 52. Rxd6
Re3 {Cuts off White's K, the o^f4 will run.} 53. Rxb6 Re4 54. Kc3 (54. Kd3 Rd4+
55. Ke2 (55. Kc3 f3 $19) 55... Rxc4 $19) 54... f3 55. Rb8 h3 56. Rf8+ Kg4 57.
Kd3 (57. d6 Rd4 58. Rg8+ Kh4 59. Rh8+ Kg3 60. Rg8+ Kf2 $19) 57... Re1 (57...
Re1 58. Rg8+ Kh4 59. Rh8+ Kg3 60. Rg8+ Kh2 61. Rf8 Kg2 62. Rg8+ Kh1 63. Rf8 h2
64. Rxf3 Kg2 $19) 0-1

