1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. f3
Nbd7 9. Qd2 b5 10. O-O-O h5 11. Nd5 Bxd5 12. exd5 g6 (12... Nb6 13. Bxb6 Qxb6
14. Na5 (14. Kb1 g6 15. Bd3 Bh6 16. Qe1 (16. Qe2 O-O 17. h4 b4 18. g4 Be3 19.
Nd2 Bxd2 20. Qxd2 Nxd5 21. Ka1 Qe3 22. Be4 Qxd2 23. Rxd2 Ne3 24. Bxa8 Rxa8 25.
Re1 {1-0 Seps,M-Kradolfer,C/Scuol 2001/ (45)}) 16... O-O 17. Qh4 Kg7 18. Rhe1
a5 19. a3 Rfb8 20. Nd2 Bxd2 21. Rxd2 Qc5 22. Qf2 Qxf2 23. Rxf2 Ra7 24. Rd2 Rc7
25. Be2 Nd7 26. Bd1 Nc5 27. b3 f5 {
0-1 Sanchez,J-Chiong,L/Quezon City 1999/ (67)}) 14... Rc8 15. Kb1 Rc5 16. c4
bxc4 17. Nxc4 Qb7 18. Bd3 Be7 19. Ne3 g6 20. Rc1 Nd7 {
1-0 Leyva,R-Quesada,R/Holguin 1999/ (39)}) 13. Kb1 Nb6 $6 {Topalov will learn
to regret this standard move, since Kramnik comes out with a strong new idea.}
(13... Bg7 14. Na5 Qc7 15. Nc6 Nb6 16. Bxb6 Qxb6 17. Bd3 Rc8 18. Be4 $14) 14.
Qc3 $1 Be7 (14... Rc8 15. Bxb6 $18) (14... Nbxd5 15. Rxd5 $1 Rc8 16. Qd2 Nxd5
17. Qxd5 Bh6 18. Bxh6 Rxh6 19. Bd3 $16) 15. Qc6+ Nbd7 16. Bb6 $3 {The situation
is geting more serious, since tactics works miraculously for white.} Qxb6 (
16... Qc8 17. Bc7 Ra7 (17... O-O 18. Bxd6 Bxd6 19. Qxd6 Rd8 20. Na5 $16) 18.
Bxd6 Qxc6 19. dxc6 Bxd6 20. Rxd6 Ke7 21. Rxd7+ Nxd7 22. cxd7 Rxd7 23. Be2 $16)
17. Qxa8+ Nb8 (17... Bd8 18. Qc6 $18) 18. Na5 $1 Nfd7 (18... O-O 19. Nc6 Nxd5
20. Nxb8 Nc7 21. Qc6 $16) 19. Nc6 Bg5 20. Qa7 Nxc6 (20... Qxa7 21. Nxa7 Nb6 22.
Nc6 $16) 21. Qxb6 Nxb6 22. dxc6 Ke7 23. Rd3 Rc8 $2 {Serious innacuracy drags
black into difficult position, much stronger move 23...Nc4! promised chances
for survival.} (23... d5 24. Ra3 Ra8 25. c7 $1 Kd7 26. Rxa6 $1 Rxa6 27. Bxb5+
Kxc7 28. Bxa6 $18) (23... Nc4 $1 24. g3 Rc8 25. f4 exf4 26. Bg2 Ne5 27. Re1 h4
$14) 24. Ra3 Na4 (24... Rxc6 25. Rxa6 $18) (24... Ra8 25. c7 Kd7 26. Rxa6 $1
$18) 25. c4 $1 Rxc6 26. Be2 (26. cxb5 $4 Rc1#) 26... Rb6 27. cxb5 axb5 28. Bxb5
$1 {Kramnik is ruthless in the endgame and black notices with horror that
knight on b2 would be trapped.} Rxb5 (28... Nxb2 $2 29. Rb3 $1 $18) 29. Rxa4 f5
30. Rd1 Be3 (30... d5 31. Ra7+ Ke6 32. Ra6+ Kf7 33. a4 $18) 31. a3 d5 (31...
Bd4 32. b4 g5 33. Ra8 $18) 32. b4 d4 33. Ra5 $1 Rxa5 34. bxa5 Kd6 35. Kc2 e4 (
35... Kc5 36. Rb1 e4 37. a6 d3+ 38. Kd1 Kc6 39. Rb7 $18) 36. fxe4 fxe4 37. Re1
$1 {There is no defense against transfer into pawn ending.} (37. Re1 $1 Kc5 38.
Rxe3 dxe3 39. Kd1 Kb5 40. Ke2 Kxa5 41. Kxe3 $18) 1-0

