1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Bb4+ 4. Nbd2 O-O 5. a3 Bxd2+ 6. Bxd2 Ne4 7. e3 b6 8.
Bd3 Bb7 9. O-O Nxd2 10. Nxd2 f5 11. Qe2 Nc6 {The position is very solid for
black, but white has small advantage and activity on the queenside.} (11... Qf6
12. b4 Nc6 13. f4 a5 14. b5 Ne7 15. Nf3 Ng6 16. Rac1 d6 17. c5 bxc5 18. dxc5
Bxf3 19. Rxf3 d5 20. Bb1 Rfb8 21. a4 {1-0 Meister,T-Oravecz,I/Bayern 1997/ (42)
}) 12. Rac1 Qf6 (12... a5 13. b3 Qf6 14. c5 $14) 13. c5 Rae8 (13... a5 14. cxb6
cxb6 15. Nc4 Qd8 16. d5 $14) 14. b4 Kh8 (14... bxc5 15. Rxc5 Rc8 16. Rfc1 $16)
15. f4 g5 (15... Rc8 16. Nf3 bxc5 17. Rxc5 $14) 16. b5 $1 Na5 {Kasimdzhanov
was surely dreaming about better future for this knight, but at least black is
not losing a pawn.} (16... Ne7 17. cxb6 cxb6 18. Rc7 Bd5 19. Rxd7 gxf4 20. Rxf4
$16) 17. fxg5 Qxg5 18. Nf3 Qg7 (18... Bxf3 19. Rxf3 bxc5 20. Rxc5 $16) 19. cxb6
cxb6 20. Rc7 Rc8 21. Rfc1 (21. Rxc8 Rxc8 22. Qb2 Nc4 $14) 21... Rxc7 22. Rxc7
Rc8 23. Rxc8+ Bxc8 24. e4 $1 Bb7 (24... fxe4 25. Bxe4 Bb7 26. Bxb7 Nxb7 27. Qc2
$16) 25. h3 (25. exf5 Bxf3 26. Qxf3 Qxd4+ 27. Kh1 Qa1+ 28. Bf1 Kg7 29. Qd3 exf5
30. Qxd7+ Kg6 31. Qe6+ $14) 25... d6 26. Qc2 (26. exf5 Bxf3 27. Qxf3 Qxd4+ 28.
Kh1 Qa1+ 29. Kh2 Qe5+ 30. g3 Qb2+ $14) 26... Qf6 27. Kf2 fxe4 28. Bxe4 Bxe4 29.
Qxe4 {Topalov was very carefully avoiding endgames, that were better but may
be not sufficiently so. Black is suffering due to his misserable knight on a5.}
Kg7 (29... Qe7 30. g4 $14) 30. Qc2 Qf7 31. Ke2 h6 (31... e5 32. dxe5 dxe5 33.
Qd3 Nc4 34. Ng5 Qh5+ 35. g4 Qxg5 36. Qxc4 $14) 32. a4 Qb7 33. g4 (33. Ke1 Qe7
34. Qc3 Nb7 35. g4 $14) 33... Qf7 34. Qc3 Kh7 (34... Qb7 35. h4 Qf7 (35... Qe4+
36. Kf2 Qxg4 37. Qc7+ Kg6 38. Qxd6) 36. g5 $16) 35. h4 Kg7 36. h5 (36. g5 hxg5
37. hxg5 Qb7 38. Ke3 Qf7 39. Qd3 $14) 36... Kg8 37. Qc1 e5 $6 {
The defender is opting for the desperate trick in a difficult position.} (37...
Kh7 38. g5 Qxh5 39. Qc7+ Kg6 40. gxh6 Kxh6 41. Qxd6 $16) 38. Qxh6 (38. dxe5
dxe5 39. Nxe5 Qa2+ 40. Ke3 Qb3+ 41. Kf2 $18) 38... e4 39. Ng5 $2 {Topalov is
ssing a chance to keep the lid on a5 knight a winning with his strong g and h
pawns.} (39. Nd2 $1 d5 40. Ke1 Qe7 41. Qg6+ Kh8 42. g5 $18) 39... Qa2+ 40. Ke3
(40. Kf1 Qc4+ 41. Kf2 Qxd4+ 42. Kg3 Qe3+ 43. Kh4 Qf2+ $11) 40... Nc4+ 41. Kxe4
